title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs and salad oil. Stir until dry ingredients are moistened. Stir in vanilla, pineapple and 1 cup walnuts and bananas.
Spoon batter into 3 well-greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Cool for 10 minutes. Frost and top with remaining bananas and walnuts.

title: holiday butter cookies
directions: Sift together flour and baking powder.
Cream butter; add sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend well.
Add sifted dry ingredients gradually, mixing well.
Chill thoroughly (at least 4 hours).
Roll out very thin on well floured surface and cut out with flour dusted cookie cutters.
Place on lightly buttered baking sheet.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 6 to 8 minutes until brown around edges.

title: clam chowder
directions: Place potatoes in medium saucepan. Add enough cold water to cover. Bring to a boil.
Simmer until tender, 20 minutes. Drain. Cook bacon and onion in heavy 2-quart saucepan over medium-high heat until onion is tender, stirring occasionally, about 8 minutes.
Mix in flour and cook 2 minutes. Add juices from clams, bottled clam juice, cream and milk.
Bring to a boil. Stir in clams and potatoes; heat through.

title: easter bunny cake
directions: Mix and bake cake as directed on package.
Cool well.
Use one layer as bunny face.
Cut other layer for ears and bow tie.
Frost all cake.
Decorate with your own ideas.
Children enjoy helping.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into two 9-inch unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pink thing
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.
Spoon into pudding dishes or parfait glasses.
Serves 8.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Do not add salt.

title: fun time juice punch
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients in a very large container.
Add the 7-Up.
Add enough water to make 6 gallons.

title: toffee
directions: Combine butter, sugar, syrup and water.
Heat, stirring constantly	until boiling.	Boil to 300° (brittle stage, about 20 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Pour immediately on 10 x 15 x 1-inch pan lined with aluminum foil.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top until melted.
Spread evenly.
Sprinkle ground pecans on top. Cool.
Break into pieces.
Yield:
1 1/2 pounds.

title: strawberry pancakes(dedicated for brandon shaw)
directions: Mix ingredients (except for strawberries).
Cook on griddle or in skillet.
Place 5 sliced strawberries on uncooked side of pancake.
Cook as usual.
Serve with syrup or Strawberry Glaze.

title: avocado meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in loaf pan and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Remove from oven; put cheese slices on top and bake again for another 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In separate bowl, mix 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg. Beat well.
Blend dry ingredients and add to margarine mixture. Stir well.
Shape dough into balls.
Roll in cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook sausage; drain.
Add Ragu to sausage; simmer.
Boil noodles until tender.
Mix cottage cheese with egg.
Layer noodles, meat sauce, cottage cheese and cheeses two times, ending with cheeses covering top.
Bake at 375° until bubbly.

title: pecan balls
directions: Roll peanut butter into balls, then roll peanut balls into chopped pecans.

title: divinity
directions: First, stir sugar into corn syrup, water and salt until dissolved.
Boil to medium ball stage (240°).
Slowly pour 1/2 over 2 stiffly beaten egg whites, beating constantly.
Second, cook remaining syrup to very hard ball stage.
(Test a few drops in water.
It should form a firm ribbon that bends when lifted from water.)
Beat syrup into candy mixture, continue beating until stiff.
Third, cool for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
When mixture holds its shape when dropped from spoon, add vanilla.
Drop from teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Makes 4 dozen pieces.

title: orange bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a small bowl and set aside. Separate biscuits; gently separate individual biscuits in half. Place a cream cheese square between 2 halves, pinching sides to seal. Dip in butter and dredge in reserved sugar mixture. Stand biscuits on edge in a lightly greased 12-cup Bundt pan, spacing evenly. Drizzle with remaining butter and sprinkle with remaining sugar mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown. Immediately invert onto a serving plate.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and put into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix next 3 ingredients and pour over cake mix in pan.

title: cream dried beef gravy
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add dried beef and brown on medium to medium-high heat.
Sprinkle on flour and brown.
Turn heat to low and add milk.
Cook and stir until thick.
Add pepper to taste.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix cream cheese, dry Ranch dressing and fresh green onions and spread on floured tortillas.
On top of each divide and spread chopped pimento and green chilies.
Roll tightly, jelly roll style, and slice.
May be served with warm or cold salsa.

title: partridge pie with oysters
directions: In a stew pot, cover partridges with water and stew over low heat until tender (about 30 minutes).
Remove partridges and reserve broth.
Drain oysters and save liquor.

title: fruit and marshmallow
directions: Fold together all ingredients.
Chill for 1 1/2 hours and serve.

title: coleslaw dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients a few minutes until mixture thickens a little.
Add 1/2 cup vinegar.
Yields 1 pint.

title: best ever barbecues
directions: Brown meat.
Add rest of ingredients in a roaster.
If electric roaster is used, cook at 400° to 500° for two hours.
If put in oven, bake at 350° for 2 to 3 hours.
Yields 6 to 7 servings per pound with large buns and 8 or 9 servings with small buns.

title: cheddar cheese vegetable soup
directions: In hot butter in 3-quart saucepan cook carrots, onion and potatoes, covered and stirring occasionally, about 25 minutes or until tender.
(Put carrots in first).
Add peas and remove from heat; stir in flour and mix well.
Cook 1 minute, stirring occasionally.
Add chicken broth.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir in cheese; cook over medium heat until cheese has melted.
Gradually add milk.
Season.
Bring to boil, but do not boil.
Serve with croutons.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Stir butter to soften.
Gradually add sugar, creaming until light and fluffy.
Add eggs.
Mix all dry ingredients together and blend into egg mixture while adding tomato soup.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Bake in a greased and floured pan.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Frost or sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Bakes best in round tube pan.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichokes.
Mix all ingredients by hand.
Bake at 350° in pie dish until cheese is melted or top is light golden.

title: healthy oat 'n blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Place oats in blender and grind (stir occasionally).
Line 12 muffin cups with paper baking cups. Combine dry ingredients.
Add blueberries and remaining ingredients.
Mix until just moistened.
Bake 20 to 22 minutes. Makes 1 dozen.
Freezes well.
Microwave on High for 30 seconds per muffin.

title: kentucky chicken casserole
directions: Place in 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with Pepperidge Farm dressing.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: tater tot hamburg casserole
directions: Brown hamburg and salt in skillet.
Cook vegetables according to package.
Add hamburg to vegetables and add soup also.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and place Tater Tots on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: boston salad with fruit and shrimp
directions: Peel grapefruit and oranges.
Divide into wedges.
In a salad bowl, combine all ingredients.
Coat with a light dressing.

title: april's favorite cranberry sauce
directions: In a large saucepan, bring liquids and sugar to a boil, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Add 1 1/2 packages cranberries; return to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer until berries begin to pop. Add remaining cranberries and orange zest.
Simmer for 5 minutes. Remove from heat; cool at room temperature, then refrigerate.

title: anise loaf
directions: Soften dry yeast in warm water and set aside.
Pour scalded milk over sugar, butter and salt, stirring until butter melts. Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in flavorings.
Add 1 cup of the flour; mix well.
Stir in 1 egg and softened yeast; beat well.
Add remaining flour or enough to make a soft dough.
Turn out on lightly floured surface.

title: creamy scalloped potatoes
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, alternate layers of potatoes and onion.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over potatoes.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes.

title: joy's poppy seed chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 4 ingredients and spread half of the mixture in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Next, put the cubed chicken on top of the stuffing.
Mix the last 3 ingredients and put on top of the chicken.
Top with the remaining stuffing.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Very yummy!

title: cookie icing
directions: Into powdered sugar add enough
water
(approximately 1 tablespoon) to make icing easy to
force
through pastry tube, yet hold its shape.
Tint with coloring, if desired.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Throw everything into 6 cups of boiling water.
Stir everything, so the rice doesn't stick.
Put a lid on the pan and bring the pot to another boil.
Turn the stove down to a simmer. Simmer for about one hour.
Yum!

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Unroll and spread rolls over a pizza pan.
Cook enough hash browns to cover rolls.
Layer potatoes on rolls.
Brown, drain and layer sausage on potatoes.
Sprinkle cheese on top of sausage. Beat eggs well and pour over pizza.
Bake at 350° until eggs are done and cheese has melted.

title: country dirt cake
directions: Empty Oreos into a "brown paper bag".
Beat with a hammer until well crushed.
Then set them aside for a few minutes.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Put all the ingredients in a bowl and beat well with a beater. Pour batter into a 10-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Serve warm with Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream.

title: honey beef
directions: In large skillet over medium-high heat, cook sliced beef, red pepper, spinach, green onions and parsnip in 2 teaspoons hot oil, stirring constantly, 2 to 3 minutes until meat is brown.
Remove from skillet; keep warm.
In same skillet in remaining, 1 teaspoon oil, cook garlic and ginger 1 minute.
In small bowl, stir well soy sauce, honey, cornstarch and 2 tablespoons cold water.
Return meat and vegetable mixture to skillet.
Add soy sauce mixture. Cook 1 to 2 minutes until heated through and thickened.

title: two bean chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken, coat large skillet with spray.
Put on medium-high until hot.
Add chicken and cook 3 minutes on each side unti lightly browned.
Remove chicken.
Set aside.
Wipe skillet with paper towel.
Coat skillet with spray; when hot.
Add onion and garlic.
Saute 1 minute.
Add green beans, chickpeas, tomatoes and oregano; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 30 to 35 minutes.
Yields two servings.

title: black-eyed pea salsa
directions: Mix all together. Chill and serve with Fritos or tortilla chips. May also pour into pretty jars and seal for great gift ideas.

title: crab and shrimp dip
directions: Blend ingredients; chill for at least 3 hours (better if overnight).
Serve with wheat crackers.
This is really a crowd pleaser.

title: london broil
directions: Marinate for 4 to 6 hours, then broil or put on grill.
Slice into thin slices.

title: quick strawberry cake
directions: Mix jello according
to
directions
on
box.
Place in bowl and
let
set
in refrigerator until begins to set.
Pour half over
bottom of cake.
Put cake together and pour remaining jello over cake;	pour strawberries over cake.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: gayle's upside-down popover pizza
directions: Heat
oven
Cook meat and onion; drain.
Stir in tomato
sauce,
spices
and the 2 tablespoons flour.
Heat until boiling; boil 1 minute.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Arrange Mozzarella cheese on top.
Beat eggs, milk, oil, the 1 cup flour
and
salt
until
smooth.
Pour
over cheese. Sprinkle with Parmesan
cheese.
Bake
until
puffy and golden brown, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chop suey
directions: Tenderize meat.
Put butter in pan and cook meat 10 to 15 minutes.
Add onion and celery. Stir in soy sauce and water.
Add sugar and cornstarch and stir until thick.
More cornstarch can be added to thicken gravy.
Serve over rice.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix ingredients together with spoon.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve hot.
You may use all fresh vegetables, instead of cream of mushroom soup use cream of celery, or you may add canned chicken or ham for an alternative.

title: orange delight
directions: Drain pineapple.
Cut mandarin orange slices in half.
Combine pineapple, oranges, cheese and jello.
Add enough Cool Whip to desired consistency.
Chill for 2 hours before serving.

title: sugar pecans
directions: Beat lightly the egg white and cold water.
Mix together brown sugar, sugar, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Turn pecan halves in egg white mixture.
Then turn in sugar mixture.
Spread on ungreased cookie sheet in single layer. Bake at 250° for 50 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet and cool on wax paper in single layer.
Freezes well and makes wonderful Christmas gifts for friends!

title: wild mushroom soup
directions: Separate the stems from the caps of the wild mushrooms.
Do not wash the mushrooms, but rub them with a dry cloth; reserve the tops.
In a heavy 10-inch skillet over medium heat, saute the wild mushroom stems, shallots, onions and button mushrooms in the olive oil or butter.
After 1 minute, lower the heat and simmer for 5 minutes or until most of the liquid evaporates.
Deglaze with sherry by pouring it over the mushroom mixture and scraping the sides of the pan.
Incorporate the mushroom pieces into the liquid. Add the hot stock or broth.
Simmer 3 minutes or until mushrooms are very soft.
Place the mushroom stem mixture into the food processor and puree until smooth.
Return the mixture to the pot and add the cream.
Dice the reserved mushroom caps and add them to the soup.
Simmer until the soup has thickened slightly, 5 to 10 minutes.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
To serve, ladle into warmed bowls and garnish with chopped tarragon or a swirl of creme fraiche.
Serves 4.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Beat sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add sour cream and flavorings.
Beat in flour and beat for about 5 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: spritz
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, milk, vanilla and almond. Beat well.
Add flour and baking powder to cream mixture.
Mix until smooth; use cookie press.
Put on ungreased cookie sheets and top with jelly or candy or add jello to mixture.

title: vegetable rotini
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, gradually stir soup into cream cheese. Add milk, mustard and pepper.
Over low heat, heat through, stirring often.
Add rotini, vegetable and Parmesan cheese.
Heat through.

title: tex-mex cornbread salad
directions: Prepare cornbread according to package directions.
Crumble 1/2 of cornbread into bottom of a large serving bowl.
Top with half of beans.

title: beef, rice and beans ole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in oil or shortening.
Add beans, barbecue sauce and salt.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add water and rice.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat, cover and cook for 8 minutes or until rice is tender.
Serves 4.

title: no cook peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Shape into cookies.
They are ready to eat.

title: mexican yum yum
directions: Spread cream cheese in bottom of microwavable dish.
Spread chili over this. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top of that. Microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Dip Doritos into this.

title: beef shanghi
directions: Stir-fry beef in oil.
When done (approximately 3 minutes), then add cornstarch; chop scallions.
Add onions, soy sauce, bouillon and rice to beef in a deep fryer or wok; sprinkle with pepper (water chestnuts optional).
Turn on low heat and cover. Simmer for 20 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: just plum apples
directions: Peel, core and dice apples.
Mix sugar, flour, juice from lemon, cinnamon and 1/2 butter.
Add apples and plums; mix gently. Pour into flat baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Spread over apple and plum mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool and cut crispies into squares.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix flour, powder, soda, salt and sugar in a large bowl.
Cut in margarine with a pastry blender until mixture forms small crumbs.
Add buttermilk.
Mix just enough to make a soft dough. Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead a few times.

(Don't knead too much or biscuits will be dry and hard!) Roll the dough out to a 6 x 8-inch shape and place it on an ungreased cookie sheet. With a sharp knife, cut the dough into 12 equal pieces but do not separate.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: chicken and vegies casserole
directions: Mix all together. Bake for 1 hour, covered, at 300°.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Mix cornstarch and milk; stir until smooth.
Add margarine, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil for 1 minute.
Add Cheddar cheese.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs; mix well and add flour gradually. Add vanilla, apples and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a tube pan.

title: holiday apple salad
directions: Mix all well and chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: sausage-cheese party snacks
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease a baking sheet.
Mix above ingredients in a bowl and knead.
Shape into 1 1/2 inch balls.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Drain. Serve hot.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Put ingredients together (except chips) and pour dressing over.
Mix well.
Just before serving, crunch chips over salad and mix.
Makes 10 servings.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix pineapple, flour, sugar and some syrup. Pour into buttered casserole dish. Crush stack of Ritz crackers.

title: zucchini bake(yellow squash)
directions: Mix all ingredients
together
except
stuffing mix and margarine.
Put in 8 x
12-inch pan.
Mix margarine and stuffing mix.
Put on top and bake in 350° oven 30 minutes or until bubbling.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix together all ingredients and bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: banana boats
directions: Combine peanuts, coconut, 1/4 cup powdered sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Unroll crescent dough and separate into 4 rectangles. Place rectangles of dough on ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle peanut mixture over each dough rectangle.
Dip each banana half in lemon juice, then maple syrup.
Place each banana half on narrow end of dough rectangle and roll up, ending with seam-side down. Pinch edges well to seal.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup powdered sugar while warm.
Cut each roll into 2 or 4 pastries.

title: crunchy oven baked chicken
directions: Combine crumbs, cheese, salt, pepper and parsley flakes.
Mix well to combine.
Dip chicken pieces in melted butter, then roll in crumb mixture.
Arrange chicken in shallow baking dish, skin side up.
Pour remaining butter over chicken and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Do not turn chicken.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Combine water or soy milk, flour and cornstarch or arrowroot in a saucepan and cook until thickened.
Cool.
In a blender, put lemon juice, onion powder, salt, garlic powder and oregano.
Add all ingredients from the saucepan with those in blender.
Mix well and chill.
If you want to make mustard, add a little turmeric.

title: spinach casserole with water chestnuts
directions: Wash spinach well and remove tough stems.
Cook with 1 tablespoon water and 1 teaspoon salt for 10 minutes, or until tender.
Drain well and chop fine.
(If using frozen spinach, prepare according to package directions; drain well.)
Return drained spinach to pan.
Add water chestnuts, 3 tablespoons butter, cream and seasonings to taste.
Place in a buttered casserole.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Pour milk over bread and allow to stand 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Form into a loaf and place on a rack in a shallow roasting pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.
Total fat:
9 grams.

title: lemon delight
directions: Blend together flour, margarine and 1/2 cup pecans.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Blend together cream cheese, powdered sugar and half of 9 ounce carton of whipped topping.
Spread over crust.
Combine pudding mix with lemon juice and milk.
Pour over previous layers.
When firm, top with remainder of whipped topping.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup pecans. Chill overnight and keep in refrigerator.

title: diabetic peanut butter cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package and add peanut butter. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until done.
Makes 10 servings. Exchanges:
1 serving:
1 bread, 2 fat and 169 calories.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, arrange the pie filling and pineapple (do not drain).
Cover with the cake mix (dry).
Slice the margarine into pats on top of the mix and sprinkle with nuts. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Mix dressing mix and cream cheese until thoroughly mixed. Wash, pat dry and cut celery into small pieces.
Fill with cream cheese mixture.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix
eggs,
sugar, flour and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir in evaporated milk.
Since raw eggs are in homemade ice cream, you now
must cook the egg mixture at least 8 minutes or until mixture reaches
Pour
into a gallon freezer bucket and finish filling to the line marked on bucket with regular milk. Place in ice
bucket
and
layer ice and rock salt around it. Ice cream
is ready
when electric motor stops (about 20 minutes).

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: In blender, thoroughly blend all ingredients.
Store in the refrigerator in a covered container for up to 1 week.
Use instead of canned sweetened condensed milk in cooked recipes.
Will take the place of Eagle Brand milk.

title: honey mustard slaw
directions: Dressing:
Stir mayonnaise, sour cream, honey and Dijon mustard.
Cover and chill.

title: garbage(a party snack)
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients and mix.
Blend and mix well the cereal, raisins and nuts.
Pour chocolate mixture over dry ingredients.
Stir well until coated. Pour powdered sugar into garbage bag.
Add mixture.
Shake bag vigorously to blend.
Add more powdered sugar, if needed.
Store in airtight container. Freezes well.

title: sparkling white-grape lemon punch
directions: Combine thawed juices and water.
Add soda and stir gently. Garnish with lemon slices.

title: banana pudding
directions: Whip sour cream, 1/2 small bowl of Cool Whip, pudding and milk together with electric mixer.
Layer in dish with banana slices and vanilla wafers.
Top with remaining 1/2 bowl of Cool Whip.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Combine Jell-O and water; stir.
Add blueberries and pineapple with juices; mix well.
Chill until firm.

title: awase zu for sushi meshi (rice)
directions: Heat ingredients
until
salt
and sugar are dissolved. Cool and fold
into
the
hot rice, being careful to keep rice grain whole.

title: rave reviews coconut cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding mix, water, eggs and oil in large mixer bowl. Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes. Stir in coconut and pecans and pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch pans. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Cool in pan 15 minutes; remove and cool on rack. Frost with Coconut Cream Frosting.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Blend cheese and picante sauce.
Spread on tortillas.
Roll and chill.

title: plum cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Gradually add flour and spices.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and fold in plum baby food and nuts.
Bake in a tube pan for approximately 1 hour at 350°.

title: country fried steak
directions: Combine meat, 1 tablespoon salt, pepper and 3/4 cup flour. Mix well.
Roll out with rolling pin about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into 4 x 4-inch pieces.
Place in hot oil in skillet.
Cook until lightly brown.
Remove from skillet.
Add remaining flour and cook until browned.
Add milk and remaining salt and cook until thick. Pour the gravy over the steak.
Yields 5 servings.

title: australian outback salad
directions: Place salad greens on individual plates.
Sprinkle with carrots, avacoda, oranges and pineapple.
Serve with creamy dressing.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Layer first 3 ingredients in a buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole. Beat eggs, milk and mustard.
Pour over top and refrigerate 2 hours or overnight.
Bake at 325°, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Great for busy mornings, such as Christmas.

title: a different cheesecake
directions: Combine melted butter and graham cracker crumbs, and press into bottom of cake pan.
Save just a small amount.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add Cool Whip and mix until smooth. Pour into pan with cracker crumbs, and spread cherry pie filling in the center and sprinkle the remaining crumbs on edges.

title: rhubarb matrimonial bars
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add sugar and oatmeal. Cut in butter until it is crumbly.
Put half of this in bottom of pan.
Cover with 2 quarts of young tender rhubarb, cut fine and mixed with 1 cup of granulated sugar.
Cover with remainder of crumbs.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven until a deep golden color. Let cool.
Cut and serve.

title: cheese twirls
directions: Roll process cheese spread between two pieces of wax paper to form a 9 x 12-inch rectangle.
Beat cream cheese, olives and cilantro until well blended.
Spread over process cheese spread. Roll up starting at narrow side to form 9-inch roll.
Garnish with additional cilantro, if desired.
Chill, covered, until firm. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in large casserole. Sprinkle with bread crumbs and cook about 30 minutes at 350°. Serves 12.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Add all remaining ingredients except strawberries and blend with mixer.
Add strawberries after completely mixed.
(Add red food coloring if you want a redder color.)
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: bombay turkey
directions: In medium skillet, melt butter.
Add curry and heat 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in onion and cook until tender but not brown. Blend in flour, salt and pepper, stirring well.
Add chicken broth all at once.
Cook and stir until boiling; cook 2 minutes longer. Add cooked turkey and shredded lemon peel.
Heat mixture to boiling.
Cook rice according to package directions.
Stir in cashew nuts and pimiento.
Serve mixture over rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cone cakes
directions: You will need a cupcake tin and cupcake papers.

title: lady cabbage
directions: Saute onion in margarine in large pan for 2 minutes.
Add cabbage, water and salt.
Cover pan, cook quickly for 10 minutes or just until cabbage is crispy tender.
Stir in milk; serve hot.

title: mother's cake recipe
directions: Mix together, adding enough flour to make a thin batter. Makes enough batter for a 3 to 4 thin layer cake.
Very good for coconut cake.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut round steak into thin strips.
Dust with flour.
In large skillet, brown meat in oleo.
Add mushrooms, onions and garlic. Brown lightly.
Stir in beef broth.
Cover and cook 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Stir now and then.
Gradually stir in sour cream.
Cook over low heat 5 minutes.
Serve over rice or cooked noodles.

title: beef bourguignon
directions: Cut beef into 1 1/2-inch cubes; place in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine wine, 1 cup water, soup and soup mix; stir well and pour over beef.
Stir in mushrooms.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Add green pepper, onions and garlic powder.
Cover and bake an additional 30 minutes.
Stir in cherry tomatoes.
Garnish with parsley sprigs.
Serve over rice.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: mom's chocolate pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven 350°. Mix ingredients, then pour into ungreased 8 x 8 Pyrex dish.

title: sotangjon
directions: Saute the garlic and onion in hot oil.
Add the pieces of chicken and cook 5 minutes.
Pour water and add the vegetables. Let boil.
When chicken is tender, remove from broth and flake the meat.
Strain broth.
Press vegetables, through a sieve to get all the flavor.
Season with salt, ajinomoto and patis.
Pour back chicken meat, add taingang daga, mushroom and sotangjon.
Boil 10 minutes.
Serve hot with Biscocho.

title: german sauerkraut
directions: Chop bacon into small squares and fry at medium heat in large saucepan until brown.
Do not drain fat!
Drain excess water from sauerkraut, and if necessary, rinse out excess salt with cold water.
Stir the sauerkraut into the bacon and grease.
Add the chopped onion, 2 pinches of garlic powder and enough salt and pepper to season.
Slowly cook for about 45 to 60 minutes, stirring occasionally, or until sauerkraut becomes tender.
Serves approximately 4 to 6 people.

title: creole cabbage rolls
directions: Core cabbage and place in boiling salted water until 12 outer leaves can be separated.
Set them aside; reserve water.
Chop remainder of cabbage.
Mix ground beef, rice, minced onion, parsley, salt, pepper, Tabasco and egg.
Divide mixture into 12 parts and place in cabbage leaves, making rolls by folding in the sides and rolling up.
Place rolls, seam side down in a 2-quart casserole on top of chopped cabbage.
Saute garlic, chopped onion and green pepper in butter for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes, honey and lemon juice.
Simmer gently 10 minutes, then stir in 1 cup of cabbage water and spoon over cabbage rolls.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Chill in refrigerator overnight. Serve with crackers.

title: apple burritos
directions: Spray jelly roll pan with Pam.
Place 1 tablespoon apple pie filling in flour tortilla and roll.
Place, open side down, in pan.

title: quick applesauce-bran bread
directions: Place in large mixing bowl the first 4 ingredients; beat until fluffy.
Add eggs.
On wax paper, combine flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
In small bowl, combine applesauce and bran. Blend flour into creamed mixture alternately with applesauce and bran.
Stir in raisins.
Turn batter into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes, or until loaf tests done.

title: vegetable sauce
directions: Melt butter or oleo in saucepan; blend in flour and mustard. Add milk; stir over heat until thick.
Add salt and green vegetables or garnish with parsley.
Pour over servings of pie like a gravy.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Rinse chicken with cold water; pat dry with paper towels. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Heat oil in large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and cook, covered, for about 6 minutes, turning once, until golden brown. Remove from skillet.

title: strawberries romanoff
directions: Sprinkle strawberries with sugar; stir gently.
Refrigerate 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Just before serving, beat whipped cream until stiff, pouring orange juice in slowly.
Fold in the strawberries. Makes 6 servings.

title: evelyn's cheese log
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients.
Divide into 2 parts; shape in logs or balls.
Roll in mixture of the chili powder, paprika and chopped pecans.
Garnish with cherries or pecan halves.

title: pineapple-cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese, pineapple, green pepper, onion and salt; mix well. Chill.
Shape into a 4-inch ball and roll in chopped pecans.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Spread on cake.

title: easy and good no knead yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and set aside.
Cream next three ingredients with fork.
Add egg and cream again.
Add dissolved yeast to this mixture.
Then add flour.
Mix until well blended. Put a small amount of oil in large bowl; coat sides.
Put mixture in oiled bowl.
Let rise 2 hours or doubled.
Punch down and roll out on floured surface to about 1 1/2 inches thick.
Place on baking sheet close together and let rise 2 hours.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Microwave bacon on High 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain bacon.
Add okra and onion to small amount of bacon drippings.
Cover and microwave on High 9 minutes or until tender-crisp, stirring after 4 minutes.
Add tomatoes and next 4 ingredients.
Cover and microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Let stand covered 5 minutes. Sprinkle crumbled bacon on top.

title: holiday salad
directions: Melt red hots in boiling water.
Add gelatin and stir in applesauce.
Chill until firm in an 8-inch mold or pour into individual serving dishes.
Unmold on plate.
Serve with whipped cream or sour cream.

title: baked chicken dinner
directions: Brown the chicken
in
butter or margarine.
Remove the chicken and add the onion
and
rice to the pan;
brown, stirring. Add the soups,
carrots
and
frozen
peas.
Salt
and pepper to taste.
Put the
chicken
in a baking dish and cover with soup mixture.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: a happy home recipe
directions: Take love and loyalty; mix thoroughly with faith.
Blend it with tenderness, kindness and understanding.
Gently stir in forgiveness.
Add friendship and hope.
Season heavily with work, play and laughter.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Peel and dice sweet potatoes.
Boil sweet potatoes until tender.
Drain sweet potatoes and mash potatoes until smooth, using milk, butter, salt and pepper.
Mix in crushed pineapple. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with marshmallows and bake for 15 minutes.

title: vegetable filled zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini in half, scoop out pulp and dice.
Saute in butter with mushrooms, carrots, onions, salt and pepper.
Stir in cheese.
Fill shells, place in narrow baking dish.
Pour water around the zucchini.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: cheesy ham quiche
directions: Bake pie shell for 3 minutes. Remove from oven and gently prick with fork.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Let cool on a rack. Place ham in pie shell. Top with cheese and sprinkle with nutmeg. Beat eggs until foamy. Stir in half and half and seasonings.
Pour over cheese and ham.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm.

title: low-fat banana bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a food processor or blender puree 2 bananas.
Spray a shallow 2-quart baking dish with cooking spray; add bread cubes.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Form into patties and bake 10 to 15 minutes at 450°.

title: chocolate cream cake
directions: Mix all together and bake in 3 layers at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: red cinnamon pickles
directions: Soak pickles in mixture overnight.
Boil pickle mixture 40 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.
This recipe is really good for overgrown cucumbers.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine sugar and cereal. Melt peanut butter and butter; pour over dry ingredients, then mix. Shape into bite size balls. Melt chocolate bits and paraffin in double boiler over low heat. Dip balls in chocolate. Place on waxed paper to cool.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Let
eggs and butter sit until they are
room
temperature. Cream together butter and Crisco.
Add eggs, one
at
a time, creaming
after
each
other.
Add brown
sugar.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add flour and baking powder mixture alternately
with
milk
to
sugar mixture.
Bake
in greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: super supper
directions: Mix potato flakes, sour cream and water.
Press mixture firmly in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown beef; pour off excess fat. Drain corn and add with remaining ingredients except cheese. Spoon meat over potato mixture.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: Line 15 cupcake pans with cupcake liners.
Place a vanilla wafer in bottom of each liner.

title: egg pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together (except oleo) and pour into the buttered pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: cheeseburger rice
directions: Brown meat and onion in large skillet on medium-high heat; drain fat. Stir in water, ketchup, mustard, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil. Stir in rice; cover. Remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes. Fluff with fork. Sprinkle with cheese; cover. Let stand 3 minutes or until cheese melts.
Garnish with lettuce, pickles and tomato slices, if desired.

title: frosted grape clusters
directions: Separate grape bunches into small clusters.
Wash and pat dry with
paper towels.
Dip grapes into egg whites.
Combine gelatin and spice.
Sprinkle over grapes.
Dry on cake rack or baking sheets in cool place.
Makes 12 servings.

title: easy chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine chicken and 1/2 cup enchilada sauce; cook until chicken is done.
Stir in green chiles.
In a separate skillet bring remaining enchilada sauce to a boil and remove from heat, dip each tortilla into heated sauce to soften.
Spoon 2 tablespoons chicken and 1/4 cup cheese down center of tortilla. Roll, place tortillas, seam-side down in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Pour remaining enchilada sauce over top and sprinkle with remaining cup of cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 servings.

title: broiled fish
directions: Brush cooking oil over the fish and sprinkle with paprika and a liberal amount of garlic powder.
Place the fish about 3-inches from the heat source and broil about 10 minutes on each side.
A sprinkle of lemon juice will improve the flavor of the fish.

title: jambalaya
directions: In large frying pan (with lid), saute onion, green and red pepper and diced celery in hot olive oil/oleo mixture, until soft. Add tomatoes, corn, okra, diced ham and/or chicken.
Simmer 20 minutes.
add shrimp; simmer 7 minutes.
Test shrimp for doneness.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Separate cabbage leaves and blanch in boiling water until limp.
Remove and drain.
Cut into large leaves, removing tough vein.
Mix together ground beef, rice, salt, pepper, onion, cinnamon and basil.
For each roll, use an amount about the size of a finger.
Squeeze together and place on leaf.
Fold in tips of leaf and roll.
Put in heavy pot and arrange in layers.
Add tomatoes, water to cover, 1 chopped clove garlic and sliced lemon, arranging on top of rolls.
Put a plate on top of cabbage rolls to anchor them.
Cook slowly for about 1 hour.

title: deep dish peach pie
directions: Place peaches in shallow baking dish, about 1 1/2-quart capacity.
Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Add lemon juice and dot with butter.
Cover with pastry, rolled thin, to fit the top.
Cut gashes in pastry for steam to escape.
Brush with milk.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 35 minutes or until peaches are tender.

title: boiled chocolate delights
directions: Melt margarine over medium heat and remove.
Blend sugar, cocoa, milk and add to melted margarine.
Cook for 2 minutes after full boil begins.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and quick oats. Mix well.
Drop from spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Refrigerate until ready to serve as refreshments.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour into baking dish.

title: beef noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown beef and drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat slowly until bouillon cube is dissolved. Transfer to large mixing bowl before adding noodles.
Stir in noodles.
Pour into greased 8 x 12 x 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: nutty stuffing
directions: In a large bowl, toss together the bread cubes or crumbs, giblets, almonds, sunflower seeds, celery and onion.
In a small bowl, combine the melted butter, chicken broth and Spike or seasoning salt.
Pour over the bread cubes mixture and toss to combine well.
Place in a buttered baking dish and bake, covered with foil for the last hour the poultry is cooking.
If you want crunchy stuffing, remove the foil for last half hour of baking. Serves 4 to 6.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Place cucumbers, onions and pepper in large pot.
Combine sugar, vinegar and spices.
Add to mixture in the pot.
Bring to a boil, stirring to mix.
Place in hot Ball jars, leaving 1/4-inch space at top.
Process 15 minutes in hot water bath to seal jars.

title: lemon snow bars
directions: In medium bowl, combine crust ingredients.
Mix on low speed until blended.
Pat into ungreased 8 inch square baking pan.
Bake for 15-20 minutes or until brown on edges.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Grease cookie sheet, 10 x 15 x 2-inch.
Line with wax paper. Grease paper.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat until creamy the eggs and sugar.
Add pumpkin, soda, cinnamon and flour.
Pour batter on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts if desired.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on tea towel.
Remove cake from oven and flip on towel.
Remove wax paper.
Roll in log shape and set aside to cool for 1 1/2 hours.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Put in roaster.
Cover and cook at 300° for 6 to 7 hours.

title: mother's pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well; pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 300° for about one hour.

title: pineapple cream cheese
directions: Blend cream cheese, sugar and pineapple together until smooth. Take 2 slices of white bread and strip off crust.
Smooth cream cheese mixture onto one slice of bread.
Make into sandwich.
Then cut into 4 halves.
Repeat until all mixture is gone.
Great appetizer.

title: fudge-y-mallows
directions: In double boiler heat chocolate chips, water and vanilla until melted.
In separate container sift flour and soda.
In another bowl blend with a spoon shortening, egg and brown sugar.
Mix dry ingredients to shortening.
Mix chocolate into mixture.
Take frozen marshmallows and wrap dough around each, one at a time. Bake on ungreased sheet at 400° for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: oreo cake
directions: Crush cookies; save 1 cup for the top.
Melt butter; mix with cookie crumbs.
Press in an 11 x 14-inch pan.
Mix 3 cups of milk and pudding mix.
Mix cream cheese with pudding and fold in Cool Whip.
Spread this over the pressed cookie crumbs, then sprinkle with 1 cup of cookie crumbs.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: spiced pears
directions: Peel, core and slice
pears.
Cover with water and cook until tender but firm.
Drain
water completely and pack pears in hot jars.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Arrange in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish in this manner:
Lay chops in single layer on the bottom. Sprinkle onions and garlic over this. Arrange potatoes over this. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour the 2 cans of tomato sauce over top.
Refill the cans with water and pour over. Bake in oven at 400° for 1 hour until fork goes through potatoes and meat easily.

title: white bean soup
directions: Clean beans.
Soak overnight.
Drain off soaking water. Put in large pot all ingredients. Cover with water. Bring to a boil. Turn down
and
simmer
several
hours
until beans are tender. Remove bay	leaf.
To thicken, remove about 1 cup soup and mash by hand
or put in processor. Return to soup and stir in.

title: perfect gravy
directions: Pour drippings from pan into large measuring cup.
Remove 1/2 cup fat from drippings to saucepan and discard remaining fat.
Add enough liquid to drippings to make 4 cups.
Mix flour and small amount of drippings or broth to make thin paste.
Over low heat, stirring constantly, add the thin flower paste to liquid and simmer until thickened.

title: no-bake strawberry shortcake
directions: You will need a trifle bowl.

title: vegetable soup for 50
directions: Soak pinto or white beans overnight.
Drain, then cook in 6 quarts water until tender.
Heat olive oil in large soup pot over medium heat.
In the order given, add the following, stirring after each addition:
onions, celery, carrots, garlic and cabbage.
Add the cooked beans or potatoes, 4 gallons hot water, the canned tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Cook at a simmer until vegetables are tender, about 1 hour.
Add water, if too thick.
As with most vegetable soups, one can vary ingredients according to taste and availability.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Add 3 slices of bread, moistened with milk, to meat.
Form into small meatballs.
Mix together rest of ingredients to form sauce.
Add meatballs to sauce.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: bean hash
directions: Brown ground beef in microwave at 100% for 5 minutes.
Drain off excess grease.
Add remaining ingredients and microwave at 100% for another 3 to 5 minutes.
May brown beef in skillet and add ingredients.

title: boiled beef with horseradish sauce
directions: In large kettle or Dutch oven, combine first 8 ingredients. Simmer covered for 30 minutes.
Add meat and continue to simmer covered for 3 1/2 to 4 hours.
Replenish water if necessary.

title: linguini salad
directions: Cook linguini as package directs, drain and put into a large bowl.
Pour in Italian dressing.
Stir together well, then add Salad Supreme spice, pepperoni and green pepper.
Mix well.
Chill in refrigerator an hour or longer.
Serve chilled.

title: crackling corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt drippings in shallow baking pan. While drippings melt, beat egg, then add dry ingredients.
Mix well with milks and add cracklings.
Add excess drippings to other ingredients and stir well.
Pour into pan and bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pork chops and sauerkraut
directions: In a skillet, brown chops; remove.
Saute onion and apple until golden brown.
Stir in sauerkraut, beer, caraway seed and bay leaf.
Return chops to skillet, cover and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: guacamole
directions: Combine mashed avocados with remaining ingredients.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: rocky mountain pie
directions: Bake in greased pan 30 to 35 minutes at 300°.

title: pot pie
directions: Bake at 400° for 15 minutes and then at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook pasta; drain.
Stir butter into hot pasta.
Stir in Parmesan and eggs.
Form spaghetti mixture into a "crust" in a buttered 10-inch pie plate.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Melt margarine and shortening.
Cream with sugars.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Add rest of ingredients.
Drop by tablespoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: sicilian zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini about 1/8-inch thick.
Place 1 cup water in a small bowl and gradually add the flour, sifting the flour through a sieve.
Continually blend the mixture with a small hand beater. Continue to add flour until the batter has the consistency of sour cream.
Heat vegetable oil in skillet (3/4-inch deep) over high heat.
When hot, place zucchini slices in a pan to cover the bottom.
Allow slices to float.
When golden, turn them over and brown the other side.
When both sides are golden, remove from skillet with a slotted spoon; place on a plate with paper towels. Sprinkle with salt and serve as soon as possible.

title: peggie's pot roast
directions: In a finger bowl, mix all spices and rub into the meat.
Coat the meat with flour.
In a large pot (Dutch oven), heat shortening or bacon fat.
(Browning tip:
Heat pot first, then add shortening.
To see if shortening is hot enough, sprinkle with cold water.
If it sizzles, temperature is right for quick browning.)

Brown meat in pan on all sides. Add water with beef bouillon cubes, halved onion, Worcestershire sauce and wine. Cover and simmer for 2 1/2 hours on low heat. About 1 hour before it is finished, peel and quarter potatoes and add to pot.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: meat balls
directions: Form first 4 ingredients into balls and place in casserole dish.
Add tomato soup, onion and chili powder.
Bake until done.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: In a large saucepan or iron skillet, mix your flour, cocoa and sugar together.
When mixed up, pour some milk (not a lot, just enough to make the mixture into a liquid) into your saucepan or skillet.
Taste your mixture and add sugar or cocoa, if needed for your taste preference.
Turn your stove to medium temperature. Pour the 4 cups of milk into the mixture.
Stir the gravy.
The gravy will get thicker the longer it stays on the stove, so if you don't like your gravy too thick, make sure to check ever so often. When done, pour over hot buttered biscuits and enjoy.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain and set aside.
Drain all the canned vegetables and mix with ground beef in a casserole dish along with cheese.
Mix corn bread according to directions on back of package; then spread over casserole and bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken marinade
directions: Mix together.
Marinate chicken for at least 3 hours.
Cook on grill.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put the can of fruit into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix the Bisquick and sugar together.
Add the milk and vanilla. Pour over the fruit.
Add the margarine.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: coconut balls
directions: Combine crushed vanilla wafer crumbs, margarine and pecans. Shape into balls and roll balls in powdered sugar.
Dip into orange juice and roll in coconut.
Chill.

title: 3 layer cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle in crumbs.
Next, sprinkle coconut on top of crumbs (don't mix).
Pour milk evenly on top of coconut.
Bake 22 minutes and remove from oven.
Melt chips and peanut butter for 2 minutes in microwave.
Stir until smooth.
Spread on top of baked layers while both are still hot.
Cool before cutting.

title: garbure(bean, cabbage and meat soup, french riviera)
directions: Cook beans in
6 cups water in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil
and let boil for 2 minutes.
Remove pan from heat.
Let stand for 1 hour.
In large, fat casserole or soup kettle, saute onions, carrots, leeks and garlic in oil only until wilted.
Place pork butt on top of vegetables.
Add beans with their cooking liquid.
Stir in 6 additional cups of water with parsley, salt, thyme, pepper, bay leaves and cloves.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Stir in potatoes, turnips and cabbage; bring to a boil. Cover and simmer 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.
Remove pork; cut into small pieces and return meat to soup and reheat. Discard bone.
Makes 6 1/2 quarts.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all together and bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° until lightly browned (35 to 45 minutes).

title: mocha cooler
directions: Microwave sugar, cocoa and water on High until mixture boils. Stir in coffee and milk.
Serve over crushed ice.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Remove seeds from chili peppers.
Place a layer in a casserole.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of both cheeses.
Add another layer of chili peppers, with rest of cheese.
Beat eggs, flour, salt and milk until smooth; pour over peppers and cheeses and bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: lilikoi chiffon pie
directions: Stir
together	in pot the egg	yolks,	sugar,	lilikoi juice and
cornstarch.
Cook over low
flame
until
custard consistency.
Add gelatin that has been dissolved
in
1/4 cup water; mix until dissolved.
Remove from heat
and cool.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff
peaks
form.
Add 1/4 cup
sugar slowly while continuing to
beat
egg
whites. Fold lilikoi mixture, cooled to room
temperature,
into
egg whites. Pour into cooled pie crust.
Refrigerate until solid, 4 hours. Top with whipped cream and serve.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans and diced mushrooms.
Mix soup, beans and mushrooms and put in casserole.*
Bake at 375°.
When this starts to bubble, put onions on top and place in oven until onions are hot.
Serve immediately.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients together and spread into pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
A very tasty appetizer.

title: sweet-sour smokies
directions: Combine all ingredients. Cover and simmer in slow cooker for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix well first 3 ingredients.
Add cereal and mix well.
Roll into small balls (1-inch).
Place in refrigerator until chilled. Melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip balls in mixture.
Place on wax paper lined cookie sheet.
Refrigerate until chocolate sets.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions.
When done, remove from oven.
While hot, poke holes in cake using wooden spoon handle.
Mix together the cream of coconut and Eagle Brand milk; pour over cake while cake is still hot.
Allow to cool before frosting.

title: pound cake
directions: As you pick up each item, put it in a large mixing bowl while mixer is running.
Beat until batter is smooth.
Put in a greased tube pan and place in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Guaranteed delicious!

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all together in large bowl. Can be topped off with picante or salsa. Delicious.

title: chicken cornelia for three
directions: The breasts should be cut in two and the legs disjointed. (All breasts can be used.
It
is
a
matter
of
taste.) Season the pieces of
chicken
with
salt, pepper and paprika. Butter a shallow baking pan or
dish
that
is large enough to accommodate the
pieces of chicken without one being on top of the other.

title: butter crunch candy bars
directions: Line a cookie sheet with foil.
Take 1 inner package from a box of graham crackers; break along the perforations.
Place in cookie sheet, all sides touching.
In a saucepan, melt butter, margarine and sugar.
Bring to a boil and stir; boil for 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers; sprinkle with 1 cup finely chopped walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: m&m's cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugars.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add to the mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in 1/2 cup M&M's.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Place the rest of the M&M's on top.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: christmas ribbon sandwiches
directions: Grind pickles and pimientos.
Drain thoroughly between paper napkins.
Cream the softened cheese.
Blend cheese with sour cream or mayonnaise.
Add drained pickles and pimientos.
Remove crusts from bread.
Spread filling between 3 slices of bread.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Refrigerate for several hours before cutting into slices.
Trim ends.
Yields 100 thin ribbon sandwiches.

title: country pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; mix well with fork.
Pat gently into bottom and sides of one or two greased 9-inch pie plates.

title: m&m brownies
directions: Follow directions for brownie mix. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish or in a well-greased pizza pan. Do not overbake. Immediately pour marshmallows evenly on top of brownie. Sprinkle candy pieces and peanuts on top. Drizzle with caramel ice cream topping. Cut into squares.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar, then add rest of ingredients, except egg whites.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold into mixture.
Pour into uncooked pie shell and bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and cook for 30 minutes or until done (pie is done when a knife inserted in center comes out clean).

title: hidden valley ranch nachos
directions: Arrange chips in shallow baking dish.
Pour salad dressing over chips.
Sprinkle cheese and green onions evenly over chips and dressing.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes or until cheese is melted slightly.
You can also heat in microwave instead of oven. Put on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese is slightly melted. Additional topping suggestions:
sliced ripe olives, jalapeno peppers and diced bell peppers.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Melt cheese and mayonnaise; mix in hash browns with onion. Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: hunter's cooler turkey
directions: Wash bird and pat off moisture.
Combine garlic powder and pepper.
Cover the turkey inside and out with garlic and pepper mixture.
Wrap the bird in heavy duty foil lengthwise, then sideways, rotating directions with 10 to 12 layers.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Wash and cap berries.
Set aside to drain.
Mix together sugar, jello, starch first, then add water, stirring until mixed well. Then cook on top of stove until thick and glossy.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first seven ingredients.
Dip chicken in butter and then into crumb mixture.
Place in a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until chicken is tender and juices run clear. Yield: 6 servings.

title: sunday morning cinnamon rolls
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients together in a bowl, and set aside. Combine 2/3 c. milk, eggs, and 1/2 c. melted and cooled margarine in a separate bowl, stir into dry mixture.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured board, and roll into a 1/2 inch thick rectangle, about 12 X 16 inches.
Using a pastry brush, spread remaining 1/4 c. melted margarine over dough.
Sprinkle with 1/2 c. sugar and cinnamon.
Roll as for a jelly roll, and seal edge.
Cut into 3/4 inch slices.
Place slices flat, sides touching, in a greased 9 X 13 inch pan.
Bake in a 375 degree oven for 25 to 30 minutes, or until golden.
Combine powdered sugar and vanilla in a small bowl; stir in enough milk to make a thin icing.
Drizzle over hot rolls. Yield:
18 rolls.

title: rice casserole
directions: Add enough water to beef consomme to make 2 cups liquid.
Mix all ingredients together and bake, covered, at 325° for 1 hour.

title: crock-pot enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken breasts and chop or shred. Set aside. Mix together soups, milk, green salsa and onion. Set aside. Cut corn tortillas into strips. Set aside. Layer into crock-pot 3 times: sauce, tortillas (crisscrossed), chicken, Cheddar cheese and olives. Cook in crock-pot on high for about 5 to 6 hours.

title: jelly
directions: Bring juice to boil.
Add Sure-Jell.
Boil one minute; add sugar.
Boil until juice clings to spoon.
Pour into clean jelly glasses.
Cool.
Top with melted paraffin.

title: skillet stew
directions: In a large skillet, brown turkey and onion. Cut carrots and potatoes in chunks.

Place on top of turkey. Add 2 tablespoons water. Steam over medium heat while you fix the other vegetables. Add remaining vegetables. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer until done. Add salt, pepper and oregano to taste.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix sugar, egg yolks, cream and milk.
Add vanilla and beaten egg whites.
Freeze.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except the bread crumbs and pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Top with butter bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Freezes well.
For microwave, cook on full power for 10 minutes.
Bread crumbs may be browned under the broiler.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cranberry cream salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, then fold in cream and chill.

title: oyster stew
directions: Cook undrained oysters and salt until edges of oysters curl. Stir in milk, cream and paprika; season to taste.
Top with pats of oleo.

title: california blend vegetables
directions: Mix this all in a large bowl.
It will seem like a lot for a 9 x 13-inch dish, but it will bake down.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beef parmesan
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Coat meat with flour mixture. Dip meat in egg and water.
Dip in crumbs, cheese and basil leaf mixture.
Brown in oil.
Combine tomato sauce, garlic and oregano.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Put Mozzarella on top.
Bake for 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve over noodles.

title: baked chicken livers
directions: Roll chicken livers in flour and salt and pepper.
Roll bacon around livers and hold with toothpicks.
Put in oven and bake on 350° for around 15 minutes.
Put on dish and garnish with slices of onions.

title: easy mix meat loaf
directions: Combine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from pan and let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together rice, water, salt, vinegar and 1 tablespoon butter and cook for 20 minutes.
In another pan, take broccoli and cook according to directions on package.
Drain well.
Take cooked rice and add to broccoli, 1 stick oleo and mushroom soup.
Stir well. Place in casserole and bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Now cover top with cheese.
Put back in oven and melt cheese.

title: pepper soup
directions: Put all veggies in pan; cover with water and simmer until tender.
In a large kettle, melt 1 stick butter.
Add 1 cup flour slowly and work out all the lumps.
Then slowly add 1/2 gallon water and cook until thick.
Drain veggies and add to broth.
Add browned hamburger, stewed tomatoes, pepper, Accent and beef bouillon.
Cook until tender (medium heat).

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Cut meat into 1 1/2-inch cubes.
In a large heavy skillet, heat the oil until smoking hot.
Place as many cubes of beef in the skillet as will fit comfortably without touching one another and brown well on all sides.
Transfer meat to a heavy casserole when brown and add a little more oil, if needed.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Let oatmeal and boiling water stand for 30 minutes.
Cream shortening, brown sugar and white sugar.
Add oatmeal mixture. Sift together flour, cinnamon, salt, soda and baking powder.
Mix together and bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well.
Roll ball in parsley or nuts; chill.

title: beets in orange sauce
directions: Mix cornstarch with beet juice and add orange juice, lemon juice and vinegar.
Cook in a medium saucepan until mixture thickens and turns clear.
Stir in sugar, salt and beets.
Heat mixture and add butter and grated orange peel.
Serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: french toast souffle
directions: Place bread cubes in a lightly greased 9 X 13 inch baking pan. In a large bowl, beat cream cheese with an electric mixer at medium speed until smooth.
Add eggs one at a time mixing well after each addition.
Stir in milk, half and half, maple syrup, and vanilla until mixture smooth.
Pour cream cheese mixture over the bread; cover, and refrigerate overnight.
The next morning, remove souffle from refrigerator, and let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes in the preheated oven, or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar and serve warm.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots and drain.
Combine with onion and green pepper. Set aside.
Combine soup, vinegar, salad oil, sugar and mustard. Stir until well mixed.
Pour over carrots.
Toss lightly with a fork.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: jubilee jumbles
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Stir in the milk and vanilla.
Sift together the dry ingredients and stir into the batter.
Blend in the chocolate bits and chill at least 1 hour. Dough will be soft.
Drop by rounded tablespoons 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Glaze.

title: plum sauce(to serve over steamed fish, broiled chicken)
directions: Combine all ingredients (except food coloring) in saucepan. Bring to boil; cook over moderate heat, uncovered, until sauce is thick, stirring frequently.
Add food coloring, if desired. Yield:
2 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes in 9 x 13 dish. Mix ingredients in pot to heat with half of cheese. Pour over potatoes and sprinkle with remaining cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry pecan cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix altogether.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.
Top gets real brown. Cool.

title: swiss cheese casserole
directions: Make paste out of the flour, butter, sugar and onion; remove from heat.	Add sour cream and cheese.
Mix well; add green beans and put in greased casserole.
Melt butter.
Add corn flakes; place on top of casserole.	Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: brigadeiros(confection)
directions: Mix ingredients together in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture leaves sides of pan.
Cool until mixture can be handled.
Butter hands and roll by teaspoonfuls into balls, then in chocolate confetti or sprinkles.
Serve in paper holders if available.
If overcooked, the bonbon crumbles.
If undercooked, it is sticky.
The name means "fighters."

title: applesauce delight
directions: Melt gelatin in water over low heat.
Stir in evaporated milk. Add applesauce, lemon peel, salt, vanilla, lemon juice and sweetener.	Chill until thick as unbeaten egg whites. Add cinnamon (optional).

title: nappa oriental salad
directions: Cut up cabbage and onion.
Refrigerate overnight or all day. Use a large frying pan and brown lightly the noodles, seeds and almonds.
Drain on paper towels to cool.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Cream the margarine, powdered sugar and cream cheese together. Add both boxes of pudding mix and then the cold milk.
Blend until smooth.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Crush the Oreo cookies to resemble dirt (a food processor does a great job).

In a see-through bowl, place a layer of about 1/2 the cookie mixture, then all of the pudding mixture and top it with the remainder of the dirt.	A few strategically placed gummy worms can add a special touch!

title: strawberry dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in small bowl with a mixer. Serve with strawberries for a great dessert.

title: lemon chicken-mushroom risotto
directions: Cut chicken, mushrooms, onion and snow peas to same size.
Fry onion until brown.
Add rice.
Add chicken, grated lemon rind (brown).
Add 7/8 ounces stock; bring to boil.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Add veggies and rest of stock.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: peanut clusters
directions: In a double boiler, melt imitation chocolate chips and peanut butter chips until smooth.
Remove from heat and add peanuts, coating peanuts well.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.
Cool.

title: lazy weekend beef casserole
directions: Combine beef, wine, consomme, salt, pepper and onion in casserole.
Mix flour with crumbs; stir into casserole mixture. Cover; bake in slow oven (300°) for about 3 hours, or until beef is tender.
Serves 4.

title: easy oriental casserole
directions: Fry in oil, cut into walnut size pieces.
Add the onion and celery, cook until all vegetables are clear.
Add the soups.
Mix all in casserole, top with chow mein noodles.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles through.

title: spaghetti with meat sauce(6 servings)
directions: Brown the meat and onion; drain grease off.
Add the remaining ingredients; bring to boil.
Reduce heat immediately and simmer, uncovered, for about an hour, or until sauce reaches desired consistency.
You may add a small amount of water to taste, or 1/4 cup of dry red wine during cooking.

title: triple treats candy
directions: Over hot (not boiling) water, melt chocolate morsels and vegetable shortening.
Stir until smooth. Remove from heat.
Pour half the melted chocolate into an 8-inch greased, foil lined pan, spreading evenly. Refrigerate until firm (about 15 minutes). Return remaining chocolate mixture to low heat.
Melt caramels and margarine with water over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Stir in walnut pieces until blended.
Pour into the chocolate lined pan. Spread evenly.
Refrigerate until tacky, about 15 minutes. Top with remaining chocolate, spreading evenly to cover caramel. Chill until firm.
Cut into bars.
Keep refrigerated.

title: peaches `n' cream
directions: Combine flour, melted margarine and pecans. Place in 13 x 9 x 2 dish. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Let cool.

title: vanilla cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in milk over medium heat until it bubbles.
Cook and stir 2 minutes.
Remove from heat. Stir in 1 spoon hot mixture into yolks.
Pour yolk into mixture. Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour in pie crust.
Beat 3 egg whites and 6 tablespoons sugar.
Add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until thick.
Pour on pie. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese slices, spoon soup over chicken and sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Drizzle butter over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crab bisque
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan over medium-high heat.
Add vegetables and saute until soft.
Reduce heat to medium and add flour, whisking constantly until smooth.
Cook 5 minutes, whisking frequently.
Stir in parsley and seasonings.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Add Madeira, crab and salt to taste and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Do not boil.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: holiday fruitcake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, then add eggs and flour with salt, cream of tartar, baking soda and buttermilk.
Alternate flour and buttermilk mixing well.
Add bourbon, vanilla, nuts, fruit and then coconut, mixing after each addition.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Make a white sauce with butter, flour and half and half.
Add parsley, chives, salt and pepper.
Stir until thickened.
Adjust seasonings and remove from heat.
Add sour cream.
Blend well.

title: claire's favorite sweet carrots
directions: Use 2 carrots per person.
Peel and cut carrots into 3/8-inch thick "wheels."
Place in a small boiler and add sugar and butter. Cover with water and boil until tender (approximately 10 to 15 minutes).

title: ground turkey delight
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package, drain.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with nonstick spray.
Brown meat and drain. Return to skillet and add onion, garlic and onion soup mix. Saute about 2 or 3 minutes.
Add the stewed tomatoes.
Allow to start to boil.
Pour over macaroni and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mold into rolls and wrap in waxed paper.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Cut in thin slices and bake at 425° about 8 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen cookies.

title: icebox slaw
directions: Grate or chop first 4 ingredients.
Add salt and mustard seed. Mix well.
Heat vinegar, water and sugar until it comes to a boil and sugar is dissolved.
Cool and pour over cabbage mixture.
Let stand 24 hours in refrigerator, then enjoy.
Will keep a month.

title: monster cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and drop onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for eight minutes.
Makes lots.

title: divinity
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine first 4 ingredients.
Cook and stir until sugar dissolves and mixture comes to a boil.
Cook to hard ball stage or 250°, without stirring.
Remove from heat. Immediately beat 2 egg whites until stiff.
Pour hot syrup slowly over egg whites, beating on high speed about 5 minutes.
Add 1 or more teaspoons of vanilla.
Beat until mixture loses gloss and forms soft peaks (mixer will have higher pitch when ready).
Add pecans.
Drop on wax paper.

title: stroganoff
directions: Brown beef and onion in oleo until tender.
Add soup, sour cream and seasonings.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
Serve over noodles.

title: 30 second pie
directions: Empty pineapple (juice and all) into bowl.
Pour into the pudding and pie filling mix.
Then add the sour cream.
Mix all ingredients well and pour into graham cracker crust may garnish with fruit and serve with whipped topping.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Pour everything into large mixing bowl, except broccoli.
Cook broccoli for 5 minutes.
After broccoli comes to a boil, drain and fold into other mixture.
Grease casserole dish with butter or margarine.
Pour mixture into dish.
Roll cracker crumbs with rolling pin.
Spread on top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes or until spoon comes out clean.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Bake in greased casserole for 1 hour in 350° oven or until knife test comes out clean.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and spices.
Cook noodles as package directs; drain.
Combine and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Last 15 minutes add shredded Cheddar or Mozzarella.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil together sugar, cocoa and milk for 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: red-eyeria
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake 30 minutes at 350° in 9-inch casserole.

title: mom b jam cake
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice together.
Add margarine, eggs and jam.
Mix soda and buttermilk, add to other ingredients.
Bake in 3 round 8-inch cake pans or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in 375° oven for 40 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill about 1 hour before serving.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas and add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Put in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and save broth.
Cook noodles in leftover stock. Saute onion, pepper and mushrooms with 1/2 stick butter (set aside).
In pan, melt 2 sticks butter, flour, stock and milk, stirring until thickened.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Mix all ingredients together; put in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine eggs, sugar, corn syrup, margarine and vanilla in large bowl and blend well.
Stir in pecans and pour into pie crust.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes, or until set.

title: almond pimento spread
directions: Bring to a boil the agar flakes and water, stirring constantly, until agar is dissolved.
Set aside.
Blend almonds with a little of the agar water and when the almonds are blended to a creamy texture, add the rest of the ingredients.
If using oil, add slowly while blending.
Stop occasionally and scrape sides.
Add the lemon juice to the mixture while still blending. Pour into plastic containers and refrigerate.
(Margarine containers are good.)
Makes 2 cups.
Refrigerate.
Will become firm, but spreadable.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Mix flour and cheese.
Coat potatoes with flour and cheese mixture.
Put melted margarine in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking pan and place coated potatoes in a single layer in pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes, then turn potatoes and continue baking for another 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix together sugar
and flour.	Add beaten eggs, margarine, nutmeg, cinnamon
and
vanilla.
Stir
in chopped apples and pecans.
Bake at
425° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake until done.
(Use single pie crust.)

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Add dry ingredients with buttermilk.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Fold in stiffened egg whites.
Bake in prepared pan, 9 x 13 x 2-inch or 3 round cake pans at 325° to 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: milk chocolate pie
directions: Heat chocolate and 2 tablespoons of the milk in saucepan over low heat, stirring until chocolate is melted.
Beat sugar into cream cheese.
Add remaining milk and chocolate mixture; beat until smooth.
Fold chocolate mixture into whipped topping; blend until smooth.
Spoon into crust and freeze about 4 hours.

title: rich rice pudding
directions: Cook rice in boiling water until absorbed.
Add hot milk and cook slowly until rice is tender.
Add sugar and heat until sugar dissolves.
Beat eggs and stir into hot mixture.
Add butter and stir until blended.
Pour all into rice mixture.
Replace pan on heat.
Stir until creamy.
Add vanilla.
Pour into dessert dishes. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Serve plain or with cream.

title: pink punch
directions: Add boiling water to gelatin mix.
Stir until dissolved.
Add sugar, cold water and fruit juices.
(When ready to serve, add ginger ale.)
The fruit mix should be chilled.
Makes enough for 50 people.

title: best ever brownie pudding
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa and salt.
Add milk, vanilla and shortening.
Mix until smooth.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Sprinkle over batter.
Pour hot water over all. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Combine all ingredients but wings in a 4 to 5-quart Dutch oven.
Mix well and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and add wings. Simmer, covered, 40 minutes, then uncover and simmer 15 minutes more.
Drain and arrange wings on a broiler pan.
Broil 5 minutes or until skin is lightly crisped.
Serve hot or cold.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl.
Seal with a cover and shake. Add the oil and shake well again.
Let mix blend in a bowl at least 4 hours before enjoying.

title: holiday spice tea
directions: This needs to be prepared in a 20-cup percolator. Put cloves, brown sugar, cinnamon sticks and tea bags in the basket. Pour juices over the items in the basket.

title: graham cracker pralines
directions: Cover cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Line graham crackers on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Boil butter and sugar together for 3 minutes.
Pour over graham crackers and bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool slightly and separate with spatula.

title: m&m's cookies
directions: Blend shortening, brown sugar and granulated sugar in a large bowl.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift next 3 dry ingredients together.
Add to sugar and egg mixture, blending well.
Stir in 1/2 cup M&M's candies.
Blend well.
Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Decorate with remaining M&M's.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes until brown.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: peanut butter drops
directions: Don't use mixer.
Beat the eggs with a fork.
Stir in the peanut butter and sugar.
Drop by small spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes approximately 2 1/2 dozen 2-inch cookies.
Very good cookies.

title: fried fish in a pocket
directions: Cut fish into 2-inch pieces.
In a bowl, mix flour, seasonings, beer or milk and egg.
Pour oil to a 1/4-inch depth in skillet and heat.
Dip fish in batter.
Fry until lightly browned. Drain and keep warmed.
Slice the bread in half.
Making 2 pockets per person, fill each one with equal amounts of fish and vegetables.
Top with yogurt and Feta cheese.
Sprinkle with pepper, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: honey graham crackers
directions: Sift flours into
a mixing bowl, thoroughly cut in half the butter before
cutting
in	the
rest.
Mix
in sugar, and baking powder; stir
in
honey, followed by the egg; mix well. Gradually add 1 teaspoon water, tossing and mixing well before adding more; stop adding water when the dough is moist enough, but not sticky, to	form
a
ball.	Knead
on
