a well floured surface for 1 minute or until the dough holds together enough to be rolled. Roll
to
a
thickness
midway
between 1/8 and 1/4-inch, then cut it
into
3-inch
squares,
using	a pizza cutter, a ravioli wheel
or a sharp greased knife.
Space the squares slightly apart on
ungreased
cookie
sheet
or in an upside-down baking pan; prick
tops
with
fork.
Bake
in	a preheated 350° oven for about 15 minutes.

title: cranberry appetizer spread
directions: In a saucepan over medium heat, bring water and sugar to a boil without stirring, boil for 5 minutes.
Add cranberries; cook until berries pop and sauce is thickened about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cut apricots in preserves into small pieces and add to cranberry mixture.
Stir in lemon juice.
Cool.
Add almonds. Spoon over cream cheese.
Serve with crackers.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix and cream sugar and butter.
Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add eggs, dry ingredients, apples, nuts and vanilla. Mix by hand.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: just a good cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
While still hot, spread pineapple on top.
Let cool completely.
Mix pudding mix as directed, then mix in cream cheese; whip until fluffy. Spread on cake.
Spread Cool Whip on top of this.
Refrigerate.

title: pineapple-nut salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Blend in cream cheese.
Add other ingredients and congeal.

title: banana cake
directions: Sift flour, salt, soda and baking powder together; set aside. Cream butter and sugar together; add beaten eggs and mix well. Add the vanilla and mix well again.
Next, add the dry ingredients alternately with the buttermilk; mix well.
Add the mashed bananas and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil until tender.
Put through blender
with
4 ounces Philadelphia cream cheese.	Salt and pepper to taste.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Put cucumbers, onion and peppers in a gallon glass jar.
Mix vinegar, sugar, celery seed and salt and bring to a boil.
Cool. When cool, pour over pickles in jar.
Ready to eat in two days. These will keep up to one year
in the refrigerator.
(Be sure to use a glass jar.)

title: ann's jewish coffee cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together and bake in tube or Bundt pan at 325° until toothpick inserted in center comes clean, about 50 minutes.

title: shrimp and rice
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add rice and pepper.
Saute until lightly browned, stirring constantly about 3 minutes.
Add water, mixing with fork.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in parsley.

title: tamale casserole
directions: Sprinkle chips in baking dish.
Unwrap tamales and arrange over chips.
Combine remaining ingredients except cheese and spoon over tamales.
Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes.
Add cheese on top. Bake 5 minutes more.

title: carrot coconut cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg, carrots and coconut; mix well.
Add dry ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Add orange juice. Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Yield about three dozen or so.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Combine brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts in small bowl.
Set aside.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt in large bowl.
Add butter, sour cream and vanilla.
Mix until ingredients are combined.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 15 seconds after each addition.
Spread half of batter in greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with half cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Spread remaining batter in pan and top with remaining mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: three tone mocha pie
directions: Combine and melt in double boiler over hot boiling water and set aside.

title: hello dolly bars
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Sprinkle crumbs, then layer each of the ingredients.
Pour milk over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: saltine cracker candy
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line cookie sheet with foil and completely cover with saltine crackers.
Melt real butter and light brown sugar in pan.
Boil 3 minutes, stirring constantly. Pour boiled mixture over crackers and put in oven and bake 5 minutes.
Remove immediately and sprinkle with milk chocolate chips.
Refrigerate until cool.
Lift foil and candy will break into different pieces.
Do not substitute anything.
A sweet, salty taste!

title: pork chops mexicana
directions: Brown chops.
Arrange in 9 x 13-inch pan and season with salt. Sprinkle rice around meat.
Combine taco seasoning, tomato sauce and water.
Pour over chops.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Arrange pepper rings on top.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: blonde chocolate chip brownies
directions: Cream butter; gradually add brown sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.

title: whole wheat pizza crust
directions: Mix all dry ingredients except all-purpose flour.
Mix well and add warm water (120° to 130°).
Add oil.
Knead dough until mixed and add all-purpose flour as needed to stiffen it.
Let rest 15 minutes.
Divide into 2 balls and roll them out to pizza pan size.
Put on greased pizza pans and bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Remove from oven.
Add pizza sauce and remaining topping or bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: maui ribs
directions: Combine all ingredients except ribs over low heat. Add ribs and marinate for 24 to 48 hours. Barbecue.

title: broiled fish
directions: Mix ingredients.
Arrange fish in baking pan.
Brush fish all over using all mix.
Broil until done, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions, rinse and drain.
Combine noodles with butter, grated Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Spoon into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Brown ground meat with onions; drain.
Spoon atop spaghetti.
Pour spaghetti sauce over all and sprinkle liberally with Mozzarella cheese. Arrange slices of pepperoni over the surface.
Cover with foil and bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Remove foil and continue baking 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before cutting into serving pieces.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: special spaghetti sauce
directions: Pour spaghetti sauce in saucepan.
Rinse jar out with small amount (maybe 1/2 cup) of water.
Put in saucepan.
Shake in all of your spices.
Add the brown sugar.
Mix all ingredients together. Simmer on very very low heat for at least 20 minutes to whatever.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and eggs; add cooking oil and food coloring.
Mix well; add buttermilk and flour.
Add vanilla, vinegar, baking powder and soda.
Mix well.
Pour into 4 (9-inch) pans and bake for 20 to 25 minutes, until done at 325°.

title: cinnamon swirl cake
directions: Combine nuts, 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Mix flour with baking powder and salt.
Combine sour cream and soda. Cream butter and 2 cups sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.

title: apple crunch
directions: Mix all ingredients except apples; use fork.
When crumbly put on top of 5 cups of sliced apples in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Melt 1/4 cup butter and drizzle over mixture in pan and then sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: salmon souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. In saucepan, soak bread in milk; add salt, mustard and cheese.
Heat until cheese melts; cool.
Add egg yolks and salmon. Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into salmon mixture.
Pour into 2-quart buttered casserole.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Let cool, then pick meat from bone. Mix meat with chicken soup and sour cream.

title: rigatoni
directions: Simmer all but rigatoni together about 3 hours.
Then cook rigatoni noodles and drain.
Add the noodles after you have cooked the sauce.
Heat.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix
together all ingredients with boiling water.
Pour into pie shell and cook at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix first three ingredients well.
Add a few drops of food coloring.
Pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: creamy caramel pecan rolls
directions: Mix sugar and whipping cream.
Divide between 2 baking pans. Sprinkle pecans over sugar mixture.
Roll each bread dough into a 12 x 8-inch rectangle on a floured surface.
Brush with melted butter.
Mix together brown sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over dough.
Roll dough jelly roll style and pinch to seal.
Cut into slices.
Place rolls into pan with mixture.
Let rise in warm place until doubled in size.
(Can refrigerate overnight, covered; leave at room temperature for 20 minutes.)
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line cookie sheet with foil.
Bone chicken and remove skin; cut each breast into 12 to 16 pieces about 1 1/2-inches square.
Combine cracker crumbs, cheese and salt on waxed paper.
Dip chicken into the melted butter, then into the crumb mixture.
Place in single layer on foil-lined cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 20 minutes until golden brown.
(Do not overbake or meat will be dry.)
Dip in honey or your favorite sauce.

title: down south beans
directions: Sort
and
wash
beans
and place in Dutch oven.
Cover with 4
inches
water.
Add
salt,
chili powder, red pepper, pepper, garlic and ham hock and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and
simmer 8 hours, adding water as needed.
Remove meat from bone,
return meat to beans.
Top with green onions.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven
to
Melt butter; place in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle
brown
sugar
evenly over butter.
Place pineapple slices in pan.
Place cherries in pineapple slices. Fix cake by directions; put on top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: punch
directions: On your oven's highest setting, bring a cup of water with a dash of lemon juice to a boil.
Change the temperature setting to low and boil for 3 minutes, then thoroughly dry the inside of the microwave and its door.
Your oven will be shining clean, and the kitchen will smell fresh.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix well.
Place in casserole and cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter with cream; once it its smooth, add parsley and pepper.
Fill a large pot with water and bring to a rapid boil.
Add salt if desired.
Add pasta and stir until water returns to a boil.
Cook, stirring occasionally,until desired tenderness, about 10 min.
Drain fettucine and return to pot.
Add Parmesan cheese and toss 1 min.
Add butter/cream mixture; continue to toss 1 min. longer or just until thickened.
Top with Parmesan cheese and parsley, if desired.

title: fruit tray with marshmallow dip
directions: Make cornbread as usual, but substitute quick eggs and skim milk.
(Do not use any shortening in bread.)

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper (cut up very small) in cooking oil.
Put in ground chuck and season to taste.
Cook until slightly brown.
Drain majority of grease.
Add squash and let cook slow, turning squash over in skillet, until squash is almost done.
Add 1/4 cup sugar or to taste.
Add cheeses and stir in. Do not overcook.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Bring to boil the sugar and Karo syrup.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter, margarine and corn flakes.
Mix well, drop on wax paper.

title: broccoli cheese rice casserole
directions: Prepare the rice as directed, using liquid Butter Buds.
Add the cooked broccoli, water chestnuts and chicken broth.
Add seasoning and cheese.
Spoon into a large casserole dish that has been sprayed with nonfat cooking spray.
Top with the croutons; cover and bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover the last 10 minutes.

title: buttermilk biscuits(from original light crust flour sack)
directions: Put flour, salt, soda and baking powder together in mixing bowl.
Push flour to sides of bowl, making a well in the center. Pour milk into this and place shortening in milk and blend together, making an emulsion.
Blend well and turn out on rolling board; cut into biscuits.
Have a greased, hot, cast-iron skillet ready to put biscuits in and bake in hot oven (425°) for 5 to 8 minutes.
Use cookie sheet (well-greased) if no iron skillet available (floured).

title: tots angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water and set aside.
Mix dry ingredients in order given.
Cut in shortening.
Stir in buttermilk.
Blend thoroughly.
Knead lightly.
Roll out; cut biscuits and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake.

title: magic fruit cake
directions: Break mincemeat into small pieces and put in 2-quart saucepan. Add water and place over heat and stir until lumps are broken. Boil 1 minute more, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add nuts, fruits, milk and egg.
Blend well.
Stir in flour and baking soda blended.
Pour mixture into loaf pan well-greased. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mexican salad toss
directions: Combine process cheese spread and sour cream.
Add onion and chili powder; mix well.
Chill.
Combine greens, chips, corn, tomato, avocado and bacon; toss lightly.
Serve with dressing. Makes 8 servings.
tags: whole kernel corn with sweet peppers

title: portuguese potatoes
directions: After boiling potatoes, cut into cubes.
Do not peel.
Place cubed potatoes in a large greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle cubed cheese over potatoes.
Follow with onion, pimentos, parsley flakes, paprika and garlic salt.
Place croutons on top of casserole.
Melt margarine and pour over top.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven. Makes 10 to 12 large servings.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Soften butter. Cream butter and sugar until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well.
Add the flour (baking powder and salt) and milk alternately.
Bake in 3 greased pans at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake pastry shell 8 minutes; remove from oven.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.

title: spinach supreme
directions: Mix spinach with cream cheese.
Put into casserole.
Top with bread mixed with butter and sage.
Heat, uncovered, in a medium oven until brown.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, beat eggs slightly; beat in both cheeses, flour, salt and pepper.
Drain broccoli well, patting dry with paper towels.
Stir into egg mixture.
Pour into greased
9 x 9-inch baking dish, spreading evenly with spoon. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes until mixture is firm and pulls away from sides of pan.
Loosen edges with spatula, slice and serve.

title: tomato breakfast salad
directions: Scoop out tomatoes with spoon.
Simmer tomato pulp with chopped parsley until thick paste.
Scramble eggs and cheese together in skillet.
Mix with tomato mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Restuff tomatoes and serve for breakfast.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix sausage, cheese and Bisquick. Roll mixture into 1/4 inch balls. Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and sprinkle with salt over the tops of vegetables and set in the refrigerator for 12 hours. Squeeze vegetables with hands to drain.
Then add to the following mixtures.

title: curried beef and rice
directions: Brown beef in skillet and drain well. Add remaining ingredients EXCEPT beans. Bring to a boil over medium heat. Cover. Reduce heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes until rice is done. Stir in drained green beans and serve.
Serves 6.
Delicious one pan meal!

title: christmas casserole cookies
directions: Beat eggs well and gradually add sugar. Beat until fluffy. Stir in remaining ingredients. Place in a 2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. While hot, stir well with a wooden spoon. Cool and form into small balls; roll in granulated sugar.

title: round steak in mushroom sauce
directions: Salt and pepper steak.
Coat with flour on both sides.
Brown steak on both sides.
Place in casserole dish.
Mix soup with milk and pour over steak.
Sprinkle sliced mushrooms over steak.
Cover casserole dish.
Bake at 300° for two hours.

title: lo-cal parmesan chicken
directions: In small bowl, combine buttermilk and Parmesan cheese; set aside.
Sprinkle chicken breasts with flour, salt, pepper, garlic powder and onion powder.
Dip floured breasts into buttermilk cheese mixture, coating both sides and using entire mix.
Repeat with bread crumbs.
In 9-inch skillet, heat oil; add chicken breasts and cook, turning once, until brown on both sides.
Makes 2 servings.

title: bill's carrot cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, oil, buttermilk or yogurt and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat well.
Gradually mix in flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, ginger and cloves.
Stir in carrots and nuts or granola.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes, until cake tests done.
Serve plain or frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: sour cream cucumbers
directions: Peel cucumbers and score with fork tines.
Slice evenly in a large bowl and sprinkle generously with salt.
Let stand until cucumbers appear soft.
After a few hours, drain salt off.
Taste, if too salty, rinse in clear water.
Squeeze all liquid from cucumbers.
Add onions.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over cucumbers.
Coat.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: taco grande
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease bottom and sides of 8-10 inch round pan.
Set aside.
In skillet, cook and stir ground meat over medium heat 8-10 minutes or until it is no longer pink, breaking it into small pieces.
Add taco mix and amount of water as directed on pkg.
Continue cooking according to pkg. directions.
Remove skillet from heat.
Stir in one cup of salsa. Arrange 4 tortillas in bottom and up the side of the prepared round pan.
(Tortillas will overlap on the bottom but not all of the area on the sides of the pan will be covered.)
Spoon meat mixture evenly over tortillas.
Sprinkle with one cup of the cheese.
Slice and sprinkle half of the green onion over cheese. Top with remaining 4 tortillas, overlapping them to create a scalloped edge effect.
Press tortillas down over filling. Spread salsa over tortillas.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and onion. Bake 30 minutes.
Remove and let stand 5 minutes.
Cut into wedges.
Chop lettuce into thin strands.
Serve taco wedges over lettuce and top with sour cream.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: tuna appetizers
directions: Cut bread into 24 (1 1/2-inch) rounds and toast on one side only.
Set aside.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Roll into balls.
Cook until done and brown.
Serve with spaghetti and sauce.

title: holiday ham balls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet (15 1/2 x
x 1-inch).
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into 1-inch
balls.
Place about 2 inches apart in pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Immediately remove from pan. Serve warm. Makes about 7 dozen appetizers.

title: basic chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, eggs, pickles and salt.
Do not add mayonnaise until ready to serve.
Then mix with enough mayonnaise to lightly blend everything.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix Jell-O, apricot nectar and Wesson oil.
Add cake mix in two portions, beating after each addition.
Add eggs, one at a time, blending after each.
Then add vanilla and salt.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan.
Bake about one hour at 350°.
Cake is done when toothpick is inserted and comes out clean.
While cake is hot, make a mixture of powdered sugar and lemon juice and pour over cake.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream the sugar and margarine together.
Add eggs and mix; (baking powder and salt if using plain flour).
Add flour gradually.
Mix together well.
Add flavoring.
Drop by teaspoons on greased sheet.
Bake at 375°.

title: golden shrimp puff
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Cut crusts from bread and cut slices into cubes.
Beat eggs, milk and seasoning.
Stir in bread cubes, cheese and shrimp.
Pour into oblong baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour or until center is set.
Serve immediately.
Serves 8.

title: one step cream sauce
directions: Measure cold milk into saucepan.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add butter.
Heat to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Makes 1 cup medium cream sauce.

title: italian hunter's stew
directions: Toss meat with flour; brown on all sides in oil in a 5-quart Dutch oven.
Add onions; saute until tender.
Stir in broth, seasoned salt, garlic powder, chili powder, oregano and rosemary. Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste and carrots.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour or until meat and carrots are tender.
Stir in macaroni; heat through.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: english muffin bread
directions: Scald milk; stir in sugar, salt and margarine.
Cool to lukewarm.
Measure warm water into large warm bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast; stir until dissolved.
Stir in lukewarm milk mixture.
Add 3 cups flour; beat until smooth.
Add enough flour to make soft dough.
Turn onto floured board; knead for about 2 minutes or until dough is manageable and can be formed into a ball.
Place in greased bowl; grease top.
Cover; let rise, until doubled, about 1 hour.
Punch down; divide in half.
Shape into loaves.
Roll each loaf in corn meal.
Place in 2 greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch pans.
Cover; let rise until doubled, about 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until done.
Remove from pans and cool on wire racks.

title: mae's coconut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour three 9-inch round cake pans.
Cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together the flour and baking powder and add alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in flavorings. Divide evenly between pans.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Turn out on racks to cool before icing.

title: cucumber dill dip
directions: Beat softened cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover and chill.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; fold in Cool Whip and then gently fold in lemon juice.
Makes two 9-inch pies.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix ingredients together well; roll into balls, or drop from a spoon into the hot shortening.
Brown them; drain on a paper towel.
These are especially good if fried in the deep lard left over from a frying fish!

title: strawberry pretzel squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix crushed pretzels, 1/3 cup sugar and butter or margarine; press firmly in 13 x9-inch baking pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: seafood cakes
directions: Mix tuna, dressing, mustard, vegetables, pimiento, seasonings and 1/2 cup bread crumbs.
Shape into 15 (2-inch) balls.
Roll in remaining bread crumbs, coating well.
Flatten balls into small patties.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Heat 1/2 cup oil in skillet over medium-high heat.
Add tuna patties.
Cook 5 minutes on each side, until golden.
Add oil to pan as needed.
Serves 8.

title: bean soup
directions: Cook celery, onion and carrots in the oil until vegetables are soft.
Add tomatoes, beans, liquid, bay leaves, salt and optional garlic.
Bring the mixture to a boil and let boil rapidly for 2 minutes.
Let mixture stand for at least 1 hour (all day if necessary).

title: honey lemon dressing
directions: Combine dry ingredients and mix.
Place all ingredients, except oil, in a blender.
With machine running, slowly add oil in a thin stream. Store in the refrigerator until needed.
Lasts up to two weeks if covered tightly.
Makes 15 servings.

title: twenty minute chocolate cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients together and set aside.
Bring next four ingredients to boil.
Add to flour mixture; then dissolve baking soda in buttermilk and add to mixture.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: pork tenderloin roast
directions: Role tenderloin in flour seasoned with salt & pepper.
Brown in 4 tbsp. butter.
Place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle 3 tbsp. of flour in drippings where meat was browned.
Brown flour as you would normally make gravy.
Add chicken broth and mushrooms to the gravy mixture.
Pour over roast.
Bake 1 hour on 350 degrees. Serve with rice.

title: banana muffins
directions: Combine biscuit mix, baking powder and sugar in a bowl.
Make a well in the center of mixture.
Combine egg, oil and banana and add to dry mixture.
Mix well.

title: tahitian coffee
directions: Heat milk until film forms on top.
Add flaked coconut and sugar.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Strain milk and reheat slowly.
Combine warmed milk with fresh brewed coffee.
Pour in brandy snifters or large mugs and garnish with toasted coconut. Serves 4 to 6.

title: fruit pizza
directions: For cookie crust:
Press cookie dough evenly onto a lightly greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Prick with a fork, bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop into a small amount of Crisco oil or butter.
Brown on both sides.
Drain.

title: barbecue green beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in covered casserole at 275° for 4 hours or cook in crock-pot on low for 4 to 5 hours.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Bring to boil the next 4 ingredients; pour
over
flour
and
sugar
mixture.
Add
remaining ingredients;
mix well.
Bake
at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes in a very shallow sheet cake pan.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll in balls (size of a walnut).
Roll in extra bread crumbs.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain well, reserving 2 tablespoons bacon fat.
Add water, vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and mustard to bacon fat and heat, stirring, until sugar is dissolved and mixture boils.
Add potatoes and onion and toss gently until most of dressing is absorbed.
Fold in sour cream, parsley and crumbled bacon.
Serve warm.

title: cheese strata
directions: Arrange 6 slices of bread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place cheese, broccoli and ham in layers and top with remaining bread slices.
Combine milk, eggs, onion, salt and mustard; blend well. Pour over layers.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Allow to return to room temperature before baking.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix all together.
Put in a loaf pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350° to 375° or until done.
Coat top with butter.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: applesauce fruit cake
directions: Warm the applesauce, and cream the sugar and shortening, combine.
Sift the dry ingredients.
Combine the wet and dry ingredients, alternating and then add the nuts and raisins.
Add 1/2 cup chopped candied fruit.
Use a 9x5x3-inch greased bundt or angel cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, or more if needed.

title: soft ginger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in molasses; add eggs, then soda and vinegar.
Stir dry ingredients and add to mixture alternately with milk.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: broiled ham sandwiches
directions: Mix together with enough mayonnaise to make a spread.
Spread on rye bread or sourdough bread and broil until bubbly.
You can adjust the curry to your taste.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: sour cream mini biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine all ingredients in large electric mixer bowl. Beat until well blended. Spoon into ungreased miniature muffin pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: scallops maison
directions: Combine scallops and mushrooms in a shallow casserole. Combine wine, soup, half and half and curry powder.
Pour over scallops and bake at
350° for 40 minutes.
Serve over rice. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chow chow
directions: Cook each vegetable separately until tender, but not mushy. Drain; rinse with cold water to stop its cooking and preserve color.
Drain; layer into a large dishpan.
Combine sugar, vinegar, water and spices into stock pot.
Bring to a boil.
After sugar dissolves, spoon in vegetables and boil for 5 minutes.
Stir gently so you don't break up the vegetables, but mix them well. Spoon into hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: confetti pasta(4 to 6 servings)
directions: Prepare linguini according to directions on package.
Mix mayonnaise and mustard together, folding into warm linguini.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: bessie edwards pound cake
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature.
Cream sugar, shortening and butter.
Add 1 egg at a time.
Add vanilla flavoring then milk and flour.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Dust tomato slices with flour seasoned with salt, pepper and sugar.
Brown lightly in butter and transfer to a baking dish. Stir cream, sugar and soda into pan drippings, blending well. Pour over tomatoes and bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large airtight container.
Cover and store in a dry place.
Use 3 heaping teaspoonfuls mix per cup of hot water.

title: make ahead salad
directions: Layer as written.
Cover tightly and put in refrigerator overnight using a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.

title: fruit salad
directions: In large bowl stir in instant pudding with pineapple juice until smooth.
Add drained peaches and pears; mix.
Refrigerate for a couple of hours, then about 2 hours before ready to serve, add to mixture the kiwi, bananas and fresh seedless grapes.
Slice the 1/2 orange real thin with some of the peel (take part of it off).
Add marshmallows and mix all together.
Place back in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: chocolate chip cookie delight
directions: Spread Cool Whip on bottom of dish.
Dip cookies in milk and place a layer on top of this. Then make another layer of Cool Whip and then layer cookies.
Top with Cool Whip.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.

title: pralines
directions: Combine sugars, salt and milk.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly until sugar is dissolved.
Cook to soft ball stage (238°), stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine and let stand until lukewarm.
Add vanilla and beat until creamy. Add pecans and drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.

title: cinnamon ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients. Mix thoroughly. Put in ice cream freezer. Freeze as directions list. Makes 4 quarts.

title: sweetheart salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese, crushed pineapple, drained.
Add maraschino cherries, drained and chopped, pecans, chopped.
Mix well.
Place in freezer until shortly before serving.
(Serves 6 to 8.)

title: paul newman cake
directions: Mix the box cake mix as directed and bake as directed in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Punch holes in top of cake and pour the Eagle Brand milk over top while still warm.
Pour caramel ice cream topping over cake when completely cooled.
Refrigerate (the longer, the better).
Top with Cool Whip before serving.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch Pyrex baking dish with the coconut and pecans.
Prepare cake mix by directions on box; pour over coconut and pecans.
Warm the cream cheese and margarine and blend together.
Spoon over top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: a perfect cheesecake
directions: Crust: Combine graham cracker crumbs and 2 tablespoons sugar. Add melted butter. Mix well. Pat into spring form pan.

title: crab fettucine
directions: Cook noodles.
In a saucepan melt butter; add flour.
Stir until slightly thickened and white.
Add milk until thick.
Add cream cheese, 1/2 of garlic and crab to sauce.
Simmer 25 minutes. While sauce simmers, place remaining margarine in a pan.
Melt and add remaining garlic; cook until brown.
In a shallow baking dish, pour butter.
Pour butter-garlic mixture over sliced French bread.
Bake until brown.
Layer fettucine sauce over noodles. Serve with French bread.

title: red rice
directions: Cook onion in margarine in a pot over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Stir often.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat 10 minutes; stir often.
Pour rice into a casserole.
Cover and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Stir every 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pork curry over cauliflower couscous(makes 6 servings; carb count: 2 grams)
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons oil over medium heat in large saucepan. Add curry powder and garlic; cook and stir 1 to 2
minutes until garlic is golden. Add pork; stir to coat completely with curry and garlic.
Cook and stir 5 to 7 minutes or until pork cubes are barely pink in center. Add bell pepper and vinegar; cook and stir 3 minutes or until bell pepper is soft. Sprinkle with salt.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla until creamy.
Add sour cream.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Set pan on cookie sheet and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Chill before serving.

title: tomato and green beans
directions: Peel and seed tomatoes.
Dice.
Cook tomatoes, oregano and basil in water until tender, about 20 minutes.
Keep cooking until most of the water is gone.
Cook beans as directed.
Strain water from beans and add tomatoes.
Toss.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Make a syrup of the sugar and water.

title: pepper steak
directions: Pound steak before cutting in strips.
Sprinkle with paprika. Let set while preparing vegetables.
Put oleo in a large skillet and melt.
Add meat and brown; then, add garlic and broth.
Cook 30 minutes and add vegetables.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Blend the cornstarch, water and soy sauce.
Add to meat mixture.
Cook about 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes.
Stir gently.
Serve over platter of 3 cups cooked rice.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Combine oats, cocoa, nuts and coconut.
Place sugar, milk and butter in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Stir in dry ingredients. Spoon onto waxed paper.
Let stand 20 minutes.

title: cherries in snow
directions: Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and vanilla until fluffy with an electric mixer.
Add the Cool Whip, then the milk and mix well.
Take your sponge cake and cut in half, cutting from side to side.
Put bottom half of sponge cake on a platter and add half the mixture onto the top of angel cake.
Then put the top half of the angel cake on top of the mixture.
With the other 1/2 of the mixture cover the top part of the angel food cake.
Then pour the can of cherries over top the whole cake.
If you don't like cherries, use some other fruit topping you desire.

title: taco dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread bean dip over bottom of baking dish (5 x 7).
In mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, sour cream, taco seasoning mix and garlic; mix well.
Spread cream cheese mixture evenly over bean dip.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Sprinkle tomatoes, onions, olives, cilantro over dip.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown pork well in a little hot oil.
Season well with salt and pepper.
Add broth; simmer covered on low 20 minutes.
Add peppers, onion and pineapple.
Cook another 10 minutes.
Blend cornstarch with sugar, vinegar, soy sauce and syrup.
Add to mixture.
Stir constantly until thickened, then 5 minutes more. Serve over hot rice.

title: spinach pie
directions: Prick pie shell with fork.
Bake pie shell in conventional oven until golden brown.
In 1-quart microwave-safe dish, cook spinach, covered with plastic wrap.
Cook on High for 6 minutes, stirring 1 time.
Drain thoroughly.
Layer half spinach mixture and cheese in bottom of pie shell.
Repeat layers.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt, nutmeg and cayenne pepper.
Pour over spinach mixture. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
and turn into an unbaked pie shell. Bake
in preheated oven at 450° for 10 minutes.
Lower temperature to 350° and bake for 30 to 40 minutes longer.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Boil chicken in large pot for 30 minutes.
Take out of pot. Remove bones and return to pot.
Add rice, salt and pepper.
Cook until rice is done.

title: italian macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until done; rinse with cold water.
Cut broccoli into flowerets, green pepper into strips and carrot into thin cuts.
Mix all together and pour Italian dressing over; let set for several hours before serving.

title: cheese sticks
directions: Mix all ingredients with 2 tablespoons ice water; let chill. Roll and cut in strips.
Cook in medium oven.

title: granny cake
directions: Sift first 4 dry ingredients.
Add eggs and pineapple.
Pour mixture of brown sugar and nuts on top.
Bake for 40 minutes at 325°.
Punch holes in cake when done.

title: upside down pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°; grease a 9 x 13-inch pan with deep sides. Mix pumpkin, milk, sugar, eggs and spices very well and pour into pan.
Sprinkle the dry cake mix over the pumpkin mix.
Sprinkle nuts over the cake mix.
Pour or drizzle the butter over the top. Bake for 1 hour.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant and slice like French fried potatoes (let bleed). Roll eggplant in mixture of corn meal and flour.
Pan-fry eggplant lightly.
Drain on paper towel.
Layer eggplant, onions and tomatoes in a baking dish.
Season to taste.
Cook 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Top with cooked, seasoned corn.
Yields 6 servings.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Bring pineapple to a boil in saucepan.
Stir dry gelatin into pineapple and mix until dissolved.
Chill until partially set. Stir in buttermilk.
Chill again until partially set.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: barbecue chicken burgers
directions: Combine chicken, bread crumbs, 1/4 cup green onions, 1/4 cup barbecue sauce, garlic, chili powder, salt and 1/2 teaspoon red pepper sauce.
Form into four 1/2-inch thick patties.
Place on a plate lined with wax paper and refrigerate.
Coat rack with cooking spray.
Preheat grill to medium-hot.

title: bread cake
directions: Melt margarine in the pan you will use to bake in.
Crumble bread and add remaining cake ingredients.
Mix well; pour in pan. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry waldorf salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; toss well.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Toss gently just before serving.
Yield:
9 servings, 103 calories.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and add other ingredients, except the noodles and cheese.
Simmer for one hour.
Cook noodles; drain. Place alternate layers of noodles, meat mixture and cheese in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain all fruit; save pineapple juice.
Mix all ingredients and set in refrigerator for 6 hours.
When ready to serve, add pineapple juice if too dry (normally not needed).

title: rebecca's onion relish
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer. When onions become clear, pour into pint jars and seal.
Makes 3 to 4 pints.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel sweet potatoes and cook until done.
When done, cut in half lengthwise.
Set aside.
Bring syrup, sugar and margarine to a boil over medium heat in a small saucepan.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Pour 1/2 cup syrup into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Arrange potatoes in syrup, then add remaining syrup.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until well glazed.
Baste often.

title: good corn bread
directions: Mix together with enough water to mix well.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Sprinkle each piece of chicken with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Dip chicken in oil.
Roll in seasoned bread crumbs.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: golden potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in skin and cool, then peel and coarsely shred. In a saucepan over low heat, combine cheese and butter, stirring occasionally until melted.
Remove from heat; blend in sour cream, onions, salt, pepper and then add potatoes, stirring lightly. Turn into buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Dot with 2 tablespoons of butter and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Mix yeast, sugar and water.
Set aside to proof.
Combine whole wheat flour, 1 1/2 cups bread flour, salt and dry milk.
Add butter, honey and molasses to proofed yeast mixture.
Add flour mixture to yeast mixture gradually, mixing thoroughly.
Add the remaining bread flour until dough becomes firm.
Knead on floured surface until elastic (10 to 15 minutes).
Place in oiled bowl. Cover and let rise until double.
Punch down.
Knead 5 minutes; cut into 2 equal parts.
Let rest 5 minutes.
Shape into loaves.
Place in greased pans.
Cover and let rise until double.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool on wire racks.

title: blender tomato bisque
directions: Puree all ingredients but avocado in blender or food processor.
Serve chilled or at room temperature over avocado cubes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello with water.
Add strawberries, pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Put half of mixture in bowl and chill until firm. Spread sour cream over firm mixture.
Pour rest of mixture on top and let it get firm.

title: corn salad
directions: Chop onion, bell pepper and tomato.
Add corn and mayonnaise. Add salt and pepper.
Mix and chill before serving.

title: (easy) chicken and rice
directions: Brown chicken in butter. Stir in your soup and water. Add salt and pepper to taste. Cover and simmer about 20 minutes. Stir in your rice and simmer until rice is tender. Stir often.

title: braised wild duck
directions: Take breast of a wild duck, chill and split the two pieces of breast longways.
Will make 4 pieces of breast the thickness of your finger.
Slice these into 1-inch strips.
Marinate breast in wine, vinegar, brown sugar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce or soak them in milk.
Take strips and shake in flour, salt and pepper mixture.
Cover thoroughly.
Brown on both sides in medium hot skillet with small amount of oil.
Cut strips into bite size chunks and serve with cocktail or mustard sauce.

title: black forest pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat cream cheese until fluffy; add sugar and cocoa. Mix well. Add egg and almond extract. With a spatula, scrape filling into crust; spread evenly. Bake 35 minutes. Cool and refrigerate. Just before serving, top with nondairy whipped topping and cherry pie filling. Prep time: 10 minutes. Baking time: 35 minutes. Chilling time: 3 hours. Servings: 8.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix well all ingredients and drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: rice chex candy
directions: In a large pan, melt margarine, chips and peanut butter. Remove from heat.
When melted, mix with rice Chex.
Coat each piece completely
with the chocolate mixture.
Pour powdered sugar into a large bowl.
Take a few cereal pieces at a time and mix with sugar.
Coat each piece with powdered sugar.
Continue until all are coated.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mash softened cream cheese. Mix into cheese, finely chopped beef and onions.
Mix well. Form into large ball.
Roll cheese ball in finely chopped pecans. Refrigerate overnight. Decorate with parsley.
Set at room temperature about 30 minutes before serving.

title: mom's easy casserole
directions: Layer beef, rice and cheese sprinkled with garlic powder in greased casserole until all is used.
Pour tomatoes over all and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese, whipped topping, peanut butter, sugar and vanilla.
Pour into crust and top with whipped topping. Sprinkle with nuts and freeze.
Thaw in refrigerator several hours before serving.
Keep refrigerated. Makes 2 pies.

title: coffee frosting
directions: Dissolve Coffee in Cream; set aside.
Cream Margarine; add Vanilla and Salt.
Gradually beat in Sugar.
Beat in enough of the coffee mixture to achieve spreading consistency.
Frost cake. Yield:
12 servings.

title: pineapple cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except nuts.
Form into 2 balls and roll in chopped nuts.
Freezes well.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Boil the potatoes in jackets.
Grate when cool.
Melt the butter and Cheddar cheese over low heat.
Remove and add the sour cream, green onion, salt and pepper. Blend.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chili rellenos bake
directions: Remove seeds from chili peppers.
Line an 8 x 11-inch glass baking pan with chilies.
Mix cheese and toss on top.
Beat eggs; add canned milk, salt and pepper.
Pour on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°, until a knife comes out clean.
Pour tomato sauce over chili and bake.
Mix with 1 teaspoon chili salsa.
Put back in oven until it bubbles.

title: choucroute a l'alasacienne
directions: Peel onions and stud each with 4 cloves.
Place onions, pork chops, salt pork, carrots and bacon in large 8-quart kettle.
Add black pepper and juniper berries, tied in a piece of cheesecloth, to the kettle.
Cover all with drained sauerkraut and pour chicken bouillon and white wine throughout.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 2 1/2 hours.
Make diagonal cuts (3) in each of the knockwurst and add them to the kettle 15 minutes before the end of cooking.

title: apple-carrot cake
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, vanilla, and vegetable oil.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon, and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Add carrots and apples.
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 13 pan and bake at 350 degrees for 60-70 minutes.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Blend cream cheese and butter with mixer.
Add sugar and vanilla and blend until smooth.
Add nuts, if desired.

title: lemon cheese cake(willa brown, hinesville, georgia)
directions: Bake cake in at least 6 layers.

title: microwave barbecued meatballs and sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs and sauce.
Add enough crumbs to meat mixture to hold together.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Arrange in pie plate.
Microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes, rotating twice.
Pour hot Barbecue Sauce over meatballs. Heat on Medium-high for 5 minutes.

title: savory pot roast
directions: Using 6 quart pan or electric fry pan, brown roast in oil on all sides.
Spoon off fat.
Add soups and 1 cup water.
Cover and cook on low about 2 hours.
Add vegetables and cook until tender, adding water if necessary.
Remove roast and vegetables.
Mix flour and 1/2 cup water until smooth.
Add gradually to soup mixture and cook until thick stirring constantly.
Serve with meat and vegetables.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Grease a 10 pie plate.
Brown beef & onion, add salt & pepper. Spread in pie plate.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Beat rest of ingredients in blender on high speed for 15 seconds.
Pour over meat & cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 min. or until knife in center comes out clean.
Let stand 5 min. before cutting.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Serve with crackers.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients slowly; stir until sugar dissolves. Cook to soft ball stage (238°).
Remove candy from heat while testing.
Blanch 2 cups unroasted Virginia peanuts (raw Spanish do not need blanching).
To blanch, cover with boiling water for 3 minutes; run under cold water.
Remove coating.
Add nuts and 1/4 teaspoon salt to mixture.
Cook to hard crack stage (290°), stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.

title: garlic dip or spread
directions: Cook butter and garlic together until garlic is done, then add Dales Sauce.
Cook until boiling.
You can add flavor or cornstarch to thicken if necessary.
Serve over steak, hamburgers or chicken.
You can also use this as a bread dip.

title: tamale corn
directions: Mix in order and bake in greased dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet n sour green beans
directions: Cook frozen green beans as directed; omit salt. Cook fresh green beans in 1/2 cup unsalted water until tender; drain and set aside. In a separate pan, melt oleo. Stir in flour and brown lightly. Stir in remaining ingredients; cook over low heat until thickened. Pour over green beans and heat 5 minutes. Serves 4 and contains only 40 calories.

title: carrot salad with raisins and nuts
directions: Scrape carrots to get a thin layer of skin off.
Grate carrots coarsely into bowl.
Add and mix remaining ingredients.
Chill and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: st. paul rice
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Brown peppers and celery; cook until tender.
Mix soup, rice and water in a pot.
Cook about 5 minutes. Add all other ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Tastes something like Chinese food.

title: glacier bay carrot cake
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pour mixture into pan and bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until done.
Let cool; spread frosting over cake.

title: fun cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Cream together the butter or shortening and sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Blend in flour mixture slowly.
Stir in M&M's.
Drop heaping teaspoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 11 minutes until browned.

title: good coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine with 1 cup sugar.
Add eggs and mix to blend. Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add dry ingredients to cream mixture alternately with sour cream to which vanilla has been added.
Mix just to blend chopped nuts, 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Turn 1/2 dough into greased 9-inch tube pan. Sprinkle 1/2 crumb mixture over this.
Pour rest of batter on top of crumb mixture.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: deannie's cheesits
directions: Work all ingredients thoroughly.
Roll very thin.
Cut rounds about size of a quarter.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets at 400° for about 10 minutes.
Watch to see they don't burn.
Salt lightly when out of the oven.
Keep tightly closed in tin.

title: hot pineapple dish
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 1/2 cup juice.
Set aside.
Combine sugar and flour in a bowl.
Add margarine and 1 cup cheese.
Mix well; gently stir in pineapple.
Pour in quart baking dish, greased.
Sprinkle crushed crackers on top.
Drizzle with reserved pineapple juice.
Bake, uncovered, for 35 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake brownies(ouie gooies)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut frozen dough into 1/4 inch thick slices.
Cover bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan with 1/2 of the dough to form crust.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Add hot water to jello and gelatin.
Stir to dissolve in large bowl.
Gradually add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into large casserole dish.
Chill until jelled.
Makes one large dish.

title: carrot salad
directions: Place carrots in a saucepan with enough cold water to cover. Add salt and bring to a boil.
Simmer, uncovered, until tender, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine eggs and milk.
Beat until well blended.
Add cracker crumbs.
Set aside until all liquid is absorbed.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese to cracker crumbs mixture.
Stir well. Spoon mixture into a greased 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.
Sprinkle cheese on top while still hot and just let it melt.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: standing rib roast
directions: Trim most fat, then pierce under fat left and put in garlic cloves.
Season with black pepper (I use coarse ground) and roast in a 325° oven for about 20 minutes per pound.
Check temperature: for rare 140°, medium 150° and well 155°.
Pour off most of the fat drippings.
Add water and A.1. sauce for au jus.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Drain all fruits.
Let cream cheese stand at room temperature. Beat cheese until fluffy.
Blend in sour cream, sugar and salt. Fold in fruits, marshmallows and nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch glass dish and freeze.
Take out of freezer about 1/2 hour before serving.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: meal-in-one
directions: Brown meat with bell pepper and onions. Cook macaroni and add to meat. Then add catsup and water. Cook for 8 minutes. Serve hot.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time, mixing well. Add vanilla; fold in potato chips.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes, until light brown, at 350°. Sprinkle with powdered sugar while warm.

title: breakfast bake
directions: Layer a 9 x 13-inch pan with croutons, sausage and cheese. Blend eggs, dry mustard and milk.
Pour over meat.
Refrigerate overnight.
In the morning, mix 1 can cream of mushroom soup and 1/2 cup milk.
Pour over it.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Saute onion in skillet with a little butter.
Add cheese and soup.
Melt.
Add sour cream.
Spread potatoes in buttered 9 x 13-inch dish; heat thoroughly.
Pour cheese mixture over potatoes. Place corn flakes in Ziploc bag and mash into crumbs.
Sprinkle crumbs over potatoes and bake approximately 1 hour at 325° or until potatoes are done.
Do not salt.

title: cheese soup
directions: Combine the ingredients.
Microwave until Velveeta begins to melt.
Put in crock-pot and cook until bubbly.
(Good with oyster crackers.)

title: lemon squares
directions: Sift together the 2 cups flour and 1/2 cup confectioners sugar.
Cut in margarine until mixture begins to cling together. Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: oatmeal war bread(recipe from ww1, 1918)
directions: Grease three 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
First measure the oatmeal, salt, sugar and fat and pour the boiling water over them.
Let stand until lukewarm; dissolve the yeast in the 1/4 cup of lukewarm water and add it to the other mixture.
Stir in the flour and knead until smooth and elastic; let rise until double in bulk; form into loaves and let rise again.
Bake in a hot oven (400°) for 30 to 35 minutes.
This is delicious toasted.
Yields 3 loaves.

title: dad's favorite chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend soft butter, sugar, eggs and water together.
In separate bowl, mix cocoa, flour, baking powder and baking soda; add to sugar mixture and blend.
Add milk and vanilla and mix on medium speed for 1 to 2 minutes.
Place in 2 (8-inch) rounds that are greased and floured.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: manicotti
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add spinach.
Mix with oregano, basil, eggs, half and half and Parmesan cheese.
Boil manicotti shells at least 5 minutes.
Drain; put ingredients in manicotti shells.
Pour spaghetti sauce over stuffed manicotti; then pour white sauce on top.

title: tune up a tuna
directions: Grease a 10 x 6-inch baking pan.
Mix Bisquick mix and water. Knead on floured surface until smooth.
Press into pan bottom and up sides.
Grate cheese.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup over dough.
Mix other ingredients together and pour over dough.
Add remaining cheese. Decorate with pimento strips.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: mom's cranberry-cheese salad
directions: In small saucepan, dissolve unflavored gelatin in cup of cold water.
Heat to mix, set aside.
Dissolve flavored gelatin in boiling water, stir in relish, 2 tablespoons lemon juice.
Pour in a lightly oiled 1 1/2-quart mold.
Chill until slightly thickened.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in soda.
Mix well.
Pour over popcorn in large container, mixing well.
Place on 2 large cookie sheets in 200° oven for 1 hour.
Stir several times.
Nuts or peanuts may be added before baking if desired.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Break up ground beef into a baking dish.
Sprinkle onion and pepper over meat.
Spread soup over meat.
Top off with layer of Tater Tots.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: oatmeal coconut crispies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well. Sift together flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Fold into the creamed mixture. Blend in oats, coconut and nuts.
Drop by spoonful onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Combine milk, eggs, cake mix, pudding and chips.
Mix by hand until well blended, about 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Do not overbake. Cool 15 minutes in pan.
Remove from pan and finish cooling on rack.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: bran muffins
directions: Beat sugar and eggs.
Add oil, molasses, oatmeal, buttermilk, flour, soda and salt; beat well.
Add cereal, raisins and boiling water.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight (covered).

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar. Add to rest of ingredients, except for bacon and refrigerate overnight.
Add bacon just before serving.

title: edible play dough
directions: Mix all above ingredients well.
Form into ball.
Divide among children to play with and eat.
May use edibles to decorate: raisins, nuts, chocolate chips, Cheerios.

title: dilled pork scallopini
directions: Cut pork crosswise into 12 slices.
Flatten to 1/4 inch thickness.
Dust pork lightly with flour.
Combine egg and water. Dip pork into egg mixture, then coat with crumbs.
In large skillet, saute pork in butter, a few pieces at a time, about 3 minutes per side.
Add more butter if necessary.
Keep pork slices warm.

title: guacamole
directions: Cook tomato pieces in a dry skillet until all water is absorbed and lightly brown.
Cool to room temperature.
Mix all ingredients well.
Keep refrigerated.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and margarine with sugar.
Add beaten egg and milk and beat until creamy.
Add vanilla.
Then add dry ingredients.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheets; flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar (red or green, if desired).
Bake at 350° to 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 5 1/2 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: baked white fish
directions: Melt butter in a baking dish.
Place 1 pound of fish in dish. Drizzle lemon juice over fish.
Sprinkle fish with thyme, tarragon, salt and pepper.
Pour white wine over fish.
Mix crushed corn flakes and Parmesan cheese together.
Sprinkle flakes over fish.
Bake in a 425° oven for 20 minutes.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, egg and molasses until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken stuffing bake
directions: Heat water and butter to boiling; pour over stuffing.
Mix well.
Put one half of this into 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Stir together soup, mayonnaise, milk, chicken, celery and spinach. Spoon evenly over stuffing mix.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes more until cheese is melted.

title: aunt seralla's pink salad
directions: Heat pineapple and juice until boiling.
Stir in gelatin.
Mix well.
Set aside to cool.
Fold in cottage cheese and whipped topping.
Put mixture in jello mold.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.

title: avocado pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain in colander and return to pot.
Add butter, grated cheeses, seasonings and thinly sliced avocados.
Stir.
Serves 4 to 6. Very quick and easy to make and your family will think you're a gourmet cook!

title: lime salad
directions: Mix lime Jell-O with 1 cup hot water.
Add cream cheese and mix
with
fork
until smooth as possible.
Add Carnation milk and stir.
After mixing, and crushed pineapple and nuts. Refrigerate and serve when congealed.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand and juice until blended.
Then stir in cool whip. Save 1 cup for top.
Pour into pie crust and top with cool whip.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put in dish.
Place in 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Top with crushed potato chips before baking.

title: chocolate-butterscotch rice krispies treats
directions: *I use 12 ounces of each!

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Use ungreased cookie sheet or round cake pan.
Chop shortening into flour with pastry blender until fine pieces.
Mix in dry ingredients and then milk.
Stir only enough to combine.
On floured surface, pat dough flat but thick. Less handling, the better.
Cut biscuits with floured large glass and bake about 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: In a pan or double boiler, mix all ingredients except egg whites and sugar and cook on low heat, stirring often, until it begins to thicken.
Add 1 Tbsp Knox gelatin to 1/4 c cold water and let stand 5 minutes.
Then add to pumpkin mixture. Then beat 3 egg whites, add 2 Tbsp sugar, mix and pour into hot pumpkin mixture and mix about 3 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, saute onion in melted butter.
Add potatoes. Barely cover with water.
Season with salt and pepper and cook until well done.
Stir in soup and add cheese which has been cut in thin slices.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Add milk and heat thoroughly.
Can be served hot or cold.

title: fudge batter pudding
directions: This pudding when baked has a chocolate sauce on bottom and cake on top.
Mix margarine, 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla together. Sift flour, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and 1/2 teaspoon salt together and add alternately with milk to first mixture.
Mix well and stir in nuts (nuts may be omitted if desired).
Mix together 1/2 cup sugar, 5 tablespoons cocoa, 1/4 teaspoon salt and boiling water.
Turn into 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish or pan and drop batter by tablespoon on top.
Bake in moderate oven, 350°, for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm.
Spoon out a portion of the cake and cover with sauce.
Whipped cream or top milk goes well with this pudding if it is served cold.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Cook chicken breasts and your favorite Chicken Tonight sauce on low heat all day.
Prepare noodles.
Serve with a vegetable, salad and bread.
Easy meal for working Moms.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix well the first 5 ingredients.
Add enough of milk to fill up a gallon freezer; then freeze.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 10 minutes in a 350° oven.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake for 40 minutes until done.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat, onion, and pepper.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and oil.
Add rest of ingredients to egg mixture.
Butter and flour pans.
Bake at 350° for one hour. Makes two loaves.

title: fried zucchini flowers
directions: Wash blossoms and remove inner small piece, drain and wrap in paper towel while making batter.
Beat eggs with salt, flour and baking powder.
Dip 1 flower at a time into batter and fry until golden.
Eat as appetizer.

title: corn pudding
directions: Add all ingredients in order listed.
Mix well, then sprinkle nutmeg on top. Bake in a slow oven at 350° until golden brown or about 40 minutes.

title: irish stew(crock-pot)
directions: In your Crock-Pot, season cubed lamb with salt and pepper. Add remaining ingredients, except peas or vegetables (omit Tapioca if you don't want gravy thickened).
Stir well.
Cover and cook on Low 10-12 hours.
Add peas or vegetables during the last 1-2 hours of cooking

title: pickled eggs
directions: Simmer vinegar, water, sugar, salt, celery seed and spices. Cool liquid.
Strain over shelled, hard-cooked eggs.
Add minced garlic and marinate in covered jar.
Store in refrigerator for 2 or 3 days.

title: oven fried herb chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place butter in a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan; place in oven and melt butter.
Combine flour and seasonings in bowl.
Dip chicken pieces in butter, then flour; coat well. Arrange chicken, skin side down in single layer in remaining butter in pan.
Bake 20 minutes; turn chicken, continue baking 35 to 40 minutes until tender.
Baste with drippings.
Remove chicken to heated platter, keep warm.

title: mock lasagne
directions: Boil water to cook shells. Drain and rinse.
Brown crumbled hamburger.
Drain off grease.
Add Ragu and spices, and simmer. In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer part of Ragu to cover bottom. Put 1/2 shells in pan.
Cover with half remaining Ragu and half cheese. Layer again with remaining shells, Ragu and cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cut in squares.
Serves 8.

title: pork chops
directions: Combine soup, water, vinegar, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, and pepper sauce.
Spoon mixture over chops. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until chops are done.

title: stuffed winter squash
directions: Cut squash in half; remove seed.
Place squash halves, cut side down, in a shallow baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes, or until almost tender.

title: peanut butter and banana sandwich
directions: Spread 1 tablespoon peanut butter on 1 slice of bread. Arrange banana slices on peanut butter.
Top with another slice of bread with 1 tablespoon peanut butter on it.

title: egg custard
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in a bowl; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch pie plate.
Bake for 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil, eggs and bananas; blend well.
Add buttermilk.
Blend well.
Add chopped nuts (optional).
Bake 55 minutes in oiled medium loaf pan.

title: o'henry bars
directions: Butter a 12 x 17-inch cookie sheet and set aside.
Preheat oven to 200°.
Measure sugar and syrup; put in saucepan.
Stir and cook over medium heat, stirring frequently.
Bring to a boil. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Put into prepared cookie sheet.
Press down slightly.
Sprinkle chips evenly on top of bars.
Put in oven and leave in until chips are melted soft enough to blend and spread. Let cool and enjoy!

title: aunt fern's sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage until browned; drain. Add remaining ingredients. Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and stir.
Bake an additional 30 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes.
Garnish with fresh mushrooms and pepper strips.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: cold carrot salad
directions: Cook and dice carrots; set aside.
Combine all other ingredients.
Pour over carrots.
Refrigerate for 4 hours.
Serve. Lasts in refrigerator at least 4 weeks.

title: black forest chocolate cheese cake
directions: Combine crumbs and butter; press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Mix in large bowl the cheese until fluffy; gradually add Eagle Brand and blend until smooth.
Add eggs, cornstarch and extract; mix well.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 300° for 55 minutes or until center is set.
Cool; chill.
Slice and serve with cherry filling over top.

title: corn salad(from 1975 edition)
directions: Cook onions 10 minutes; drain.
Mix all together; boil for 20 minutes.
Makes 7 quarts or 14 pints.

title: corn souffle
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes. Serves 8.

title: nut horns
directions: Mix all together and roll out on board sprinkled with 3 parts sugar
to
1 part flour.
Cut dough half lengthwise and sprinkle with filling.
Roll like a jelly roll from corner to corner.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Cut dates. Place in bowl and sprinkle with baking soda. Pour boiling water over and let stand until lukewarm. Add butter, sugar and beaten eggs. Add balance of dry ingredients. Bake in greased loaf pan (two). Bake at 300° for 40 to 45 minutes. Check to see if done with toothpick.

title: shrimp pizza
directions: With a mixer, combine cream cheese, lemon juice, Tabasco, onion, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt.

Spread this mixture with a spatula on a platter or large round plate (like a crust). Pour chili sauce over cream cheese "crust" and spread evenly. Sprinkle the shrimp on top, forming the 3rd layer of your pizza. Serve with crackers - we love Sociables crackers.
Can be made the night before.

title: mound cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake mix using package directions for a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pierce holes in top of cake with fork.
Combine sweetened condensed milk and cream of coconut in bowl; mix well. Pour over cake.
Cool completely.
Spread with whipped topping; sprinkle with coconut.
Chill overnight.
Yield:
15 servings.

title: okra patties
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add milk, oil and eggs.
Mix well.
Add okra and onion; stir to mix.
Drop by teaspoon into skillet of hot oil.
Brown on both sides.

title: ensalada de naranjas(orange salad)
directions: Peel and slice oranges, discarding seeds.
Peel and slice cucumber.
Chop onion and green pepper.

title: my sister's rum cake
directions: Mix all for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan which has nuts in the bottom, if you desire.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Cream softened margarine with sugar.
This will look coarse and crumbly.
Add Eagle Brand milk.
Mix until smooth.
Add vanilla. Stir until blended.
Chill in refrigerator for about 1 hour.
Then shape sugar mixture around each cherry.
Place on wax paper on cookie sheet.
Freeze until hard (overnight).

title: christmas fig pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Set for hour.
Steam for 4 hours. Serve with sauce.

title: butterfinger banana cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 inch baking pan.
Prepare cake mix batter according to package directions; stir in bananas and 3/4 cup chopped Butterfinger.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely in pan on wire rack.
Frost cake with white frosting and sprinkle with remaining chopped butterfinger.

title: mustard easter eggs
directions: Slowly blend Heinz distilled vinegar, prepared mustard, water, sugar, salt and 6 whole cloves.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Cool.
Pour over 18 shelled hard-cooked eggs and sliced onions.
Yellow food coloring may be added for a deeper color.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: pork chop potato bake
directions: Brown the chops in a lightly greased skillet.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt and set aside.
Combine the soup, milk, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 teaspoon seasoned salt.
Stir in the potatoes, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can of the onions.
Spoon the mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange the chops over the potatoes.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 40 minutes. Top with the remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel sweet potatoes.
Slice in half lengthwise.
Place in an ovenproof dish.
Cover with brown sugar and sugar.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and dot with butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: very good cake topping
directions: Beat egg yolks with sugar until reaching a lemon color.
Add pineapple juice.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, about 8 minutes, until thick.
Add marshmallows.
Chill.
When cold, fold in vanilla and whipped cream.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl. Refrigerate. Can be used as salad or dessert.

title: asparagus chicken casserole
directions: Drain asparagus and combine with soup, chicken, cracker crumbs, cheese and water chestnuts in a 1-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with garlic powder and almonds.

title: low calorie island dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl or screw-top jar.
Makes 1 1/2 cups dressing.
Keeps a week in refrigerator.
Two tablespoons is 26 calories.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray cookie sheet or large jelly roll pan with cooking spray.
In a large bowl, mix potatoes with oil. Pour out potatoes into single layer on prepared pan.
Salt.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes, turning 2 to 3 times, until light brown. Resalt, if desired.
Delicious!

title: marinated brisket roast
directions: Sprinkle the meat well with garlic and onion powder.
Place in non-metallic roasting pan.
Pour the liquid smoke and Worcestershire sauce over the meat.
Place in refrigerator overnight, turning at least 1 time.
When ready to cook, turn once more.
Cover with foil and bake about 4 hours at 350°.
Slices better after cooling.

title: banana salad
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients in double boiler until mixture is fairly thick.
Add butter.
Then layer bananas, dressing and peanuts.
Keep layering until you run out of dressing.

title: rice casserole
directions: Grate onion and saute in butter.
Place in large baking dish with 1 cup of rice and bouillon cubes.
Add water.
Bake 1 hour in medium oven.

title: heavenly chicken
directions: In a small saucepan, cook spinach according to package directions; drain well.
In a medium saucepan, make white sauce by sauteing onions in margarine over low heat until tender; then stir in flour, adding milk all at once.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until bubbly.
Boil and stir 1 minute more until smooth and thickened.

title: mother's cottage pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients, but egg whites.
Beat egg whites stiff and mix (fold) into cake batter.
Put into greased pan.
(I can still see Mother's pan.
It was blue and white granite on the outside and white on the inside, about 9 x 13-inch size.)

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine mashed bananas and sugar; blend well.
Add egg and oil; mix well.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts; mix well, then pour into well-greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: spicy buffalo wings
directions: Rinse
chicken	wings.	Add
salt
and	pepper to flour (other seasonings
may
be added if desired) in a bowl.
Heat grease. Coat
chicken
wings
with flour mixture and place in the
grease for about 4 minutes or until done.	Take out wings and place in a bowl.
Add butter to the hot wings and sprinkle hot sauce all over the chicken.

title: cajun deep-fry turkey
directions: You also need a 60-quart boiling pot with basket, elevated propane burner, meat pump and long reed temperature gauge.

title: red punch
directions: Boil water.
Add Jell-O and sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Add pineapple juice.
Freeze.
Thaw 4 hours before serving.
Add 1 (2-liter) bottle of 7-Up.

title: peach pit jelly
directions: Collect a 2-pound coffee can of peach pits.
Soak pits overnight in cold water.
Boil 15 minutes in same water; drain well and use the juice as you would any other juice to make jelly. Plum jelly can be made the same way.

title: barb's cheese ball
directions: Let the cheeses soften. Mix cheeses together with mixer until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients, except nuts, and mix well.
Roll into a ball, cover and place in refrigerator. Chill at least 2 hours.
When ready to serve, roll it in the chopped nuts.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Place in 8-inch casserole dish. Pour soup over meat.
Top with cheese.
Cover with Tater Tots. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until Tater Tots are browned.

title: cherry cheese salad
directions: Combine the orange Jell-O, water, cream cheese and marshmallows and cook until melted and well blended.
Set aside until it starts to set.
Whip cream; blend into Jell-O with vanilla, pineapple and mayonnaise.
Put in 11 x 13-inch pan and let stand until firm.
Prepare the cherry Jell-O according to package directions.
Cool and then pour over first mixture. Sprinkle with walnuts, if desired.

title: cheesy broccoli casserole
directions: Cut broccoli into spears.
Cook until crisp.
Drain. Meanwhile, combine beaten eggs, cottage cheese, Cheddar cheese, onion, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper in a bowl.

title: country cornbread
directions: Mix and beat all ingredients well.
Bake in greased pan or muffin tins.
Bake for 12 minutes or until brown at 475.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill.

title: holiday ham ball
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch).
Mix all ingredients.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart in pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Remove from pan immediately.
Serve warm.
Yield:
about 7 dozen.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage for a few minutes.
Saute onion and celery in a small amount of oil or margarine.
Add soup and cheese, then mix all ingredients together, including bread crumbs.
A few crumbs may be used to top the casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, sugar, flour and egg yolks.
Add melted butter. Add remaining ingredients and beaten egg whites last.
Pour into unbaked pie shells, 3 or 4.

title: lemon squash
directions: Stir honey and cinnamon into water in a saucepan.
Add squash and lemon; bring to boil.
Cover and simmer about 10 minutes, until squash is tender.
Serves 4.

title: scallops scampi
directions: In heavy frypan, saute onion, garlic and parsley in oil until onion is tender, but not browned.
Add scallops and simmer, turning often, until cooked (about 10 minutes).
Season to taste, sprinkle hot, cooked linguini liberally with cheese.
Spoon scallop mixture over all.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: zucchini-corn pudding
directions: Cook zucchini until tender; drain.
Squeeze out all liquid. Saute onion, pepper, garlic and rosemary in oil until tender.
Add zucchini, corn, cheese, eggs, salt and pepper; mix.
Turn into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: homemade heath bars
directions: Line a cookie sheet with foil, then coat with cooking spray. Place crackers in rows to fill the sheet (you probably won't use the whole box, so make chili, too!) Melt butter in a saucepan, and add brown sugar. Boil for 3 minutes, stirring constantly. Pour syrup over crackers and spread gently to cover all of the crackers. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Remove and turn off oven. Sprinkle chocolate chips over top and place pan back in warm oven for 5 minutes until chocolate is melted. Spread chocolate evenly over crackers and top with pecans, if desired. Allow to cool completely, then cut (or break) into pieces.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all above ingredients and chill before serving.

title: amaretto bread pudding
directions: Break challah into 1-inch pieces in a large bowl.
Add half and half.
Cover and let stand 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder. Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy; add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Add flour and milk alternately, ending with flour.
Bake in 10-inch tube pan about 50 minutes at 350°.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in heavy roaster with lid.
Bake in 275° oven for 5 hours.
Do not stir.
Delicious!

title: shortcut red velvet cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions except for liquid.
