Pour red food coloring in measuring cup; finish filling with liquid called for.
Bake as directed.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add barbecue sauce, peppers and onions. Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Serve on hard rolls.

title: chicken salad hawaiian
directions: Cook rice.
Cool.
Mix rest of ingredients together and chill.

title: venison jerky
directions: Blend all ingredients well; roll between wax paper sheets. Take off top sheet and brush meat with 1 ounce liquid smoke diluted with 1 ounce of water.
Place in oven on wire racks.
Dry partially at 160°, then remove paper.
Place back on wire racks and dry for another 3 to 4 hours.
Cut as desired.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix and make loaf.

title: gone-all-day stew
directions: Mix together soup, water/wine and flour until smooth. Combine with remaining ingredients in covered roasting pan. Bake at 275° for 4 to 5 hours. When ready to serve, adjust seasoning, if desired. Serve over noodles or with crunchy French bread (to soak up the gravy). Coleslaw is a nice winter accompaniment or serve fresh tomatoes on a bed of lettuce in summer. Yield: 8 servings.

title: caramelized brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare the brownie mix according to the package directions.
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt the butter in a small saucepan.
Add the pecans and sugar and cook, over medium heat, stirring frequently until the sugar dissolves.
Drizzle the caramel mixture over brownie batter and bake until a toothpick can be inserted and withdrawn cleanly, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: Drain sauerkraut real well.
Mix together lightly the potato soup, sour cream and milk.
Blend this mixture into the drained sauerkraut lightly.
Place in a greased casserole and top with Swiss cheese slices.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: eggplant patties
directions: Peel and cut eggplant. Steam until tender (10 to 15 minutes). Drain 1 hour (this removes excess water).
Mix eggplant with remaining ingredients. Shape into patties.
Fry on top of stove or bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli and cheese soup ii
directions: Cook onion in margarine; stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk; cook until thick.
Add cheese and stir until melted; remove from heat.
In medium saucepan dissolve bouillon in water.
Add bay leaf; add broccoli and simmer 20 minutes.
Add to cheese mixture.
Cook 10 more minutes on low heat.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix well.
Pour into a greased and lined tube pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350° or bake in layer pans and cook according to cake box directions.
Cool cake before frosting.

title: peppered cheddar dip
directions: Mix sour cream and Cheddar cheese until well blended. Add onion, green pepper, salt, Tabasco sauce and milk; mix well. If necessary, add another tablespoon of milk to make a good dipping consistency. Cover; chill at least 1 hour.
Serve with carrot and celery sticks. Makes 2 cups of dip.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Combine all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight. Drain mushrooms when ready to serve.

title: new potatoes with cheese
directions: Wash and slice potatoes (do not peel).
Place in a saucepan and cover with water.
Boil until tender.
Drain completely.
Line a greased casserole dish with a single layer of cooked potatoes. Sprinkle with part of the cheese and then with part of the bacon. Continue to layer in that order.
Pour melted butter over all. Bake for 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: pickled beets
directions: Boil all
together
for about 10 minutes.
Put in beets and simmer for about 10 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: spicy oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat all ingredients until well mixed.
Drop by spoonful 1 inch apart on cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 16 to 20 cookies.

title: scones
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease large baking sheet.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cream of tartar; blend with pastry cutter.
Beat half and half and egg; reserve 2 tablespoons.
Add to dry ingredients.
Form soft dough.
Knead 4 or 6 times and divide in half.
Roll half into 8-inch round and cut into 4 wedges.
Do second half.
Pierce tops of scones with fork.
Brush with reserved egg mix.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes.

title: hash
directions: In large skillet, heat butter and oil.
Add potatoes and onion and cook over medium heat until potatoes are lightly browned, turning occasionally.
Add corned beef, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook over medium heat until hot, turning frequently.

title: quick chicken pot pie
directions: Combine chicken, broth, soup and mixed vegetables in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into
9x13 inch baking dish.
Combine flour, margarine and milk in bowl; mix well.
Spoon over chicken mixture. Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: yeast dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add Crisco, sugar and salt. Beat in 1 1/2 cups of flour.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add rest of flour or enough flour just so it isn't sticky.
Let raise until double. Make out into rolls.
Let raise again.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: deion's special fruit dish
directions: Mix low-fat Cool Whip with all the fresh or canned fruit.
Add 1 to 3 drops of lemon juice and stir well.
Let mixture set in refrigerator 15 to 25 minutes.
Yields 4 to 8 servings.

title: perfect meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 5 x 6-inch loaf pan.
Mix beef, oats, eggs, 1 can tomato sauce, onions, salt and pepper. Pack firmly into greased loaf pan.
Chill until meat loaf is firm. Bake 1 hour.

title: spaghetti and meatballs
directions: Meatballs:
Add Progresso bread crumbs, diced onion, salt and pepper to uncooked ground beef.
Mix well.
Roll into balls.
Slow cook in frying pan until cooked through.

title: coconut sheet cake
directions: Follow directions for cake mix except add coconut to the cake mix.
Put in 13 x 9 x 2-inch sheet pan.

title: recipe for a happy life
directions: Serves any number of teddy bear lovers!

title: deviled tuna
directions: Over low heat, melt butter.
Stir in flour, salt and 1/4 teaspoon paprika until blended.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook, stirring, until mixture is thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in tuna and remaining ingredients, except cheese.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients well, then add the oatmeal and coconut.
Stir and pour into a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: buttermilk lemon pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry; trim, seal and flute edges.
Set aside.

title: eagle brand milk cookies
directions: Dissolve chocolate chips in pan. Add milk, graham crackers and nuts. Mix well. Drop with spoon on waxed paper. Allow to harden and cool. Cookies can be made any size you prefer.

title: gnocchi
directions: Peel the potatoes and boil them in salted water.
When they are thoroughly cooked, puree them, then while they are still hot, incorporate the flour and lightly beaten egg until a smooth paste is obtained.
Leave them for 30 minutes.

title: stewed shrimp
directions: Add potatoes and onion to oil and water in a 2 to 3-quart boiler or saucepan.
Cook on medium heat for 20 minutes.
Add shrimp; salt and pepper.
Cook another 15 minutes, making sure potatoes are soft.
Mixture should be thick, not soupy.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, stir all ingredients together until well mixed.
Drop from a teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes until centers of cookies are golden brown.
(Edges will look darker.)
Cool on cookie sheet for about 1 minute, then remove.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Soften and combine cream cheese with dressing mix. Chill until ready to use. (Can be made 2 or 3 days ahead.) Spread on bread. Add a slice of cucumber. Sprinkle with dill weed.

title: one step lasagna
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Spread 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Layer one-half of each of the noodles, cottage cheese, yogurt mixture, spinach, Mozzarella, then spaghetti sauce.
Repeat.
Top with Parmesan.
Add the cup of water around the sides; cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Remove foil and bake 15 minutes longer.
Let sit for 20 minutes before serving.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spoon onto a cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until cookies are done.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Mix these and spread on top with melted chocolate bits.
This makes the icing.
When cooled, cut into strips the size of a finger.

title: chicken supreme
directions: In very large mixing bowl, place chicken (cut into pieces), sliced mushrooms (reserving juice), pimento and onion.
(*Add enough milk to mushroom juice to make 1 1/2 cups liquid.)
Stir into mayonnaise together with seasonings.
Add to chicken and toss lightly.
Pour into large ungreased baking tin or casserole. Cover.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.
Serve on hot, toasted Chinese noodles; top with toasted almonds.
Serves about 16.

title: smothered pork chops
directions: Fry and drain grease from pork chops.
Fry onions.
Put a little water in frying pan; add fried pork chops.
Cook about 15 minutes.
Then thicken with a little flour and water.
Let simmer on low; season the gravy with salt and pepper.

title: spinach bread
directions: Toothpicks will be needed to hold bread together during baking. Remember to count the toothpicks.
Remove after baking. Preheat oven to 400°.

title: chicken legs in coconut cream
directions: Peel and chop the onions and garlic. Wash and dry the chicken legs. Add salt and pepper to taste. Brown chicken in hot oil on both sides. Set aside. Saute briefly the onions and garlic in some oil. Add curry powder, soy sauce and brown sugar; saute, stirring for 1 minute. Add the broth and chicken legs and cook covered for 20 minutes. Stir in coconut cream. Garnish with parsley. Serves 6.

title: cracker dressing
directions: Crush crackers into small pieces (not crumbs).
Place in a baking dish.
Mix in egg, onion and celery.
Cover with broth until edges are visible.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Combine peanut butter, milk and cream cheese in a large mixing bowl on low speed.
Add powdered sugar and whipped topping; mix until smooth.
Pour into a 9-inch graham cracker crust.
Freeze until firm.
Drizzle with chocolate syrup.
Store leftovers in freezer.

title: low sugar apricot-pineapple jam
directions: Cook apricots, lemon juice, 1 cup sugar and pineapple juice to a boil then slowly add the other 1 cup sugar and the Clear Jell. Cook an additional 3 minutes.
Ladle into pint jars.
Seal with lids and rings.
Put in hot water bath for 10 minutes.

title: salad
directions: Add potatoes just before serving.

title: deep dark chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixer bowl.
Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in boiling water.
(Batter will be thin.)
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.
Frost with One-Bowl Buttercream Frosting.
(Recipe on every can of Hershey's cocoa.)

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes; cool, peel and grate potatoes.
Cook onions in melted margarine until onions are clear.
Add cheese, sour cream and potatoes to the onion and margarine.
Cook altogether over low heat until the cheese melts.
Put into buttered casserole dish. Add more grated cheese on top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until cheese is bubbling.

title: easy chicken and rice
directions: Place rice in ungreased 9x12-inch baking dish.
Mix liquids and pour into dish.
Place chicken in mixture and sprinkle onion soup over.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: cherry fluff salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: chocolate peanut butter clusters
directions: Combine peanut butter, butterscotch morsels and chocolate morsels.
Microwave (50% power) for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add peanuts. Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper.
Chill until firm.
Store in refrigerator.

title: meatball soup
directions: In a large bowl, mix ground beef, bread crumbs and 1 teaspoon salt.
Shape mixture into 1-inch meatballs.
In 5-quart Dutch oven, over medium-high heat, in hot salad oil, cook meatballs, a few at a time, until well browned on all sides, removing meatballs to a plate as they brown.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Dice onion and green pepper.
Saute in cooking oil until tender.
In another pan, cook frozen lima beans until tender. Drain.
Dilute mushroom soup and combine all ingredients.
Pour into baking dish topped with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted through, 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: frosty orange cooler
directions: In pitcher combine water, orange juice, lemon and sugar. Dissolve sugar, then chill.
Just before serving, add ginger ale. Scoop sherbet into glasses and pour juice mixture over it. Garnish with mint sprigs and orange slices or as desired.

title: tuna apple salad
directions: Rinse and drain tuna.
Mix tuna and other ingredients, except lettuce, in bowl.
Use immediately or chill 1 to 2 hours.
Serve on a bed of lettuce leaves.

title: dirty ice cream
directions: Crush Oreos.
Soften ice cream.
Mix all ingredients together. Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze until serving.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Roll
out pastry a little less than 1/8 inch thick and cut into
7-inch squares.
Pare and core an apple for each dumpling.	Boil next 4 ingredients together for 3 minutes.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, brown sausage.
Drain well and set aside.
In large bowl, combine milk, eggs, dry mustard and salt.
Beat for 1 minute on medium speed.
Stir in cheese, sausage and bread.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes, or until knife inserted into center comes out clean.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Cream sugar with salad dressing.
Mix baking soda and water; add to creamed mixture.
Sift flour and cocoa.
Stir into creamed mixture and add salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: apple bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beaten well.
Stir in flour and salt.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk; add to batter, mixing well. Stir in vanilla and apples.
Spoon into well-greased and floured loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Sprinkle with topping.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: noodle-rice
directions: Crush noodles; brown in melted margarine until golden.
Add chicken broth and rice.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until broth is absorbed.
(Can add small, drained peas.) Great with chicken.

title: lo-fat chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt and herbs.
Heat oil. Brown chicken on both sides. Add lemon juice. Cover and simmer 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Let set 5 minutes, covered.
Serve on rice with pan juices on top.

title: mmmm-mmmm meat loaf
directions: Mix tomato sauce, milk and egg into meat.
Add remaining ingredients.
If necessary, add more cracker crumbs.
Mold into a loaf.
Bake at 350°, covered, for an hour or a little more. Uncover and bake for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer.

title: a b c breakfast rolls
directions: Butter pan.
Shape rolls into golf ball size.
Put in Bundt pan half of the rolls.
Sprinkle sugar, cinnamon, nuts and dry coconut pie filling over rolls.
Repeat, using second dozen rolls.
Put in cool oven overnight (uncovered).
Next morning, remove rolls from oven.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mexican davis style
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Brown beef in 12-inch skillet over medium
heat.
Drain
grease.
Pour
2 tablespoons sauce into meat;
mix well.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Pour 2 tablespoons sauce
into bottom of 9 x 9-inch dish.
Fill flour tortilla with beef, beans and cheese.
Place in dish.
Make as many as
you
like.
Pour
sauce over tortillas, then sprinkle cheese over.
Cook
for
minutes
until
cheese is melted. Serve with remaining beans and add chips to complete meal.

title: fudge brownie pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch glass pie pan.
In double boiler, melt chocolate and butter.
Cool.
In medium bowl, slightly beat eggs.
Stir in sugar, flour and vanilla.
Blend well.
Add cooled chocolate and nuts.
Spread in pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add all ingredients.
Bake in greased 2-quart casserole at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes, until bubbly.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients.
You will probably have to use your hands. Form into a ball and roll in chopped pecans.
Chill.

title: chicken stroganoff
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken.
Cook until opaque, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes.
Transfer to a bowl.
Cover and keep warm.
Add onion and mushrooms to skillet; cook about 6 to 8 minutes.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Roll in balls and press with fork on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: date refrigerator cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream the sugars and shortening.
Add the beaten eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Add oatmeal, nuts and dates.
Form in long, individual rolls (about 18 inches long) on Saran Wrap; wrap tightly.
Chill.
Slice 1/2 inch thick.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes. Makes 5 dozen.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix together and cook over low heat until real thick.
Pour into baked pie shell and bake for 5 to 10 minutes.
Top with meringue.

title: holiday squares florentine
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients except crescent rolls. Mix well.

title: gold punch(serves 75 seven ounce cups)
directions: Pour liquid together and add sherbet last.

title: pecan waffle mix
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add liquids and egg yolks, mixing well. Beat egg whites until stiff; add to mixture, stirring just until blended. Cook in waffle iron.

title: coconut sour cream layer cake
directions: Split cake layers. Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut. Blend and chill. Reserve 1 cup of mixture for frosting.
Spread remaining portion between layers. Combine reserved mixture with Cool Whip and ice the cake. Seal in an airtight container and refrigerate 3 days before serving.

title: cheesecake father sarducci
directions: Combine ricotta and sour cream.
Slowly beat in cream cheese, sugar and butter.
Increase speed to medium, add eggs, flour, cornstarch, vanilla and lemon juice.
Beat on highest speed 5 minutes.
Pour mixture into 12-inch spring form pan.
Bake in preheated 350 oven for 1 hour.
Turn oven off and leave in over with door closed 1 hour.
Cool on rack.

title: pepperoni potato salad
directions: Season to taste with salt, pepper, celery salt and garlic powder.
Add enough mayonnaise to coat, then 3/4 bottle Catalina dressing to coat.
You can mix the mayo.
Add less if too much dressing.
Enjoy.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Place in 10-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 box yellow cake mix on top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: "old mexican inn's" orange dip(corsicana's oldest mexican restaurant)
directions: Blend well, cover and refrigerate.
Serve with chips.

title: fresh berry pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Pour mixture over berries and mix lightly.
Pour berries into pie pan lined with 1/2 of the pastry.
Dot with butter.
Roll remaining pastry in circle to fit pan.
Place over berries and flute edges to enclose.
Cover pastry edges with 1 1/2-inch wide strip of aluminum foil to prevent excessive browning.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 45 minutes or until crust is golden brown and juice begins to bubble through crust. Serve warm but not hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate eclaire
directions: Mix well with mixer, 2 pkg. vanilla instant pudding and milk until thick. Fold in cool whip. Put layer of whole graham crackers in a 9 by 13 inch dish as close together as possible. Spread 1/2 of the pudding mix on crackers. Place another layer of crackers and pour on remaining pudding mix. Top with crackers, then spread icing on top. Refrigerate.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a large bowl.
Make dressing by shaking remaining ingredients together in a jar.
Pour dressing over cabbage mixture and toss gently to coat.
Chill before serving.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Top with topping.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into thin strips.
Dredge in flour, salt and pepper. Saute onions, mushrooms and garlic in butter.
Add meat and brown lightly.
Add bouillon and simmer meat until tender (several hours).
Add Worcestershire and paprika.
Add a little water during cooking to keep meat tender.
Before serving, add sour cream.
Cook rice according to directions on box.
Serve Stroganoff over hot rice.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix and add to shredded cabbage. Let stand in refrigerator for 2 hours.

title: onion dill bread
directions: Heat onion, water, cottage cheese and margarine.
In a large mixing bowl, combine 2 cups flour, yeast, salt, sugar, baking soda, eggs and warm mixture.
Mix well.
Gradually add remaining flour, oats and dill weed.
Knead well.
Cover and let rise until doubled. Punch down and place in two 1 1/2-quart casseroles.
Brush tops with margarine.
Let rise again.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove from dishes and cool on rack.

title: chow-chow
directions: In a separate vessel put vinegar, sugar, mustard, mustard seed, celery seed and cloves.
Heat to boiling; add well-drained vegetables.
Cook slowly until tender (about 1/2 hour).
Put into sterile jars.
Process 10 minutes at simmering temperature.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion.
Add soups, cheese, seasoning and broccoli.
Pour over rice.
Bake 10 minutes at 350° until bubbly. May be stretched by adding more rice and broccoli.
May use green beans (French-cut) in place of broccoli.

title: st. paul's chili sauce
directions: In a large saucepan, lightly brown ground beef and then add all other ingredients.
Cook mixture for 10 minutes on medium setting, then turn heat to simmer and allow sauce to simmer for 15 minutes.

title: yankee cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese and add sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Pour mixture into spring form pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Turn oven off and leave door open about 2 inches.
Leave cake in oven for 30 more minutes.

title: lentil soup
directions: Rinse lentils.
Combine all ingredients in a medium pot. Bring to boil. Then simmer until tender for about 2 hours.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: easy corn casserole
directions: Beat egg.
Add corn, salt, pepper, sugar and flour.
Put in casserole.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: smearcase cheese cake
directions: Sift flour and baking powder together; add sugar, oil and eggs.
Mix well.
Press into bottom and sides of oblong pan.

title: peach or blueberry cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Mix 1/2 cup sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon in 2-quart saucepan. Stir in fruit and lemon juice. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils. Boil and stir 1 minute. Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole. Keep mixture hot in oven. Cut shortening into flour, 1 tablespoon sugar, baking powder and salt in medium bowl until mixture looks like fine crumbs. Stir in milk. Drop dough by 6 spoonfuls over hot fruit mixture. Bake 25 to 30 minutes until golden.

title: garlic roasted new potatoes
directions: Quarter new potatoes.
Toss in remaining ingredients.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Place nonstick or lightly greased pan in oven to preheat.
Place potatoes on sheet and bake about 30 minutes, turning several times to brown well.

title: world's best sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugars, butter, oil, eggs and vanilla in mixing bowl. Combine dry ingredients; flour, salt, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Mix well.
Roll into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press each cookie with a glass dipped in white sugar.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: caraway raisin bread
directions: Mix together in a large bowl.
Grease and flour 9-inch round pan.
Before baking, make a large cross and sprinkle with sugar and margarine.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake for 50 minutes.

title: french toast
directions: Makes about 20 slices.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add buttermilk, salt, lard, sugar and "enuff" flour as for bread but not stiff.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Beat egg slightly in small bowl.
Beat in 1 cup sugar, salt, vanilla, peanut butter and margarine.
Stir in remaining sugar. If necessary, add more powdered sugar to make enough to handle. Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Roll balls in peanuts and refrigerate.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: mexican layer dip
directions: Mix together and put in a dish.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Pour 1/2 batter into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, melt caramels, milk and margarine.
Pour over cooked cake.
Sprinkle with nuts and pour remaining batter on top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes. Cool and frost with coconut pecan frosting.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix until smooth and well blended.

title: grits casserole
directions: Bake in buttered dish.
Melt cheese and butter.
Mix all together.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°, covered, and for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: hamburger or pork chop casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
In buttered dish, put layer of sliced raw potatoes and sliced onions, half meat, salt and pepper.
Add a second layer.
Cover with mushroom soup.
Bake at 375°.
Cover up casserole.
When potatoes are done, uncover and brown.

title: best broccoli casserole
directions: Bring water and salt to a boil.
Add rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Melt butter in skillet.
Saute onion and celery until tender.

title: peanut pie
directions: Mix together crackers and peanuts. Fold cracker mixture into egg white mixture.
Put into ungreased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours before serving.
Top with whipped cream.

title: fudge icing
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water. Add milk, sugar, butter and salt.
Boil to soft ball stage (236°). Cool to room temperature. Add vanilla and beat until thick and creamy.
Spread on cake.

title: english pound cake
directions: Beat Crisco and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Beat well.
Add flour that is mixed with soda and salt alternately with buttermilk and juice.
Blend well.
Add beaten egg whites last.
Bake in 2 medium loaf pans in 350° oven for 1 hour or until pick comes out clean. Grease and flour pans well.

title: st. joseph's stew
directions: Cut meat into bite-sized pieces and brown in cooking oil. Combine remaining ingredients in casserole.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 hour; then bake at 325! for 2 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 6.

title: avocado salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water and cool.
Combine all other ingredients and add to dissolved jello.

title: pea-nut salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
You can serve the mixture inside tomatoes after scooping out the pulp.
Serves 4.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Optional:
Use spaghetti noodles instead of rice.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Peel zucchini and remove seeds.
Slice as for apple pie.
Cook in lemon juice until tender, about 10 minutes.
Don't overcook. Add sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Simmer for 2 to 3 minutes; cool. Add the 1/2 cup Crushed Mix to thicken.

title: date tarts
directions: Beat egg yolks until light.
Add sugar and blend thoroughly. Cut dates and chop nuts.
Combine flour and baking powder and sprinkle over dates.
Add along with nuts to egg mixture.
Fold in well beaten egg whites.
Add vanilla.
Bake in well-greased muffin tins (or paper baking cups).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream.
Yields 16 to 18 tarts.

title: pepper steak
directions: Sprinkle paprika over meat and brown in margarine.
Simmer with broth.
Add onions, pepper and celery.
Cook 5 minutes.
Mix cornstarch, water and soy sauce; stir into meat.
Cook until clear and thick; add tomatoes.
Serve over rice.

title: grandmother's pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan or two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
In a large bowl, beat butter until creamy; gradually add sugar and continue to beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift together flour and baking powder; add to butter and sugar, 1 cup at a time, beating after each addition.
Add milk as required, up to 1 cup. Blend in extract.
This batter will be thick; it cannot be poured. Spoon it into prepared pan and bake 1 hour or until a cake tester comes out clean.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and top with bacon and olives.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Melt the butter and saute the onions approximately 15 minutes. Add the Philadelphia cream cheese.
When melted, add the rest of the ingredients, stirring occasionally, for 10 minutes.

title: beef chimichangas
directions: In medium saucepan, bring beef, water, vinegar, garlic and seasonings to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer about 1 1/4 hours or until beef is tender.
Uncover; cook until liquid evaporates, about 30 minutes, stirring frequently.
Shred meat with 2 forks or let cool and pull apart with fingers.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar.
Add Dream Whip.
Put creamed mixture over the pretzel mix.
Chill.
Combine strawberry juice and bring to boil (must be 2 cups liquid, so add water if needed).
Add jello.
Add the fruit.
Cool.
Pour over top of chilled pretzel mix.
Chill and serve.

title: yummy sweet potatoes
directions: Mix together and pour into greased casserole.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Peel kiwi and bananas.
Divide in quarters and slice.
Cut cantaloupe and watermelon into small pieces.
Mix all together. Makes 6 servings.

title: four c. salad
directions: Poach chicken breasts.
Cut into bite sized pieces.
Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice, soy sauce and curry powder.
Add chicken and celery, chill.
Just before serving, add cashews and more dressing ingredients to suit taste and consistency.
Serve on lettuce.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate silk pie
directions: Sift (easy) dry ingredients into a 9-inch pie pan.
Combine oil and milk in a measuring cup.
Whip with a fork; pour oil at once over flour mixture.
Mix with fork until dampened.
Press evenly and firmly with fingers to line bottom of pan; then press dough up to line edges and partly cover rim.
Be sure dough is pressed to uniform thickness.
Bake in a hot 400° oven for 15 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the sugar, shortening and eggs. Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk. Add vanilla and cinnamon. Roll out to desired thickness. Cut into different shapes and decorate according to the occasion.
Bake at 375° about 10 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: watermelon mousse
directions: Place watermelon,
grenadine and lemon peel in blender. Blend on high
speed until smooth.
Pour into saucepan, sprinkle with gelatin.
Heat over low heat until gelatin dissolves. Refrigerate, stirring
occasionally,
until
mixture
mounds slightly when dropped
from
spoon.
Beat
egg white, cream of tartar and salt in
quart
bowl
until foamy.
Beat in sugar, 1 tablespoon at
a time, until stiff and glossy.
Fold in watermelon mixture. Beat
whipping
cream
in chilled bowl until stiff.
Fold
whipped cream
into
meringue mixture and spoon into dessert dishes. Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: beet pickles
directions: Cook and peel beets.
Put spices in a little bag and put the bag in the syrup of sugar, water and vinegar.
Bring this to a boil. Add beets and simmer 15 minutes.
Pack and seal.

title: pineapple and cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Combine and pour into greased mold; chill until firm.

title: sour cream-fudge cake with fudge frosting
directions: Mix cocoa, coffee and water; cool and stir in vanilla and sour cream.
Beat butter until smooth.
Sprinkle in sugar and beat 3 to 5 minutes.
Add eggs one at a time.
Whisk flour, soda and salt together.
Add flour mixture and cocoa mixture alternately.
Beat 15 seconds after all ingredients are combined.
Pour batter into 2 (9-inch) pans (prepared).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs well. Add sugar, salt and vanilla. Beat thoroughly. Add canned milk and milk.
Freeze in home freezer.
Makes approximately 1 gallon.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together until smooth.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake about 50 to 55 minutes at 350° (until a knife inserted in the middle comes out clean).

title: french salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Keeps well.

title: crumb pie shell
directions: In microwave, heat butter in pie plate until melted (High 1/2 minute).
Blend cookie crumbs and sugar into butter.
Press cookie crumb mixture firmly and evenly over pie plate.
Microwave on High 2 1/2 minutes until set.
Rotate pie plate after each minute.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients in heavy saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook until a soft ball is formed when a little of the mixture is dropped into cool water.
Takes from 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour on cake while warm.

title: stuffing by golly
directions: In a large frypan, melt butter. Slow fry chopped onion (don't burn). Add the raisins when onion is soft. Add the bread (small pieces, dampened but not soaked).
Add the celery. Add the small pieces of apple.
Mix all ingredients in frypan. Add pinch of salt, thyme and basil. Cover and warm over very low temperature for approximately 15 minutes.
Add the small pieces of sausage (degrease on paper towel first).
Add parsley.
Stuff into entree and cook as directed.
Warm is name of game.

title: lemon cups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put 1 teaspoon of dough in nonstick mini cupcake tins.
Form dough at bottom and around the inside of the tin.
Bake 9 to 13 minutes according to the package.
At around 5 to 7 minutes, use a teaspoon to push the dough down in the center of the cupcake.
This is important, otherwise, you will not be able to spoon in the lemon pie filling.
Let cool in pan for 20 to 30 minutes, then remove.
Makes 3 dozen.
Cupcake tins say bake at 325°, so that's what I do.

title: english matrimonials
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except the jam.
Place half of the mixture in greased 8 x 8-inch pan and press down evenly. Spread jam over bottom mixture and then add remaining mixture to top; press firmly.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let cool before cutting.

title: sour cream muffins
directions: Cream butter, stir in sour cream.
Gradually add the biscuit mix, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon into lightly greased miniature muffin pans, filing 2/3 full. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions and drain.
In a skillet brown ground beef.
Add to meat, 1/2 of the spaghetti sauce, tomato paste, garlic salt and oregano.
Simmer for 10 minutes.

title: freddie's pancake mix
directions: Add enough water to make it thin enough for pancakes.

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Combine soups; mix with milk.
Combine rice with most of soup mixture.
Place in greased baking dish.
Arrange chicken over rice.
Pour remaining soup over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered, then 15 minutes, uncovered.
Serves 6 or 8.

title: gazpacho
directions: Dice 2 tomatoes and 1/2 of a cucumber.	Cover and refrigerate until serving time.
In a blender or food processor, place 2 1/2 cups of ice water, 4 tomatoes, 1 1/2 cucumbers, green peppers, onion and garlic.
Run until finely chopped.
Add olive oil and mix well.
Pour into large bowl.
Add remaining 2 cups ice water.

title: chocolate cream cheese pie
directions: Combine first three ingredients in a mixing bowl. Beat at medium speed with electric mixer until soft and creamy. Add whipped topping, folding until smooth. Spread over crumb crust. Sprinkle with nuts. Serve immediately or store in refrigerator.

title: rice casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion.
Drain.
Add garlic salt, cream of mushroom soup, raw instant rice and Ro-Tel tomatoes. Cook for 5 or 10 minutes.
Top with shredded cheese and cook until cheese is melted.

title: apple carrot muffins
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients, except apples, carrots, raisins and nuts.
Beat 1 minute. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Put into lined cupcake pans. Bake about 20 minutes or until done.

title: pork chop-tomato casserole
directions: Brown chops in a small amount of oil in a skillet; remove from skillet and drain well on paper towels. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Saut rice and onion in skillet until rice is lightly browned. Stir in remaining ingredients and bring to a boil. Spoon rice mixture into a 2 1/2-quart casserole and place chops on top. Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour or until rice is tender. Yield: 6 servings.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease oblong 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients in order.
Spread in pan.
Bake for 25 minutes until golden brown.
Cut into small squares and serve warm.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Then mix last 5 ingredients and put on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top and bake 15 minutes more.

title: fannie may fudge
directions: Combine margarine, milk and sugar in large saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and let boil for 5 minutes.
Turn off heat.
Add marshmallows. Stir until discolored.
Add all 3 kinds of chocolate.
Stir after each addition, until chocolate melts.
Blend in vanilla.
Add nuts.

title: cheese pinwheels
directions: Mix flour, shortening and milk like making biscuits.
Roll out flat like pie crust.
Sprinkle cheese over dough.
Roll up jelly roll style.
Cut into pieces.

title: honey buns
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Stir in honey and sugar. Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly. Sprinkle with nuts.
Place biscuits evenly over honey mixture. Bake at 425° for 12 minutes. Turn upside down to serve.

title: horehound candy
directions: Pour boiling water over horehound.
Steep for 5 minutes.
Tea should be dark and bitter, but not black.
Strain.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight (approximately 12 hours).

title: fluffy marshmallow icing
directions: Combine sugar, water and cream of tartar in a saucepan.
Boil rapidly until syrup spins a 6-inch to 8-inch thread (242° on candy thermometer).

title: chunky chippers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease cookie sheets.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt onto wax paper.
Beat shortening, peanut butter, eggs, sugars, vanilla and water in bowl until creamy.
Add flour mixture; blend well.
Stir in chocolate chips.

title: goulash
directions: Cook hamburger meat until brown; drain.
Cook elbow noodles and drain.
Mix hamburger meat, noodles, tomato sauce, tomatoes and brown sugar.
Put in glass baking dish and top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: malted milk ball dessert
directions: Beat ice cream and Cool Whip together with mixer.
Add 2 cups crushed malted milk balls and stir.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan. Place 1 cup crushed malted milk balls on top.
Can put this in a graham cracker crust, if desired.

title: chili not-so-hot
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in a Dutch oven; drain any grease. Add remaining ingredients; heat thoroughly.
Serves 6.

title: roast pork and sauerkraut
directions: Sprinkle roast with salt and pepper.
Brown pork in large skillet with oil, then place in large cooker.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix ingredients.
Add water to make 1 gallon of punch.
If desired, make Kool-aid ice cubes and float in punch.

title: blueberry whipped cream pie
directions: Blend sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Stir in water; add 1 cup blueberries.
Place over heat and cook with gentle stirring until mixture boils and becomes thick and clear, 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and lemon juice.
Cool until lukewarm, then gently fold in remaining blueberries.
Cover and place in refrigerator until cold, but not set.
About one hour before serving, whip the cream until thick.
Sift in confectioners sugar and continue beating until stiff.
Spread over bottom of pie shell, leaving cream a little higher around edge.
Spread blueberry filling evenly over whipped cream.
Refrigerate.

title: cheese stradda
directions: Brown meat; drain well.
Cool.
Beat eggs and combine balance of ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set overnight in refrigerator.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana puddin'
directions: In a large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and water. Add pudding mix. Beat well. Chill 5 minutes. Fold in whipped topping. Spoon 1 cup pudding mixture into 2 1/2-quart glass serving bowl.
Top with 1/3 each of wafers, bananas and pudding. Repeat.
Chill.

title: combat dehydration
directions: Alternate above mixture with below mixture:

title: broccoli - corn
directions: In a bowl, combine the corn, broccoli, 12 cracker's crumbs, egg, margarine, onion and salt.
Turn into a 1 quart casserole. Combine remaining cracker crumbs and margarine.
Sprinkle on top of vegetable mixture.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Put aside and let stand.
Combine oleo, milk, sugar and cocoa.
Cook to boiling until sugar dissolves.
Add mixture with oatmeal.
Stir and put on waxed paper.

title: take along cheesecake squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine butter, graham cracker crumbs, flour and sugar, reserving 1/2 cup mixture.
Press remainder into an 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake 7 minutes.
Cool.

title: fruit balls
directions: Beat eggs lightly, then add sugar, oleo, flour, soda, vanilla, milk and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Chop dates, cherries, pineapple and pecans fine and mix with mixture.
Cook in greased party-size muffin tins at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes approximately 10 dozen.

title: raspberry fudge bars
directions: Use tablespoon of butter to coat 8 x 8-inch bake pan. Set aside 1 cup of chocolate chip for later use.
In double boiler, melt remaining chips and butter.
Add eggs, sugar and vanilla to chocolate mixture, beat until well combined.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Fold into chocolate mixture (batter will be thick.)
Stir in reserved chocolate chips; pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake at 300° for 60 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: bread pudding with pineapple
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in pineapple.
Line a square pan with 4 slices of bread.
Pour creamed mixture over bread and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: cranberry relish(uncooked)
directions: Mix chopped cranberries, sugar and cinnamon well.
Combine with pineapple, oranges and nuts.
Cover and place in refrigerator to blend.

title: bobbie's coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Beat in cream and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Mix one cup of sugar and 3 teaspoons of cinnamon well.
Put half of the batter in large tube pan. Sprinkle half of the sugar mixture over the batter, then knife through.
Repeat, using rest of the batter and mixture.
Bake in oven at 350° for a good hour.

title: fried chicken
directions: Split breasts so that they will be flat.
Put the flour and pepper into a bag and shake the chicken pieces until fully covered with flour.
Heat
butter,	but
just
moderately hot. Fry pieces without
crowding.	Do
not
cover.
It should take 3/4 hour to cook
a
3	pound
chicken.
Salt
at
the	table. Serves 4.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift flour and salt, cut in shortening, combine egg, vinegar and water.
Mix with fork and form into ball.
Chill before rolling out.

title: scrambled egg delight
directions: Mix all ingredients, pour in frying pan and cook over moderate heat, stirring until done.
Or cook in microwave for 2 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies in blender.
Mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar and margarine and set aside.
Mix pudding, milk and Cool Whip. Combine with cream cheese mixture.
Layer in long pan or can be layered in a flowerpot with gummy worms mixed in.
Serve with a small spade.

title: green tomato jam
directions: Add sugar to tomatoes.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Add raspberry gelatin; put in sterilized jars.
Cool and store in refrigerator.

title: soft cheese tacos
directions: Saute chilies in fat.
Add onions, garlic, sugar and tomatoes. Simmer for about 1 hour.
Just before serving, add evaporated milk and cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Dip tortillas in sauce; roll up and place in baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce over the top and serve.

title: mini cheese cakes
directions: Place 1 vanilla wafer in cupcake tin.
Mix cream cheese, vanilla and sugar on medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs. Mix well.
Pour over wafers, filling 3/4 full.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°.
Remove from pan when cool.
Chill.
Top with chocolate, nuts or fruit.
Makes 12.

title: orange punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid as directed on package.
Add pineapple with juice.
Add tangerine sections.
Stir and chill.

title: 24 carrot cake
directions: Mix together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, sugar, oil, eggs and baby food carrots.
Add coconut, chopped nuts and pineapple.
Put in two 9-inch pans or a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost as wanted or can leave it unfrosted.
Bake in a Bundt pan.

title: raspberry streusel squares
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a bowl.
Stir in both sugars. Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Stir in oat flakes. Press about 2/3 of mixture on bottom of a lightly greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Spread preserves over this.
Add almonds to remaining mixture and sprinkle over preserves.
Pat down.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden.
Cool.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in two loaf bread pans at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: walnut chicken
directions: Skin, halve lengthwise and bone chicken breasts.
Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces; set aside.

title: orange-pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve liquid.
To pineapple liquid, add water to equal 3 cups liquid.
Heat to boiling; dissolve jello in liquid.
Cool until slightly set.
Add pineapple and nuts; stir well.
Combine cream cheese (softened to room temperature) and whipped topping.
Add to gelatin mixture; stir until well blended and smooth.
Chill until set, at least 3 to 4 hours.
(I always make this up the night before and chill it overnight.)

title: sawdust pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Top with whipped cream and sliced bananas.

title: italian sausage and zucchini stir-fry
directions: Slice sausage in 1/4-inch slices.
Brown in wok or large skillet.
Add onions when sausage is nearly done.
Drain.
Add Tabasco sauce and oregano.
Cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove to serving plate; sprinkle with cheese.
Serve with crusty Italian bread.

title: noel chicken a la paris
directions: Split and skin chicken breasts.
Combine rest of ingredients and pour over chicken in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Serve with rice.

title: homemade cinnamon rolls
directions: Scald milk; stir in sugar, salt and butter so that the sugar is dissolved and the butter melts.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve the yeast in 1/4 cup of water and add to the milk mixture.
Add 1/2 of the flour and the egg and beat by hand until smooth.
Add the rest of the flour which makes a fairly stiff batter.
Cover tightly and cool for 3 hours.
Using 1/2 of the dough, knead it several times and roll to an oval shape.
Spread the top with softened butter (you choose amount) and sprinkle a mixture of cinnamon and sugar on top of the butter.
Roll up jelly roll style and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Place in a greased pan and allow to rise for an hour or so.
(At this point, they may be cooked or placed in the refrigerator until needed.)
Place rolls into a cold oven when ready to be baked.
Turn oven to 350° and cook until lightly browned (about 30 minutes).
Top with a simple powdered sugar icing.
Because this dough contains an egg, use the dough within 3 days.

title: extra crispy chicken
directions: In deep frying pan, add enough Crisco to about cover chicken. While grease is getting hot, salt and pepper chicken, roll in flour, dip completely in water and roll in flour again (cover good).
Place in frying pan and cook, covered, on medium to high heat, until golden brown.
(Be careful not to cook too quick, for chicken will not be done.)

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, flour, butter, vanilla and salt.
Blend in buttermilk.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for about 40 minutes or until brown.
Serve with your favorite preserves.

title: graham cracker pie crust
directions: Press into large pie dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: church casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; add tomato sauce, oregano, salt, pepper, onion and sour cream.
Layer noodles, cheese and meat.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs, oil, sugar and pumpkin.
Combine flour, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Gradually add to pumpkin mixture and mix well.
Pour into an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1 baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: swedish ginger cookies
directions: Cream the margarine; gradually add sugar.
Beat lightly until fluffy.
Add egg, molasses and water; mix well.
Combine flour, soda and spices; add to creamed mixture, mixing until blended.

title: valley fresh chicken salad
directions: Blend together mayonnaise, garlic, onion and mustard.
Shred chicken into very small pieces.
Combine all ingredients; cover and chill before serving.
Store in refrigerator.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: seasoned salt
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
This makes 32 ounces.
Use on roasts, steak, ribs, etc.
Can also be used in soups and stews. Put into aluminum shakers, tie ribbon for Christmas and share with neighbors.
Don't forget the recipe, they will be asking for it!

title: chocolate cookie sheet cake
directions: Sift flour; measure.
Re-sift with sugar and salt.
Place margarine, shortening, water and cocoa in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture.
Combine eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla in another bowl.
Add to mixture; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured shallow 11 x 17-inch pan. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Start frosting the last five minutes the cake is baking.

title: yellow frosting
directions: In large skillet, add the sugar and water.
Let come to a rolling boil.
Beat
the
egg
yolks
in a cup and finish filling
with
milk.
Pour
into
boiling
mixture,
stirring constantly (this is a must).
Turn on low heat and continue to stir constantly.
Add 1 stick oleo margarine and vanilla.
Add this
last.
When
a
drop is tested in cold water and you can pick it up, it is done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain very well.
Combine all ingredients (except cheese and crackers) including broccoli.
Mix well.
Pour into a buttered quart casserole dish.
Cover with cheese.
Sprinkle cheese cracker crumbs on top (or stuffing).
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
May refrigerate or freeze.
Add crumbs just before baking.
Easily doubled.
Enjoy!

title: frozen peppermint cheesecake
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Firmly press on bottom and 1-inch up sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Chill.

title: chicken ravioli
directions: Cook chicken in large pot.
Reserve liquid.
Remove chicken from bone and set aside.
Add onion, celery, noodles, salt and pepper to chicken broth.
Add additional water, if necessary. When noodles are done, add mushrooms, pimento and cheese.
May need to add more water, however consistency should be thick.
This will feed a crowd.

title: ambrosia mold
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve liquid.
Add cold water to liquid to make 1 cup.
Stir boiling water into jello; stir until dissolved. Stir in measured liquid.
Refrigerate until consistency of unbeaten egg whites (about 1 1/4 hours).
Stir in Cool Whip with wire whisk until smooth.
Refrigerate 10 minutes.
Stir in oranges, pineapple, coconut and marshmallows.
Spoon into mold and refrigerate.

title: meat puffs in mushroom sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients except the soup and cooked macaroni. Shape into balls that are not too compact. Sprinkle with flour and brown well in hot fat. Remove fat liquid if any. Mix 1/2 cup water with the mushroom soup and pour over meat puffs. Cover; simmer on low heat about 20 minutes. Add cooked macaroni the last 5 to 10 minutes. Serves 4.

title: never to be forgotten garlic loaf
directions: Cut bread in half lengthwise.
Tear out the soft center of bread in chunks, leaving crust intact.
Put bread shell on baking sheet covered in foil.
Melt butter in a large skillet.
Stir in garlic and sesame seed.
Add bread chunks and cook until golden brown.
Remove from heat.
Combine sour cream, Jack cheese, Parmesan, parsley and lemon pepper.
Stir in artichoke hearts and spoon into bread shells.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: decadent triple layer mud pie
directions: In a mixing bowl combine chocolate and condensed milk; refrigerate for 10 minutes.
In a large mixing bowl mix milk and pudding mixes; whisk two minutes or until smooth.
Pour 1 1/2 cup of pudding into crust.
Immediately, stir in 1/2 of the whipped topping into remaining pudding and pour on next; top with remaining whipped topping and nuts.
Refrigerate for 3 hours until set; garnish as desired.

title: cameo cake
directions: Combine butter and water in a medium saucepan; bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add white chocolate, stirring until melts.
Stir in buttermilk, eggs and vanilla; set aside.
Combine 1/2 cup flour and pecans, stirring to coat; set aside.
Combine remaining 3 cups flour, sugar and soda in a large mixing bowl; gradually stir in white chocolate mixture. Fold in pecan mixture.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans on wire racks 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and let cool completely on wire racks.
Spread White Chocolate-Cream Cheese Frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake.
Store in refrigerator.
Garnish if desired.
Yields 1 (3 layered) cake.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: In a saucepan, cook sausage, onion and green pepper over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain. Stir in 2 tablespoons of flour, basil and fennel. Mix well. Add tomato sauce. Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes. Transfer to an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Place the remaining flour in a mixing bowl. Beat in the eggs, milk, oil and salt until smooth. Stir in Parmesan cheese, if desired. Pour over casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes or until browned. Serves 8.

title: liver dumplings
directions: Mix liver, eggs, bread crumbs and flour.
Saute onions in butter; add onions to mixture.
Roll liver balls in flour.
Cook in hot chicken broth for 20 minutes with lid off.
Add egg noodles when dumplings are just about boiling in broth.
Do not drain broth.

title: sweet potato pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, salt, spices, eggs and vanilla.
Blend thoroughly.
Melt butter in hot milk.
Stir into mixture.
Stir in pecans.
Put into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Garnish with pecan halves.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes longer.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: crispy oven-fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Line a shallow pan with foil, or grease it lightly with spray.
In a plastic bag, mix potato flakes, cheese, parsley, onion powder, paprika and ground pepper.
Moisten chicken parts with water, milk or margarine.
(For a low-fat meal, remove skin from chicken before moistening.)
Shake each piece in the plastic bag until well coated.
Place chicken pieces in pan.
Bake for 60 to 75 minutes until chicken is tender and golden brown. (Boneless and/or skinless pieces will take less time.)

title: tartar sauce
directions: Makes 1 gallon of sauce, but can be cut down.

title: catskinner cake
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in a large mixing bowl; beat at medium speed 5 minutes. Stir in pineapple and nuts. Pour batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Set pan on wire rack.

title: grandma negus' ground beef patties
directions: In a medium sized dish break in eggs; whip with fork.
Add milk, crushed crackers, onion, salt and pepper. Let stand five minutes to soften crackers.
Knead in ground beef and make into patties.
Fry in skillet until brown.

title: apple crisp 1
directions: Generously grease a 2 to 3-quart casserole.
Add the apple slices and sprinkle with lemon juice and 1/2 cup sugar.
In a bowl, mix flour and remaining sugar.
Cut in margarine and cheese with a pastry blender.
Sprinkle over apples and press very lightly with fingers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until apples are tender and top is lightly browned.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on the box. Remember to use milk instead of water.
After mixing cake, add rest of ingredients.
Bake according to box directions.

title: cheesy calzone
directions: Optional Fillings:
Onions, mushrooms, chopped spinach, green peppers, green or black olives, ground beef, sausage, Canadian bacon and pepperoni.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions on box.
Add black walnut flavoring.

title: potatoes, tomatoes and basil salad
directions: Scrub potatoes; cook until tender (about 18 minutes).
Wash and trim tomatoes; cut into bite size.
Place in serving bowl and cut in basil.
Add vinegar.
When potatoes are cool, cut into halves or quarters; add to bowl.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Enjoy!

title: potato casserole
directions: Stir all ingredients into a 9 x 13-inch casserole baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: old-fashioned cocoa
directions: Mix together and heat on stove until hot.
Makes 2 cups.

title: pecan butter balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add flour, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add chopped nuts.
Form in small balls.
Bake on greased sheet at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
While hot, roll in powdered sugar; cool and roll again in powdered sugar when ready to store. They freeze well.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple. Do NOT drain pineapple. Add other ingredients, one at a time. Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken, reserving one cup chicken broth.
Set aside.
In a saucepan, combine onion, garlic, cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup and chicken broth.
Heat through, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add sour cream.

title: chocolate cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven
to
Reserve
cup
dry cake mix. Combine remaining
mix with 1 egg and add oil (mixture will be thick and
crumbly).
Press
into
a
x
9-inch pan. Blend softened cheese and sugar.	Add 3 eggs and remaining cake mix. Beat 1
minute
at medium speed.
Lower speed and add milk and vanilla and
mix
until smooth.
Pour onto crust. Bake at 300° for 55	to
65	minutes or until center is firm.
Cool. Spread with whipped
topping
and
garnish
with shredded chocolate. Chill.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients with this mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans. Drop by large tablespoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: strawberry shake
directions: Combine strawberries with milk and sugar in blender container. Cover and blend thoroughly.
Add ice cream and blend a few seconds.

title: dorothy's salsa
directions: Peel tomatoes and cut into chunks.
Cook tomatoes, peppers, onion and garlic until desired consistency.
Add sugar, vinegar and salt.
Pour into sterilized pint jars.
Seal.
Hot water bath for 15 minutes.
Yields 14 pints.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cut up chicken into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients.
Line bottom of pie plate with crust.
Pour mixed ingredients into crust and top with grated cheese.
Top with crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: herb chicken and broccoli
directions: Thaw, drain and cut broccoli spears into bite-size pieces and set aside.
Slice breasts into 1/2-inch strips.
Sprinkle with Italian seasoning and pound between sheets of plastic wrap.
Spray skillet with no-stick cooking spray and saute chicken until no longer pink.
Keep warm.

title: parmesan twists
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease baking sheet.
Roll bread dough into rectangle.
Trim edges.
Brush with butter.
Sprinkle cheese and paprika.
Cut into long strips.
Place on baking sheet.
Twist each strip several times.
Bake 12 minutes.
Contains 97 calories and 2 grams fat.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Tear bread into small pieces and sprinkle over butter, then crumble sausage over bread.
Divide cheese evenly over bread and pour eggs over all.
Season and cover.
Chill overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: banana pudding(u. s. a.)
directions: Mix egg yolks, sugar and flour slow.
Stir in 1 tablespoon water.
Add milk; cook until it begins to get thick.
Set off stove and mix in vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
In a casserole, put layer of vanilla wafers, layer of sliced bananas and some of the pudding.
Repeat until pudding is used up (usually takes about 3 bananas).
Put beaten egg whites on top of pudding.
Brown under broiler.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Mix sugar, butter, egg and vanilla.
Then add flour mixture to sugar mixture. Blend well.
Roll into balls, then roll balls into sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Then place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Remove bones and skin (save broth for soup).
Grease baking dish (9 x 13-inch) and place defrosted broccoli on bottom.
Place chicken on top of broccoli.
Mix soup, mayo and curry powder together.
Spoon over top of chicken. Sprinkle with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Sprinkle then with cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 370°, covered, then uncovered for 15 minutes.

title: salt ceramic clay
directions: Heat and mix well.
In about 2 to 3 minutes the mixture will be like bread dough.
Place on wax paper to cool, then knead for several minutes.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Prepare brownie mix and bake according to package directions in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Prick top of warm brownies at 1-inch intervals using a fork; drizzle with Kahlua.
Let cool and crumble. Prepare pudding mix according to package directions, omitting chilling.
Place 1/2 of crumbled brownies in bottom of a 2-quart trifle dish.
Top with 1/2 each of pudding, whipped topping and crushed toffee bits.
Repeat layers with remaining ingredients, ending with toffee bits.
Chill 8 hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar together.
Add to other ingredients and let stand for 2 hours.
Refrigerate.
Keeps for several days.

title: easy and light pineapple cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: refrigerator biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; set aside.
Mix flour, sugar and soda; cut in Crisco, then add buttermilk and yeast.
Roll out dough; cut out biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: beefy baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper.
Drain.
Pour into large mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients except bacon.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with bacon.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: baked chili rellanos
directions: Saute onion and tortillas in oil for 8 minutes, stirring frequently.
Place in 8 x 8 inch casserole dish and sprinkle with one cup shredded cheese.
Drain, rinse, seed and slice open chilies.
Sprinkle cilantro over cheese layer and top with one layer of chilies.
Place a layer of thinly sliced cheese on chilies and then the second layer of chilies.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Crush the gingersnaps and make like graham cracker crust.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix the ice cream, pumpkin, sugar, salt and pumpkin pie spice and pour over top of crust. Refrigerate until served.

title: cream of asparagus soup
directions: Cook the asparagus in a large skillet of boiling, salted water until tender-crisp (about 7 to 12 minutes).
Drain.
Remove and reserve the asparagus tips (about 1-inch).
Chop the asparagus stalks.
Saute the onion in the butter until transparent and mix in the chopped asparagus talks.
Add the flour and stir gently. Gradually pour in the chicken stock.
Add the salt, pepper, nutmeg and cayenne pepper and simmer for 30 minutes.
Puree the soup in a blender, adding the cream.
Serve hot.
Garnish with the asparagus tips.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze in 8 x 8-inch glass dish.

title: beef-vegetable soup
directions: Combine soup bones and water in a large Dutch oven; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour.
Add beef cubes, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Add cubed potatoes, carrots, onions, tomato sauce and cabbage; cover and simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Makes about 4 1/2 quarts.

title: shish kabob marinade
directions: Combine ingredients and marinate steak or chicken at least 4 hours.

title: mom's ham loaf(light and yummy)
directions: Grind the pork and ham together 2 times.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, place the next 6 ingredients and mix.
Allow to stand at least 5 minutes.
Set oven for 400°.

title: baked omelet
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
In large bowl, cover potato slices with 3 cups very hot water; let stand while preparing sausage.
In medium skillet, cook sausage and onion until crumbly and loses pink color; drain.
Drain potato slices; add to sausage mix with green pepper and mushrooms, stirring until well combined.
Spoon into prepared dish.
In same bowl, combine contents of seasoning mix that came from au gratin potatoes and 1/2 cup hot water; blend well.
Beat milk and eggs. Pour evenly over mixture in dish.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Makes 8 servings.

title: brown sugar fudge
directions: Bring white sugar, evaporated milk, brown sugar, margarine and butter to a boil.
Boil to form a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat, then add Marshmallow Fluff and vanilla.
Stir until Fluff is all melted in.
Put in cold water and stir to cool.
Add your favorite nuts.
Pour in buttered pan (long cookie sheet).

title: angel fruit cake
directions: Melt ice cream.
Crumb cake into bowl; add strawberries.
Mix well and pour into tube pan and freeze.
Slice into serving pieces when ready to serve.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix the last 7 ingredients into casserole dish, then dump in the carrots and bell pepper.
Put in just a couple of onion rings to give it just a little flavor.
Cover; let set overnight in the refrigerator so that the flavors will mingle.
Enjoy.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Fry onions and pepper in small amount of oil; remove from pan. Fry chicken or pork cubes 5 to 7 minutes, then add cornstarch, vinegar, ketchup, brown sugar and pineapple juice.
Mix this until thickens.
Throw pineapple, onion and pepper in.
Heat through. Serve over rice.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add flour and mix well.
Form balls and put on greased pans.
Flatten balls with a fork dipped in flour.
Bake at 315° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: diamond applesauce squares
directions: Grease a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg. Beat.
Add applesauce, rind and vanilla.

title: huckleberry-nutmeg sauce
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and nutmeg. Stir into water in a saucepan and cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly until thick and bubbly. Stir in huckleberries and sherry. Bring to boil again. Take off heat and cool slightly. Serve over pancakes or waffles. Yummy!

title: grandma's scratch cake
directions: Grease and flour pans, set aside.
Mix with a beater the first 8 ingredients.
Add the hot coffee and vanilla (mix on low).
Pour into pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool and frost with frosting.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions.
Mix all ingredients and chill.
Can also add broccoli, cooked chicken, shrimp and/or asparagus.
Blanch vegetables like broccoli and asparagus.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased 2-quart baking dish.

title: meatball soup
directions: Shape beef into tiny meatballs. Brown meatballs and onions in a large saucepan or in shallow pan in 400° oven.
Drain off excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients. Bring to boiling. Simmer 1 1/2 hours or until vegetables are tender.
Yields 8 servings.

title: shrimp creole casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: beef pot roast
directions: Put vegetables in bottom of crock-pot.
Salt and pepper meat. Add liquid.
Cover.
Cook on low 10 to 12 hours.
Remove meat and vegetables and thicken gravy.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Cook onion in small bowl in microwave until slightly tender. Also, heat cream cheese and milk in microwave slowly.
Add other ingredients and stir well.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Cut up very small.
Cut up celery. Cut up apples.
For dressing, use equal amounts of mayonnaise and sour cream.
Refrigerate; use for sandwiches or serve on lettuce leaves.

title: banana bread deluxe
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs, beating well.
Add dry ingredients alternating with buttermilk and banana.
Add nuts. Bake in large greased loaf pan at 350° at least 60 minutes.

title: easy fondant
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, heat margarine, syrup and 1/2 pound sugar over low heat until bubbly.
Stir in remaining 1/2 pound sugar.
Remove from heat.
Stir until mixture holds shape.
Turn into a greased pan.
Cool until warm.
Knead until smooth.
Add flavoring and coloring.
Shape into balls with lightly greased hands.
Makes 1 1/3 pounds.

title: chicken waikiki beach
directions: Wash chicken; pat dry and coat with flour.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Add chicken and brown on all sides.
Remove to shallow roasting pan, skin side up and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain pineapple and put syrup in 2-cup measuring cup.
Add water to make 1/4 cup.
In 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, pineapple syrup, vinegar, soy sauce, ginger and bouillon.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 2 minutes.
Pour over chicken.
Bake uncovered for 30 minutes.
Add pineapple slices and pepper.
Cut crosswise in 1/4-inch circles. Bake 30 more minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: creamed corn
directions: In a heavy iron skillet, heat the bacon drippings and add the corn.
Stir on high to fry about 2 minutes.
Turn heat to low and add enough milk just to come to the top of the corn.
Add sugar, salt and pepper and stir well.
Let simmer about 30 minutes until corn is cooked.
Mix a little cornstarch with 2 tablespoons cold water and stir to dissolve.
Pour into corn to thicken the milk, stirring as you add the cornstarch mixture.
Check for salt and pepper.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: In large bowl stir together mix and spices.
Add water, potatoes, egg and oil.
Stir just until moist.
Use five 4 1/2 x 2 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch loaf pans or 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: spectacular squash
directions: Combine stuffing mix with melted butter and press half of it into 9 x 13-inch or 3 quart casserole dish.
Lightly steam squash and onion until barely cooked.
Drain thoroughly.

title: brown rice and black beans
directions: Saute oil and onion in large pan or skillet.
Add tomatoes, beans, oregano and garlic.
Bring to boil and stir in rice.
Return to boil, then turn to simmer and cover for at least 5 minutes. Take off heat and let stand for a few minutes.
(I usually simmer longer and let stand longer.)

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and sorghum and beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix well.
Add hot water and mix.
Pour into a greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, melted oleo, salt, Karo syrup and peanut butter.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° until pie bubbles, then turn to 250° for 45 minutes after pouring into unbaked pie shell.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Make crust out of cake mix, egg and margarine.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan (greased).
Prepare powdered sugar, eggs, cream cheese and vanilla; beat with mixer.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until brown on top.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Toss pecan halves in oil and sauce.
Roast in shallow baking pan at 275° for 30 minutes, stirring often.
Drain on paper towel. Sprinkle with salt.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: To prepare crust:
Mix first 3 ingredients and press into pan (preferably spring-form pan).

title: chewy bread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Beat well.
Fold in coconut or chocolate chips.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.
Cut while warm.
Leave in pan to cool.

title: no stir cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan (8 x 8-inches).
Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Gradually add milk to flour mixture, stirring until fairly smooth. Don't worry about small lumps.
Spoon batter as evenly as possible over melted butter.
Do not stir. Take peach slices from can and place them evenly on batter. Drizzle peach syrup over the top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve warm topped with Dream Whip.

title: silly putty
directions: Mix glue and starch.
Allow to dry slightly until workable. Use on smooth dry surface.
Store in airtight container.
Yields 1/2 cup.
Preparation Time:
10 minutes.

title: cranberry juice punch
directions: Combine cranberry juice, apple juice and lemonade which has been diluted according to directions on can.
Chill.
Add the soft drink just before serving.

title: marinated broccoli
directions: Trim broccoli (reserving stems for another use), separate into bite-sized pieces and wash thoroughly.
Drain broccoli and put in large, shallow container.
Set aside.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together first three ingredients.
Add eggs, beating well after each one.
Alternate flour, salt, baking powder, flavoring and whole milk.
Bake in a tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: mystery pie
directions: Drain pineapple; mix milk and lemon juice.
Fold in pineapple, pecans and Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust and freeze.

title: butter chewies
directions: Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Add onion, green pepper and mushrooms to bacon fat and cook until tender.
Stir in flour, chicken broth, cream and pimento.
Simmer until thickened.
Add salt and pepper. Combine sauce, chicken, bacon and cooked spaghetti.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: sweet & sour meatballs
directions: Form meatballs.
Pour the sauce over the meatballs and bake at 350 degrees for one hour.

title: strawberry freezer jam
directions: Wash, stem and crush fruit thoroughly. Place in 4-quart kettle. Gradually stir sugar into fruit and let stand 10 minutes.

title: chinese barbecue pork
directions: Mix all ingredients except pork in pan.
Stir over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Cut pork into 1 x 1 1/2-inch strips, cutting with the grain of meat.
Score strips; marinate in soy sauce mixture 4 hours or overnight.
Line pan with foil; place meat on rack in pan and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Baste with marinade; cook 20 minutes and baste again.
Bake 10 minutes longer. Serve hot or cold with hot mustard.

title: creative dough(as close to the brand name as i've ever found.)
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium saucepan and cook over medium heat 4 or 5 minutes, stirring constantly until mixture forms a ball.
Remove dough from saucepan and let cool 5 minutes.
Knead dough about 1 minute, until well blended.
Cool completely.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: lime pineapple pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool completely, then mix the next 3 ingredients and spread over cooled crust.
Next, dissolve jello with water; add pineapple (drained), then add 7-Up or Sprite. Refrigerate jello mixture until partially set, then pour it over cream cheese layer.

title: tomato cake
directions: Puree tomatoes. Cream sugar and butter until fluffy. Add eggs, tomatoes and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Sift dry ingredients. Add to mixture.
Put in greased loaf pan or 8 x 8-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: coleslaw surprise
directions: Combine oil, vinegar and Ramen chicken flavoring.
Shake well and pour over sliced cabbage.
Add sesame seed and sliced almonds plus Ramen noodles.
Pepper and salt to taste.

title: pumpkin pie or sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 2 pie shells and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until well done.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Boil one can of sweetened condensed milk in a boiler of water, unopened, for 3 hours; let cool down.
Pour into graham cracker crust and top with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: amaretto cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Then gradually beat in sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, until stiff and glossy.
Add salt.
Gradually beat in Amaretto.
Fold in coconut and almonds.
Line cookie sheets with foil.
Drop mixture by heaping teaspoonfuls onto foil.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Cool cookies on foil.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: baked tomatoes
