directions: Mix all together.
Put in a buttered dish.
Bake at 300° to 325° for approximately 45 minutes.
This can be sliced into squares.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice apples into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Add cinnamon and water.
Work together flour, sugar and butter until mixture is fine lumps.
Spread mixture over apples.
Bake, uncovered, about 30 minutes or until brown on top and bubbly.

title: chili chicken
directions: In frypan, cook onion until tender.
Add soup, milk, pimentos and chili powder.
Cook to boil.
In large pan, layer cooked noodles, deboned chicken, soup mixture and cheese.
Repeat layers if needed.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: creamy vegetable salad
directions: Break cauliflower into small pieces.
Cut broccoli into small pieces.
Cut carrots into bite sized pieces.
Mix sour cream with mayonnaise and dressing mix.
Blend and mix with raw vegetables.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together the butter and honey. Beat in egg, vanilla and pumpkin.
Sift together, then add to the creamed mixture, the flour, baking powder, nutmeg, soda and cinnamon.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes.
When cookies come out of the oven, make faces on them with raisins.

title: diabetic jello
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Heat fruit juice to boiling. Add gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Add fructose.
Stir until dissolved.
Add 1 cup Fruit-Fresh or unsweetened canned fruit except fresh pineapple.
Gelatin will not jell with fresh pineapple.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place wings in single layer in a shallow baking dish. Season wings with salt, pepper and garlic powder. Bake for 15 minutes.

title: apple bars
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients as for pie crust.
Add egg yolk mixture to flour mixture.
Blend and divide in 2 parts.
Roll each to fit a jelly roll pan.
Put one on bottom and sprinkle dough with crushed cornflakes.
Peel and slice apples; sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Mix into apples and spread on top of cornflake crumbs.
Cover with remaining dough and seal edges. Beat egg whites slightly; brush on top crust.
Sprinkle lightly with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lizzies
directions: Sift flour.
Mix eggs, sugar, syrup, spices, coconut, flour, soda and whiskey.
Then add fruits and nuts.
Batter will be runny.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and cook at 250° for 25 minutes (put a pan of water under cookie sheet).
Let sit on sheet a few minutes; do not pile up.
(Drop 1 teaspoon for each cookie.)

title: basic lemon pie crust
directions: Mix flour, sugar and lemon rind.
Cut in butter and shortening.
Add enough vinegar to hold pastry together.
Chill until ready to use.

title: cranberry chicken shari
directions: In a saucepan, soften gelatin in water.
Place over low heat and stir until dissolved.
Add cranberry sauce, pineapple, nuts and lemon juice; mix well.
Pour in an 8-inch square baking dish and refrigerate until almost firm.
Pour chicken layer over top and refrigerate until firm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Cut cake in half.
Break both halves into bite size pieces; place 1/2 in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour pie filling over cake pieces.
Place other 1/2 of cake pieces over pie filling. Prepare vanilla pudding using the milk.
Add sour cream and mix. Pour mixture over cake.
Top with nondairy whipped topping; refrigerate.
Yields 9 to 12 servings.
May be topped with chopped pecans.

title: holy cow cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Immediately, when removed from oven, punch holes in cake with a wooden spoon.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over cake.
Let cake cool completely.
Then top with caramel and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: rice surprise
directions: Layer in casserole dish.
Add shredded cheese on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Beat cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla. Fold in Cool Whip until thoroughly blended.
Spoon into crust and chill about 4 hours or until set. Place thin slices of berries all over top.
Now ready to serve. Serves 6.

title: icebox hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water with the egg whites, slightly beaten.
Mix together the sugar, salt and 1 cup flour. Mix stick of margarine with other cup of water.
Melt over low heat; let cool.
Add all liquids except egg whites; mix for 2 minutes.
Add 2 cups flour; mix together.
Add egg whites. Cover; let rise until double in size.
Work in 1 1/2 cups flour. Work until you can handle it.
Divide into balls.
Put in muffin tins.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Brown meat, drain, add onions and cook for a few minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese and tortillas.
Cook slowly for 10 minutes or less. Cut up tortillas into pieces and layer in a 9 x 13 x 3-inch casserole.
On top of tortillas place half of the meat and repeat.
Top with grated cheese and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until bubbly and cheese melts.
Good served with green salad.

title: copper carrots
directions: Slice carrots and cook.
Dice onion and green pepper.
Add to cooked carrots.
In saucepan, heat the remaining ingredients until blended.
Cool sauce slightly; pour over carrots and mix.
Let stand overnight.
Serve chilled.

title: ham loaf
directions: Blend all ingredients thoroughly.
Place mixture in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan lined with heavy waxed paper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients into casserole dish.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil.
Mix cinnamon and flour.
Add zucchini, vanilla and nuts to the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp de jonghe
directions: Melt 3/4 cup butter in a deep, 2-quart casserole dish on Full power for 1 minute.
Add sliced garlic and heat, uncovered, on Full power for 2 1/2 minutes or until garlic is browned.
Remove garlic slices from melted butter.
Add tarragon, parsley, nutmeg, thyme, chives, onion, salt and sherry to butter.
Stir to combine.
Remove 1/4 cup of seasoned butter mixture and mix with 3/4 cup bread crumbs.
Place raw shrimp in a shallow 2-quart casserole dish with remaining butter.
Stir to coat raw shrimp with seasoned butter. Sprinkle buttered bread crumbs over shrimp.
Heat, uncovered, on Full power for 10 minutes or until crumbs are browned and shrimp are pink.
Do not overcook shrimp.

title: one dish chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until well done.
Remove all skin and bones. Cut the chicken into bite-size pieces and set aside.
Heat peas. Re-warm cooked carrots and set aside.
Cook elbow macaroni. Remove from heat and drain water.

title: turkey amandine
directions: Moisten stuffing mix with 2 cups water.
Press into bottom and sides of buttered, shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Bake in hot oven at 400°
for 10 minutes.
Saute onion and celery in butter in large saucepan.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually add 2/3 cup water and evaporated milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture just comes to a boil and thickens.
Remove from heat.
Stir in turkey and green beans. Spoon onto stuffing crust.
Sprinkle almonds over top.
Bake in moderate oven at 350°
for 25 to 35 minutes or until heated through.

title: georgia peaches and cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, blend ingredients.
Beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Grease and dust with two 9-inch cake pans with flour.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool layers.
Slice into four layers.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook hamburger; drain the fat.
Add green beans and soup; let simmer.
Make the Potato Buds according to the package directions. Put the hamburger mixture in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Spoon the mashed potatoes on top of hamburger mixture; sprinkle with cheese or chow mein noodles.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Mix together all ingredients; save some onions for top.
Put in casserole dish.
Cook for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut up the cabbage into small pieces and boil until tender. Fry hamburger, onions and bell pepper together until done.
Place layers of cabbage and meat mixture in casserole dish.
Then pour canned tomatoes and tomato juice over the top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: party mix
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Melt margarine in a large shallow baking dish.
Mix in Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt.
Add cereals, peanuts and pretzels and mix thoroughly.
Bake in oven for one hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool and store in airtight container.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook 4 hours on high. Season to taste.

title: wait cake
directions: Bake cake mix in 2 layers and split the 2 layers or bake in 4 pans.
Mix sour cream, sugar and coconut.
Save 1 cup mix and chill.
Spread the remaining mix thick between the layers.
Mix the 1 cup saved with Cool Whip.
Spread this on top and sides of cake using all.
It will be thick.
Store in airtight container and put in icebox (will stay fresh for 3 months or put in freezer).

title: frozen fruit cup
directions: Mix sugar and water in saucepan; bring to boil and allow to cool.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Warm flour in 150° oven (about 20 minutes).
In meantime, grease 2 bread pans.
Dissolve honey, molasses and yeast in 2 cups of water.
Make a hole in flour.
Add salt and pour in yeast mixture.
Stir and add more warm water until dough is elastic. Divide into 2 bread pans and let rise (about 1 hour).
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Let cool in pan for 20 minutes before removing.

title: marinated corn
directions: Heat sugar, oil and vinegar in saucepan to boiling point or dissolved.
Stir all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Will keep 1 or 2 weeks.

title: saucy little meat loaves(from the files of louella scott williams)
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into 6 individual meat loaves in shallow baking pan.
Combine last 3 ingredients and spread over top of each loaf.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
For a large loaf, pack into an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Spread with topping and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Coat a 3 quart glass casserole dish with Pam.
Drain about 1/2 the juice off the peaches.
Pour peaches and remaining juice into casserole dish.
Mix sugar, flour and egg until crumbly.
Mixture will be kind of dry.
Sprinkle cinnamon over peaches.
Sprinkle dry mixture over peaches evenly.
Pour melted margarine evenly over top.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 45 minutes-1 hour or until golden brown.
(Also works well with canned pears.)

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Spread 1/2 of the pimento, 1/2 of the asparagus (cut up), 1/2 of the boiled eggs (cut up), 1 can of soup and small slices of cheese on bottom of casserole dish (11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch is a good size).
Spread remainder of pimento, asparagus, eggs, more slices of cheese and the second can of soup.
Cover the top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: white bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast over 1/2 cup warm milk or water.
Add rest of lukewarm liquid, salt and sugar.
Mix well.
Add all of flour. When partially mixed, add melted shortening.
Mix well with hands. Keep sides of bowl clean.
Turn out on lightly floured board; knead until smooth and bubbly.
Cover; let stand until double in size in warm place.
Knead down; divide dough for loaves, if desired.
Place in well-greased pans; let rise until double.
Bake at 400° for the first 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°; bake until well browned and shrunk from sides of pan.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Layer all ingredients as listed in crock-pot.
Do not stir until done.
Cook on high for 2 hours.

title: hot garlic dill pickles
directions: Will also need quart jars.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a casserole dish.
Cook 50 minutes at 350° or microwave 20 minutes on High.

title: blondies (white brownies)
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients in order given, mixing well after each addition.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 or 35 minutes at 350°.
Take from oven while still soft. Cut into squares.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen (2-inch) squares.

title: pie pastry
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and baking powder in a big bowl.
In a bowl, put eggs, water and vinegar; beat.
Set aside.
Gently crumble lard into flour mixture.
Sprinkle water mixture on, 1 tablespoon at a time, tossing mixture lightly and stirring with a fork.
Add water each time to the driest part of mixture.
The dough should be just moist enough to hold together when pressed gently with a fork.
It should not be sticky.

title: parmesan potato crisps
directions: Scrub potatoes; thinly slice (you should have 2 cups sliced potatoes).
Arrange potatoes in a thin layer in a lightly greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Brush with melted margarine. Sprinkle cheese and pepper or seasoned salt over potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, in a 450° oven for 18 to 20 minutes or until potatoes are brown and crisp.
Serves 4.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Stir dry ingredients together. Stir in eggs and oil. Add all other ingredients.
Stir until mixed. Do not beat.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Cool in pan.

title: sam's hearty beef casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni according to package directions and drain.
Brown hamburger; drain off grease.
Add tomato sauce.
Remove from heat.
Combine in a bowl the cheeses, sour cream, onions and green peppers.
Spread half the macaroni shells into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with all the cheese mixture.
Add remaining macaroni shells.
Pour beef-tomato mixture on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: bella pasta(this dish can be low-fat and addictive!)
directions: Cook macaroni.
Combine egg, milk and Parmesan cheese.
Stir into macaroni.
Spray a 12-inch pizza pan with nonstick spray. Spread macaroni mixture evenly in pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken-rice magnifique
directions: In skillet, brown chicken in butter after liberally seasoning them with salt and pepper.
Remove and set aside.
In same skillet cook carrots, onions and parsley until tender, stirring frequently. Add raw rice and stir until well mixed; add chicken broth, salt, pepper and Tabasco.
Pour mixture into greased oblong casserole and top with chicken.
Sprinkle with additional salt and pepper if needed and place bacon on top of chicken.
Cover and cook at 325° for 1 1/4 hours or until chicken is tender.
Remove bacon slices before serving.
Delicious main dish!!

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Good with cauliflower, radishes, celery and carrots.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix together in a saucepan.
Fill a cake pan with popped corn. Preheat oven to 250°.
Pour caramel mix over popped corn.
Put in oven for 1 hour; stir every 15 minutes.
Then eat.

title: pear nut bread
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until light and creamy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Stir in mashed pears.
Sift flour, soda and salt and add to creamed mixture with sour milk. Fold in nuts.
Put into 1 large 9 x 5-inch pan or 2 smaller pans.
Cook at 350° for about 55 minutes.
Use fresh pears and double this recipe.
Put in 3 bread-size pans about 3 inches high.

title: vicki lawrence's low-fat vegetable soup
directions: Spray a 5-quart Dutch oven with nonstick cooking spray (Pam). Add chicken, celery, carrots, potato and onion; cook and stir over medium heat for 6 to 8 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink. Add all remaining ingredients, except macaroni.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium.
Simmer, uncovered, for 12 to 18 minutes or until vegetables are tender, adding macaroni during last 8 minutes of cooking.
Remove bay leaves; serve immediately.
Makes 10 (1 1/2 cup) servings.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in margarine.
Cook rice according to package directions.
Mix all ingredients.
Put in 2 quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cobbler
directions: Soften butter.
Mix flour, sugar, milk and softened butter together.
Pour fruit filling in the bottom of baking pan (square). Pour flour mixture on top of filling and bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until top of crust is brown.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken.
When cooked, remove to cool.
Add soups to broth and bring to boil.
Stir in sour cream.
Dip tortillas in hot broth.
Fill with chicken, grated cheese, onion and peppers.
Roll and place on shallow pan sprayed with Pam.
Use toothpick to hold in place.
Pour sauce over all.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika. Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Garnish with cilantro.
Serve with white rice and garden salad.

title: sausage and potatoes
directions: Saute the onions in the bacon fat until crisp and tender.
Add the bell pepper, parsley and garlic and stir.
Add the sausage and stir again.
Add the potatoes, soy sauce, hot sauce and apple juice.
Stir; cover and simmer for about 1 hour.

title: corn casserole
directions: Stir together.
Bake in a greased 8 x 8-inch dish or pan at 350° until brown.

title: instant nog
directions: In a large bowl, beat pudding mix, sugar, vanilla, milk and egg yolks.
Carefully fold in egg whites.
Chill thoroughly.

title: cherry fluff
directions: Mix together pie filling, pineapple, condensed milk, pecans and marshmallows.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for an hour before serving to set.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix well.
If too thick, add a little more milk; if too thin, add powdered sugar until stiff, but spreadable.
Spread over warm rolls.

title: chicken squares
directions: Boil the chicken until tender and pull off the bones.
Mix the cream cheese, onion and pimentos.
Put a ball of the chicken mixture into the center of each dinner roll.
Fold into squares. Put a pat of butter on each and bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: crunch pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and flour alternately.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sour cream mini muffins
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into greased mini muffin tin and bake at 400° for approximately 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes approximately 36.

title: vegetable delight
directions: Saute garlic until lightly brown.
Add all vegetables and saute until cooked.
Can be added to rice or pasta.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and oil.
Add egg yolks and beat until lemony yellow.
Add sour cream and flour into which soda has been sifted.
Add vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter.
Bake in a 10-inch tube pan at 300° for 90 minutes.

title: sauerkraut hot dish
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Mix soups with a little milk in a saucepan and warm slightly.
In a large baking dish layer:
ground beef-onion mixture, sauerkraut and drained noodles. Pour soup mixture over layers.
Cover well.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake 30 minutes more.
Bake with lid on baking dish.

title: shrimp and fruit salad
directions: Cook shrimp in boiling water about 3 minutes or until pink. Drain; rinse in cold water; drain well.
Next, drain pineapple (reserve juice).
Combine pineapple and orange.
Cover and chill. Combine 1/4 cup pineapple juice, mint, salt and pepper.
Stir in shrimp and celery.
Marinate in refrigerator for 2 hours; drain. Combine 2 tablespoons pineapple juice and yogurt.
Stir together with drained shrimp mixture and fruit.
Chill overnight.

title: chuck wagon stew
directions: Thoroughly brown meat on all sides in hot oil; add water, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, onion and seasonings.
Simmer 2 hours, stirring occasionally to keep from sticking.
Add vegetables; continue cooking until done.
Remove meat and vegetables; thicken liquid for gravy.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs one at a time and mix well.
Add milk and extract.
Add all dry ingredients last.
Place batter in tube pan and put in cold oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool 20 minutes before removing from pan.

title: carmelitas
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in large mixing bowl and beat at low speed until well blended.
Spread evenly in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: black walnut dessert
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add baking powder and sugar to egg whites, then add 3/4 teaspoon vinegar. Roll the soda crackers, not too fine.
Add the nuts.
Combine mixtures and bake in pie tin at 300° for 35 minutes. Serve with whipped cream.

title: pumpkin cupcakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into cupcake papers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
While noodles are cooking, make cheese sauce.

title: judy's specialty
directions: Brown chicken breast; cut into strips.
Cook noodles. Add herb season sauce.
Add frozen peas.
Add chicken soup.
Mix together. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: homemade root beer
directions: Mix all ingredients in a gallon jar.
Cover with the lid; set it in the hot sun for 4 hours.
Chill.
Serve after setting for 24 hours.

title: cheese stuffed mushrooms
directions: Select firm white mushrooms with caps that are closed or slightly open around the stem.
Cut ends from mushroom stems; remove from mushrooms and chop finely.
Cook and stir mushroom stems, green onions and garlic in butter over medium heat until tender, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients.
Fill mushroom caps with stuffing mixture.
Place filled sides up in greased baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 24 appetizers.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Put margarine in a large casserole dish and melt in oven.
Dip chicken in flour and place skin side down in dish.
Bake uncovered for 30 minutes at 425°.
Then turn chicken and bake 15 minutes longer at 425°.
In bowl, mix cheese, milk, soup and salt.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: fortune cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Add egg whites in 3 parts, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Add flour and beat thoroughly.

title: "crab" newburg
directions: In large skillet, melt butter/margarine.
Add pepper, sliced mushrooms.
Saute about 5 minutes.
Stir flour and cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add milk and continue stirring until sauce is smooth and thickened.
Add dry white wine and salt.
Add frozen imitation crab legs.
Cut diagonally into 1-inch slices.
Simmer just until crab is heated through, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: mexican fiesta biscuit bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spread melted margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Separate dough into 13 biscuits.
Snip each biscuit into eighths, using kitchen cutters.
Place biscuit pieces in bowl. Toss with 1 3/4 cups of salsa.
Spoon evenly into baking pan. Sprinkle with cheese, bell pepper, onions and olives.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes or until edges are deep golden brown and center is set.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Cut into squares with serrated bread knife.
Serve with cup of salsa.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: impossible coconut custard pie
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender; blend well.
Pour this into a 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: italian scalidi(honey covered cookies)
directions: Beat egg yolks well.
Add baking powder, butter and anise oil; mix until creamy.
Add as much flour as beater will take and then turn dough on floured board and add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Roll out dough; cut into thin strips and form into pretzel shape.
Deep fry until golden brown.
When cool, coat with honey.

title: sugarless apple cookies
directions: In a large saucepan, combine dates, apples, raisins and water. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; cool.
Combine flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt (if desired).
Stir into apple mixture and mix well.
Combine eggs and sweetener; add to batter.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a nonstick baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yield:
2 dozen.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat caramels, water and butter in double boiler.
Add together sugar, salt, vanilla and eggs, then add this to caramel mixture.
Add pecans, then pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°, then reduce to 350° and bake 20 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder and soda; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Add mashed bananas. Beat.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until very soft and peel while hot.
Mash together potatoes, butter and oil.
Mix sugar, flour, nutmeg and cinnamon and add to potato mixture.
Add half and half, eggs (slightly beaten) and vanilla to mixture.
Blend and pour into pie shells.
Sprinkle top with a little bit of sugar and nutmeg.
Cook at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until brown on top.

title: cheese pie
directions: Beat egg whites separately and add last.
Bake at 375° until set.
Makes two 8-inch pies.

title: gourmet rice
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a greased casserole at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Add water if necessary.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed; pour half in 9 x 13-inch pan (greased).
Bake for 15 minutes, cool.
Melt caramels, butter and evaporated milk.
Cool and pour over the top of the baked layer. Put chocolate chips and nuts on caramel layer.
Pour remaining batter on top and finish baking.

title: hot mushroom turnovers
directions: Early in day or 2 hours before serving:
In large bowl, with electric mixer at medium speed, beat cream cheese, 1/2 cup butter or margarine and 1 1/2 cups flour until soft dough forms.
Wrap dough in waxed paper; refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add 1/3 cup buttermilk, shortening and bananas and mix for 2 minutes. Add 1/3 cup buttermilk and eggs and beat for 2 minutes.
Fold in pecans and pour into greased Bundt pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: quiche lorraine(makes 6 servings)
directions: Place pie crust in 9-inch pie plate according to package directions.
Brush pie crust with egg white.
Then prick pie crust with fork; set aside.

title: zucchini walnut bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Gradually add sugar, then oil.
Combine dry ingredients; add to first mixture alternately with zucchini.
Stir in raisins, walnuts and vanilla.
Put into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake on lowest rack at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or 2 small loaves at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
May be brushed with juice of lemon and/or sugar after baking.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Boil sugar and molasses together for five minutes (not any longer).
Remove from heat.
Add butter and baking soda.
Stir mixture until it becomes foamy; pour over the popcorn and mix well.
Wet hands with cold water to form corn balls.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Mix and let stand 4 to 5 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: buster bar dessert
directions: Mix butter and Oreo cookie crumbs.
Spread in pan.
Spread ice cream over cookie mixture.
Sprinkle peanuts over ice cream.
Pour chocolate syrup on top.
Freeze until hard.

title: spinach-artichoke casserole
directions: Combine spinach and artichokes.
Combine cream cheese and next 3 ingredients.
Stir into spinach mixture.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake additional 10 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: swedish nuts
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Core and quarter the apples; do not peel.
Place the apples in a 3-quart buttered baking dish.

title: stir-fry vegetables
directions: Mix salt, cornstarch, chicken broth, soy sauce and m.s.g.
Set aside.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in wok.
Add carrots and stir-fry for 30 seconds.
Add mushrooms and stir-fry for 30 seconds.
Add remaining vegetables and stir-fry for 1 minute.
Add liquid mixture and stir-fry for another minute.
Remove from heat.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream the cream cheese with butter; add sugar and then nuts. Add a small amount of cream to bring mixture to spreading consistency.

title: chicken parmesan hoagie(lo-cal)
directions: In small saucepan over medium heat, bring the tomato sauce, tomato paste, onion, garlic, 1/2 teaspoon dried oregano and the red pepper flakes to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 2 minutes. Preheat broiler and line broiler pan with foil.
In a nonstick skillet, bring chicken broth and sherry to a boil; add chicken, the remaining oregano and pepper.
Cook until done.
Remove chicken and place on the broiler pan; spread each piece with 1/4 of sauce and sprinkle with 1/4 of Parmesan, then top with Mozzarella slice; broil 15 seconds.
Place on a roll.
Serve immediately.

title: hot salsa (ciordia)
directions: Place jalapenos, onions and vinegar in large nonaluminum pan. Simmer, partly covered, until soft.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer about 40 minutes, until thickened and well-seasoned.
Pack into jars and seal.
Process in boiling water bath 35 minutes. Yields 22 cups.

title: cream of vegetable soup
directions: In a large kettle or Dutch oven, saute onion in butter until tender.
Add flour.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Gradually add chicken broth.
Cook and stir until thickened, about 5 minutes. Stir in the milk, cream, basil salt, pepper and garlic powder. Add the vegetables.
Cook gently until heated through.
Do not boil.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Crumble Ritz crackers in a bowl.
Add chopped walnuts and baking powder to the cracker mix.
In another bowl beat egg whites until foamy, add sugar to egg whites gradually until stiff.
Fold in vanilla.
Add this mixture to the cracker crumbs.
Put into well-greased pie plate and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Humm, humm good!

title: mother michel's mess for 20
directions: Brown & drain ground beef.
Stir all ingredients together in large pan and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pork in a bun
directions: In skillet on medium-high heat and in salad oil, cook cutlets until browned on all sides, turning once.
Place cutlets in buns and keep warm.
Heat to medium the drippings in skillet; stir in catsup, molasses and lemon juice.
Heat to boiling, stirring.
Add salt and pepper to fried cutlets.
Spoon sauce over meat in each bun.

title: the easiest lasagna
directions: Brown turkey in medium skillet; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and 1 cup water.
Boil; reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes. Lightly spray 9 x 13-inch pan with vegetable cooking spray. Spread 1 1/2 cups sauce on bottom.
Arrange 1/2 the uncooked noodles on sauce.
Spread with half cottage cheese.
Sprinkle with half the oregano and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers with remaining ingredients.
Cover with foil; refrigerate overnight. Uncover.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes and cheese is lightly golden.
Remove from oven and let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
Makes 12 servings.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Stir gently.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs.
Peel and remove yolks.
Mash; add salt, pepper, mayo and sugar.
Stir well.
Put back in egg whites.

title: salmon steaks with tarragon butter
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Spread over salmon steaks. Cook with grill lid open over medium-hot coals (350° to 400°) for 10 minutes on each side.
Yields 4 servings.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Add additional milk to thin batter, if necessary.
Batter should resemble pancake batter.
Working in batches, dip tomato slices into batter.
Fry in 2-inches of hot oil in a large heavy skillet until browned, turning once carefully with tongs.
Transfer to a colander to drain.
To keep from getting soggy, stand tomatoes up like wheels instead of stacking.

title: brownies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine. Add eggs and beat. Add melted chocolate; beat. Add flour and nuts. Stir until well mixed. Spread onto a greased baking sheet. (Cookie sheet with sides.) Bake at 350° for 20 minutes (no longer or they will be overdone).

title: raisin pudding
directions: Cream 1 tablespoon butter with the sugar.
Add the milk, then the sifted dry ingredients.
Blend together.
Mix in the vanilla, then stir in the raisins and walnuts, if desired.
Spread in the bottom of a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mix the brown sugar with the remaining 2 tablespoons butter and the 2 cups boiling water in a saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until dissolved.
Pour carefully over the top of batter and bake for 1/2 hour in a 375° oven.
Good warm with cream or ice cream!

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions. Add corn and chili. Alternate in casserole the Fritos, meat mixture and cheese. Pour enchilada sauce over everything.
Heat for approximately 30 minutes at 370°.

title: cheese filled jumbo shells
directions: Cook shells according to package; drain.
Cool on a single layer on wax paper or aluminum foil to keep shells from sticking together.
Combine cheeses, eggs, parsley, oregano, salt and pepper.
Fill each shell with about 2 tablespoons cheese mixture. Spread a thin layer of sauce on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Place shells, open side down, in a single layer in the pan.
Cover with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Cover with aluminum foil; bake at 350° about 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Fills about 36 shells.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: ham ball
directions: Cream mayonnaise and cream cheese together.
Add ham.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll into a ball.
Chill overnight and then roll on chopped pecans.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: sausage squares
directions: Brown sausage and drain fat.
Add cheese.
Mix until melted. Spread mixture on cocktail bread.
Can be frozen.
Bake until brown on top.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs on high speed 5 minutes; gradually add sugar, mixing thoroughly.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to pumpkin mixture.
Spread evenly in a well-greased and floured 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
(If desired, you may sprinkle 1 cup finely chopped pecan on batter before baking.)
Turn cake out onto a tea towel well dusted with powdered sugar.
Roll up in towel and cool completely.
Unroll and spread with filling and re-roll.
Chill thoroughly.

title: prime rib roast
directions: Season roast with salt and pepper.
Place fat side up in roasting pan.
Insert meat thermometer into thickest part; make sure it does not rest on bone or fat.
Do not add water; do not wrap in foil.
Roast in 325° oven for desired doneness.
The meat thermometer will register 140° for rare, 160° for medium and 170° for well done.

title: low-fat pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl and chill.

title: quick barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger and add salt and pepper to taste.
Combine rest of ingredients and pour over meat.
Cook until well blended.

title: date squares
directions: Put half on bottom and rest on top of filling.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pinch off enough to make 1-inch balls. Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes or roll out the dough and cut into small biscuits and bake.

title: shrimp sauteed with wine and mushrooms
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in pan.
Add mushrooms, green onions and basil; saute about 5 minutes.
Dredge shrimp in flour, saute in mushroom pan until just cooked through (2 minutes).
Add wine, 4 tablespoons butter, lemon juice and parsley.
Mix and serve over cooked rice.
Serves 2.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Slice apples thin and put in baking dish.
Sprinkle sugar over apples.
Also sprinkle some brown sugar and cinnamon.
Mix flour, oil and enough water to make a thin batter; pour over mixture. Pour 1/2 cup hot water over this and bake at 350° until done, but not brown.
Dot with butter and turn oven to broil until brown.

title: cold water cocoa cake
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, butter, salt and eggs.
Add water and flour alternately.
Add
soda
water and vanilla (use an electric mixer for best results).	Bake in greased tube pan for 40 minutes at 375°.
Pour chocolate glaze over it.

title: quick and easy fruit cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spoon filling into 8 or 9-inch square pan. Stir together Bisquick, milk, sugar and margarine with fork until blended.
Drop by spoonfuls on top of filling.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, until golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: crunchy vegetables
directions: Mix cream cheese and vegetables.
Present with favorite crackers, bread or bagels.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O, sugar and salt in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Chill until it starts to set and add apples, bananas and pineapple and set until firm.
Mix and cook until thickened the pineapple juice, flour, sugar and egg.
Cool, then add Cool Whip and spread over Jell-O and sprinkle with crushed nuts.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Toast 1/2 cup coconut 5 minutes or until lightly brown; set aside. Bake pastry shell 8 minutes; cool slightly.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and form mixture into loaves.
Wrap in wax paper and store in refrigerator overnight, then slice very thin and bake in 375° oven until cookies are a very light brown.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Don't make too stiff.
Let stand overnight.
Next day, roll out to 1/4-inch deep.
Cut into rounds and bake 10 to 12 minutes in 350° oven.
Don't overbake.
Keeps well.

title: buttermilk pecan pie
directions: Cream the butter and sugar, adding sugar 1/2 cup at a time. Add eggs, stirring them in one at a time.
Combine flour and salt, then add to mixture.
Stir in buttermilk, then pecans.
Mixture will be thin.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours, until dark golden brown.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: gold cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream in butter and sugar.
Gradually beat egg yolks until as thick as mayonnaise. Add to mixture.
Beat thoroughly. Add milk and flavoring and mix well.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: chinese pork and vegetables
directions: Press garlic cloves; sliver carrots and bell pepper.
Drain pineapple, reserving 3 tablespoons juice.
Mix juice, 1/2 cup water, soy sauce, vinegar and pepper flakes; set aside.
Cut pork loin in strips and brown in hot oil.
Add garlic and ginger.
Cook 1 minute.
Add onion and carrots; cook 1 minute.
Add sauce, pineapple, bell pepper and snow peas.
Cook until sauce boils and thickens.
Serves 4.

title: french blueberry pie
directions: Crush crackers to make 1 1/2 cups.
In bowl, mix cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 cup melted margarine.
Mix with fork.
Press firmly in a 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool 45 minutes.
In large bowl, mix powdered sugar, vanilla and cream cheese; fold into the whipping cream (which you have already whipped) until blended.
Pour into the cooled crust and spoon the blueberry pie filling over all.
Chill several hours.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Bring to a boil the cranberries.
Add jello until dissolved in 3/4 cup water.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Mix and chill.
